k9kUEjBcp-mxkWDyxueJQA.text: My wife and I had breakfast at Snooze at ASU on Sunday and loved it! We shared the incredibly good 3-pancake flight with blueberry Danish, sweet potato, and chocolate choices. We added sides of perfect hash browns and extra-crispy bacon. Wow!   Our server was superb and Snooze has a nice buzz about it. We plan to go back with family and friends! Parking nearby was easy with meters along the street.   Snooze is one of the very best!

MiM7g9J7xqKugaazDt_B5g.text: My experience at Snooze was vastly different that my breakfast the prior day. That place wasn't bad, just over hyped. It did gave me a 'C' baseline to compare. The snooze decor is, 'up beat' in a late 60's space Era, Tupperware colors kind of way. I liked it. Service was great. Lyle was friendly, knowledgeable about the menu, and gave us a complimentary pancake to sample. It was whiskey, maple, white chocolate chip something. Damn awesome is what it was. My wife and I snacked part of it down as an appetizer and the rest as dessert. I love the fact they let you mix and match both pancakes and Benedict items. I couldn't decide between the Steak or Chile Verde Benedict so I got one of each. They were both excellent. My wife got the shrimp and grits special and it was also very good. There is pet friendly outdoor seating which is always a good thing whether you prefer to dine near or far from our 4 legged pals. Strongly suggest you give them a try.

cpJBlNnswgvg-UEuXiGqSw.text: The place was busy when we got here but was seated after 15 minutes and the waiter Jason aka Flip was amazing!! We went there for my daughters 24th birthday and he made it special!!!

HxO-C3HbRQnzpkC4ZJ_HKw.text: One of my favorite spots! Great food, great service and cool environment  for you and your four legged friends. I haven't had a bad meal there yet, all very fresh and I would highly recommend their breakfast tacos.  It does get pretty busy so get there earlier to avoid a wait ( they do not take reservations)

h89peYAa7PJiQh2a9mwU0g.text: Excellent food and service. We had a party of six people and took only 20 minutes for a table on a Saturday morning at 10am. The staff were all great. You can really tell that they enjoy working there. We ordered the pancake flight with chocolate chip, blueberry danish and the special bacon (who doesn't love bacon. We also ordered the Snooze Spuds and 3 egg omelette. Everything we had was delicious and not one bite was left behind. I would return again the next time I am in Tempe.

XmbYYXN_-7gnkC-rEvOHvQ.text: BACKGROUND There is no cooler place to eat pancakes in all of Phoenix than Snooze. SNOOZE AM EATERY: THE HISTORY Snooze has locations in Colorado, California and 4 in the Phoenix area (Camelback, College, Gilbert and Kierland). Every Snooze has the iconic super hype decor and edgy lighting. (see pics) And of course, their amazing menu which includes all sorts of yummy eggs and hollandaise specials, sandwiches and many sides, BUT LET'S TALK ABOUT THE PANCAKES!! Pineapple Upside Down Pancakes Sweet Potato Pancakes Drunken Punk'n Pancakes Blueberry Danish Pancakes Pancake of the Day Chocolate Chip Pancakes Peanut Butter Cup Pancakes And my favorite: Pancake Flight - which is where you can chose any 3 from above! (see pics) And my next favorite: The huge selection of breakfast cocktails: various mimosas, bloodys and mules. (see pics) CONCLUSION This is the type of place you can eat at as many times as you want and never get bored. The service is always decent. Prices are very reasonable. 5/5 RECOMMEND OF NOTE *Tip: Don't be surprised if you have to wait a bit for the morning rush on the weekends. *Hours: 6:30am - 2:30pm Daily *For more information: SnoozeEatery.com

8B669-elhbWtl12LxARICA.text: I loved this place! The I had the breakfast tacos and they were so filling and delicious. The wait staff was great. They were soooo busy but we didn't have to wait long for our food or drinks. It's a great place for families and a fun place for brunch!!

YPsRAmHQTqIZhjpnNOZl9Q.text: very upset i go to snooze 2-3 times a week. i order through doordash and they charge me extra because i ordered a different pancake of the day. when i go there in person they never charge extra

dDq_nbkQRPygF-36ZMIPhA.text: I'm not sure how I'm so late to the show here.  This place is GREAT.  It's packed as hell, You *will* wait, but it's worth it.  Great service, awesome old school vibe (it's like being on the Jetson's set) and even better is the food.  We split the pancake flight:  the Sinful (cinnamon, bacon, pecans), Pineapple Upside Down and the Pumpkin with white chocolate chips and some other stuff.  The Sinful was my absolute favorite. This is a huge amount of very very rich pancakes that you could easily share with someone.   We *also* split the breakfast pot pie.  YUM.  I loved that it was open faced, served on a fluffy, buttery puff pastry.  They also top it with eggs, but I detest any runny yolk so I got them scrambled on the side. I loved the pot pie and it wasn't too too filling (in a good way). This place has a variety of morning drinks (mimosas and such) and are really reasonably priced.   This will be a regular on my brunch lineup!

CeUP0mhLBvw6QJrJf5kcnQ.text: I leave Snooze with few regrets and with much to celebrate. I've been here three times now, trying different dishes each time, including the spuds deluxe, shrimp and grits, chili verde benedict, corned beef hash, and many of the pancakes. Each meal has been utterly transcendental. But my favorite are the breakfast tacos, with corned beef.

8bCZl7GVhhEUw8-Osi4V-A.text: My favorite breakfast place to go in Arizona!! food is always spectacular. Service is typical average nothing to special there but the food is well worth every second you spend there!!!

o-woqkQ7NT9v7n5vVnnECg.text: Great variety of breakfast food options!  Their mimosas are especially delicious with fresh takes on them using a variety of juices.  I am a fan of eggs Benedict so their vast variety makes my favorite dish fresh every time I come in to eat.  Would highly recommend for a delicious breakfast with great ingredients.

PlB7cAFy42PddZVg7iTAcg.text: I've been to snooze a bunch of times because, well, because some friends of mine love it. Because it's in the neighborhood. And because Tempe is desperately short on great breakfast options.   I know people love snooze, I know, but I just can't get past a few things:  1. The hash browns. They are not crispy. Ever. Actually they are totally bland.   2. While the egg benedict options are good, most of them leave me feeling really heavy after breakfast. This stands to reason to an extent, but I've had Benedicts that are not this way.   3. There is an absence of anything really great. Almost everything on the menu I have ordered (all of the Benedicts, sausage, pancakes, French toast, bacon) are ok or good. But not great.

h0PPcWF_3lBjp4cBXNSeXw.text: Probably the best breakfast I have had in awhile! Was so amazing I wish I could make you taste it while reading this review. I got the snooze classic and my man got the steak & eggs benny! They both were perfection! Our server was amazing as well, very down to earth and super nice. We will definitely be back. I honestly do not know how anyone could rate this place any less than 5 stars. We are impressed!

-s120C-HdwLealjEIBZ05Q.text: Snooze is a fun place. There's sort of a vintage, 60s vibe about it. Personally, I love the sweet stuff, so I usually get a flight of pancakes (you can pick any three pancakes you like!) My boyfriend likes to get something more savory, like a burrito or chilaquiles. I feel like there's something for everyone at snooze!   It's usually super busy, but it's worth your wait.

7XD15S7GRH7AagKTE6s0dw.text: The wait was a little long but what can you expect when you go to such a great restaurant! the staff is also very nice and attentive, I will definitely continue to keep going

Their morning booze game is fantastic.  I mean someone seriously went out of their way to make sure your hair of the dog tastes good. I'd suggest you get their early and sit outside before that Tempe heat gets you.  Love this place.

4nysPTZk3YIJ_EZNrEogOQ.text: I was so happy to see Snooze come to AZ. The servers here are so friendly and you must try the barbacoa eggs Benedict. The only reason I knocked a star was due to location. It's on campus so parking can be a bit of a nightmare at certain times.

VgQK-vxlnyDcs1kfKmJGHg.text: Hands down best breakfast/brunch experience I've ever had. The food is phenomenal and the staff is warm and welcoming. P7aGqaX_3MWhWaICIudUEg.text: One of the best breakfasts in town. The corn beef hash is to die for. The service was spot on, great toast, great coffee, even has great swag. Not one to miss!

QddJah967xJ6C7VoECYUpg.text: I love this place! But when I went to the Denver location tempe's just kinda fell flat in comparison. Still good food just WOW to Denver and the service is alright, Id say it's off and on. They get busy and the servers get noticeably overwhelmed like I think they under staff. But if you go at the right time then your server will usually chat be attentive and go above expectations:)

RU_fKBzIGE34e3SyxZzzEg.text: Another gem that Yelp led me to.  Saw the ratings and decided to check this place out...a hipster, cool breakfast joint with amazing menu choices and great atmosphere.  I had the Hashbrown plate, topped with 2 sunny-side up eggs and added hickory sausage gravy and bacon.  Now if you are a "carbophobe" I would suggest you not order, but if amazing spuds are your weakness you won't go wrong.  The plate came loaded with country-style hashbrowns and my guess is 50000+ grams of carbs (at least) :).  Also ordered a cappuccino and was pleasantly surprised with it's somewhat chocolatey flavor that was unusual in a great way.  Breakfast for one with cappuccino and tip was $20, but very well worth it. A couple of things to note: 1.  My Google map app was trying to take me wayyyy off course, so I am not sure if it was just my phone or if it's a Google map defect?  If you are unfamiliar with the area around ASU be careful you don't get sent to East Bumble F by your phone.  Take University to College Ave, go north on College and it's on the right near the aquatic center 2. There is no parking lot so you either park on the street near the restaurant or there is a parking deck on the little street behind the restaurant.  If you choose street parking the parking spots are metered and will take coins or, get this, will accept your phone reading a QR code to bill the parking fee.  I had no spare change and my phone would not read the code so I headed over to the deck and lo-and-behold...parking was free (it was Saturday morning, 8.30am and evidently not a "game day").  BTW the restaurant is maybe a block from Sun Devil Stadium so I can only imagine the mess it would be when the Sun Devils are playing at home. I LOVE SNOOZE AM!  Definitely a chain that would dominate if it goes nationwide!

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Hashbrown Heaven!!

7TTHcwWZBB2kuxSawJHegg.text: We first tried this restaurant in Denver and gave it 5 stars. While visiting ASU, we were ecstatic to find a location on campus. We placed our name on the list and were told it was about an hour and fifteen minute wait.    We weren't deterred because if it was good as Denver, it would be worth the wait.  We returned from walking around the campus in the estimated time and were seated shortly after.  As with Denver, the wait was worth it.  Friendly staff and great food! The French toast is a must try and is our favorite.

8ZLAL6mByGQAuRbfc00XNg.text: YES to their pancakes YES to their sandwiches. Eggs Benedict wasn't my favorite. If you're looking for some tasty breakfast you didn't have to make yourself, it perfectly hits the spot.

TmaKGsRJfvlJu0rBEgMQEQ.text: I heard about this place from some friends and was anxious to try it when visiting Arizona. And it did not disappoint!  There was a little bit of a wait to get seated but we ended up sitting at a shared high top table which was fine with us.  There were a variety of delicious options to choose from on the menu, along with some tasty mimosas! My husband and I both tried versions of Eggs Benedict. I had the Early Harvest Benny and he had the Benny Duo - Ham Benedict III and Chile Verde Benny. Both meals were excellent! Great flavors and very reasonably priced. I loved the griddles cauliflower, green harissa and poblano pepper quinoa cakes! I really wish there was a Snooze in GA so I could try some of their other delicious menu items!

4n6BQpv4zCl-AVxf08oOCg.text: My boyfriend and I both had work off yesterday, which happened to be a Monday (we typically don't have Mondays off so we wanted to take advantage!). Based on a quick Yelp search, we decided to try breakfast at Snooze. Being a Monday at 10:30, I didn't anticipate how busy this place would be! Granted, we are in a college town and in the thick of things at ASU where most students don't have a traditional schedule, but looking around there were people of all ages filling up the place. The wait was only about 10 minutes and while I would have loved to sit on their beautiful, tree-filled patio, we settled for a booth in the corner inside as we were both famished.   I decided to go with the 3 egg omelet and added avocado, garlic and tomato. This came with a choice of toast (I picked sour dough) and hash browns. The boyfriend had one of their several unique eggs benedict options, choosing the Chili Verde Benny. I can't speak for him entirely, but he cleaned his plate in under 10 minutes. The hashbrowns arrived in a neat stack and the presentation was almost as great as the meal itself. The ingredients were incredibly fresh and well prepared. I realize this is breakfast and not a gourmet dining experience, but it was certainly one of the best breakfasts I've ever had.   Being a Monday, I decided to dry-out and opted for coffee - although they had a lot of enticing breakfast cocktail items. My breakfast date was a little more adventurous and tried the "Snooze Fashioned": Cyrus Noble Bourbon, Cold Brewed Coffee, Cherry Shurb and Bitters, which he very much enjoyed!  Lest I forget, the service was pretty spot on as well. I believe our servers name was Flip. He seemed almost as excited about the place as we were, and that was refreshing! He offered suggestions for future visits and was fun/attentive without being at all overbearing.  Needless to say, we will definitely be back. A great spot to bring family or friends who might be visiting from out of town :)

0kNnXNqARZ4iJLhxBs0w0Q.text: A first visit to this location.  Seated immediately indoors as patio was n/a.  Lots of friendly staff milling around but service was slow, especially from the kitchen.  The trio of tacos and shrimp grits bowl were well crafted.  The bacon & egg sandwich had a bit of a fishy taste.  Cocktail mixology good but the champagne glass was sticky on the outside.

o-0VKzsm--zwDlIwENeRAQ.text: Last day in Tempe and needed some breakfast before boarding the flight.  Stopped by snooze at about 845.   Place was packed so i figured the food was going to be great!   There were no seats left so we sat at the bar.  I ordered corned beef hash with eggs over hard, toast and coffee while my friend ordered french toast and juice.   The coffee came quickly but it was freezing cold outside so i drank the coffee as quickly as it was poured.  They never offered to refill my coffee.  The food finally came out.  The toast was warm and thick and covered in butter.   The eggs that i had asked overhard came out almost over done and scrambled.  The corned beef hash was almost non existent.  It was barly a spoonful.  Although the food did taste good, it was not what i expected.

npf57ov2XEsSqyO3Y9-CWQ.text: Awesome fun-filled food place. And great tasting food. I like the ping-ping table. Something to keep us entertained while we wait for our table.

nMz8oPPpJeJ64ecclvEORg.text: Convenient location near ASU.  Fun, energetic atmosphere and a great place to wake up and eat some awesome breakfast.  Lots of nearby parking.  Free WiFi.  Awesome coffee and espresso.

LJiKS-WiWBY8vSdkQ16KtQ.text: Wonderful! We had the corn beef hash and the eggs, bacon and toast with a blueberry pancake on the side!! Everything was cooked to perfection and even though it was a 30 minute wait-it was so worth it! Cam was our waiter and he was very nice and helpful!

8zxlzIe6vLZzC2nFyrBEPw.text: Long wait lines that are unavoidable, but great food and atmosphere. Come early to secure a spot on the waitlist and explore Mill while you wait

87pxHMFpP_QF9RzYLgz12Q.text: Absolutely delicious! Great selection & great service. Tons of vegan options also. I really enjoyed the outside heated patio. I highly recommend this place if you're around town. It was great people watching with the street traffic also.

MszsuabZmtI0TXkekF1IgQ.text: Snooze is my guilty pleasure breakfast place. I know I've been here way more than 3 times despite the check ins saying otherwise.  Anyway, there are two main routes you can take at Snooze: savory or sweet.  On the savory side you have classic eggs options, gargantuan burritos, and my personal favorite, the breakfast pot pie. The breakfast pot pie consists of a square puff pastry smothered in gravy, veggies, and replaces chicken with egg! You also get hash browns on the side.  On the sweet side of Snooze you have a wide variety of pancakes (the pancake flight is a crowd favorite), decadent French toast, and morning cocktails.  My favorite from this group is the pancake flight. Being able to select three types of pancakes the size of dinner plates is fun and the selection changes based on what is the pancake of the day. In my opinion though, you can't go wrong with the chocolate chip pan cakes. (Side note, while I haven't had it yet, there is some kind of caramel or cinnamon French toast that my friends swear by, worth checking out.)   Bonus: on Caturday all the staff wear cat inspired attire!

pcYGB6kdAqGs7Tt1BdsS0w.text: Food is good. But hostess SUCKS. No honest wait times??? That's all I ask for as a customer. 15-20 minutes turned into a WHOLE HOUR. I would have left if they didn't keep on saying "oh, just five more minutes" or "you're next up." Really aggravating all we ask for is honesty next time.

sGYxGTYq9bPZQUeHooyT2g.text: Sophie was our server and she was amazing. We were visiting from Oregon, in January, so we sat out on the patio and soaked up the sun. We got seated quickly, the drinks were delicious, and our breakfast was so very good. I wish I could've eaten it all. The hostess sent out a sweet potato pancake before our meal arrived and I almost rethought my eggs Benedict order. This isn't my 1st time to Snooze, but it was my 1st time at the Tempe location, both places have been 5 stars both times.

NcxjQ0EshfIwxOp0Bjq9Ww.text: Seems popular since there was a 45 minute wait when we went which as blamed on 'people just not leaving'. This was correct to a degree but quickly found out once we were seated that the reason people weren't leaving was because food came out so slow. After being seated we waited around 40 minutes for our food to come out.  My breakfast burrito was rubbish unfortunately. The chorizo was really not nice as it was cooked on it own and dumped into the burrito without being mixed with the eggs. It was overpowering and made the whole burrito taste like raw paprika. The green chile sauce wasn't great either and was poured onto the burrito with cheese sprinkled on top meaning if I didn't want to eat the chile I didn't get any cheese and the burrito desperately needed cheese.  Filling was boring in all honesty.  I ordered a hash brown on the side and boy, oh boy was I  disappointed. A thick circle of potato completely pale in colour and verging on undercooked.  No crisp or crunch, it was a potato cake and not a hash brown.  Girlfriend enjoyed her eggs benedict but once again it was nothing special at all. She was bothered that her eggs were over cooked and not runny at all but after waiting 40 minutes to be seated and 40 minutes for the food she didn't want to complain because she was starving.  All three of the pancakes from the pancake flight were too sweet for us but that's a personal preference. Our soft drinks and water were topped up quickly but the coffee wasn't refilled at all, not sure if there are no refills for coffee or they jus didn't notice but either way that kinda sucked.  Very average food and at $50 for two and a half people we wouldn't return ever.

-9gaN3M053Ab59RNKTyRIw.text: Been twice now and LOVEEE the corned beef hash and they have a pretty good bloody mary. A1 pancakes can't really go wrong food wise! The only reason I take off a star was the service we received at the bar. The first time we came in we had a super fun server (wish I remembered her name so I could give her the shoutout). But bartenders seemed extremely uninterested and I felt like I was pestering them every time I asked for something! Still an awesome breakfast place especially after old town.

So many for anyone, picky eaters adventurous eaters, vegetarians! I got the Benny Goodman and it was good! My boyfriend got the burrito if you like leftovers this is for you because it was massive ! kYdIjrpqBf7g54fXxO9Jng.text: Snooze is an amazing breakfast chain eatery that I've found in many cities and states,  this particular one was really nice. Huge outdoor patio,  inside was spacious,  clean,  wait wasn't too bad (I'm pregnant so waiting right now is hard for me),  Kimmy was great,  she got us seated right away,  chatted with us about the baby, and we got water right away.  We had the French toast with seasonal fruit and the hash browns with smothered gravy.  Probably the best French toast I have ever had in my entire life.   Our servers name was George and he was cool,  chill,  fast,  friendly,  and attentive.  We were very very happy with that experience and we both said we could eat that for breakfast everyday. We truly would.

631kimUadPJt6OxTcOLsgw.text: First time at Snooze AM. Four of us arrived at 10:30 on a Monday morning and we waited 20 mins (spring break).   Between us, we ordered Two Benny Duos, a Scramble, one order of Breakfast Tacos and three coffees plus an iced tea. It all came to $60 plus tip. Hopefully the food matched the price.   My Benny Duo was a Bela! Bela! Benedict plus a Chile Verde Benedict. The Bela was excellent: good balance of flavors, texture and spices. The bread was toasted just right, the hollandaise was rich and thick. The chile verde was good as well but I had just had pulled pork for dinner the night before so it didn't thrill.   The order came with a side of arugula drizzled with balsamic vinegar, which was a good foil to the thick sauces.   The other dishes got good responses from my family. The service was almost adequate but a bit hurried. Too bad. For a $60 breakfast I would like at least some attention.   I would recommend Snooze AM for brunch but try to avoid busy times.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. First part of the menu, for breakfast.

djdb5sK3xIUcEw6nOD-mhA.text: I don't eat breakfast, except for Snooze. The OMG French Toast is the best breakfast food ever created!!!   Such a fun breakfast/brunch spot with delicious food and coffees. My go to AM food spot to take family and friends.

waN0bEfL4f1frYWlTT4MuQ.text: Located next to the Fulton center Parking, they serve solid breakfast here. Came here after the race day 2 during RNR AZ marathon as I parked at the Fulton parking in the morning. Walking back from Tempe park, I wanted to stop for breakfast sooner but I didn't have money with me, I had to go back to my car first to get my credit card. Conveniently located next to where I parked, this restaurant was perfect as I didn't have to walk anymore.  Initially I was told 20 mins wait, but they have some seats available with bar height chairs, I was told they were first come first served. Shortly after I sat down, friendly server came to take an order. She was extremely busy but her service was prompt.   Food is excellent. We had pinnacle upside down pancake and ham Benedict, both tasted very good, solid breakfast.  Porched egg was cooked perfect, good sauce, I also enjoyed their hash browns. Good textures.  Good portion size, definitely hit the spot after running.  Parking was free for runners when I arrived at 6:30am but notice they charge $5 for special event when I came back. Not sure how much is parking normally.  I always thought Tempe is just a college town and never ventured out here but now I know, I would like to explore this area more.

qnfZdFJyWTGKw3jvi0z02A.text: Normally I love this place and it is a frequent go-to for breakfast or brunch! Convenient location, trendy ambience, cool staff, and good food and fun drinks. Unfortunately this time was just something else. A friend and I went in for some Saturday morning breakfast ordered water, orange juice, and I got an iced coffee. I received my coffee after about 10 minutes but we didnt receive the orange juice or water for even more time. Minor issue, so we looked past it and ordered some breakfast tacos. Some time later our food was delivered to our table, presented perfectly, we pick up our tacos and sad to say they break in an instant. We ordered corn tortillas, but the tortillas were soggy when we got them so we ended up eating our tacos with forks. Ate one taco, decided to take the rest to go, and while boxing up my pico on my taco I noticed a big black hair.  Unfortunately my friend and I are both blonde or else I would have been less disgusted by the hair I found in my food. Needless to say I ended up tossing those leftovers.

H1cIlAy_cgRTkQZh7O5s4A.text: Snooze has a pretty trendy atmosphere overall. Well decorated with a light and bright feel throughout. It's located basically on ASU campus. I came in on a Sunday afternoon and they told me it was going to be a 45 minute wait and considering the area, I'm sure that's pretty typical. The good news is it only ended up being a 20 minute wait. Not much seating in the tiny waiting area but I was lucky enough to snag a chair. Free wifi that you don't need a code for, and I thought it was cool that they text you when your table is ready so you don't have to sit there and wait for your name to be called or carry around one of those weird little things that vibrate.   We sat outside and even though it was like 98 degrees, sitting under the umbrella was surprisingly not that hot. I ordered the Sandwich I Am with a Pineapple Upside Down Pancake.  Everything was FANTASTIC. The pancake was unbelievably tasty. Might sound stupid but it tasted exactly like...you guessed it...pineapple upside down cake! The consistency was perfect and the cinnamon butter on top was delicious. My Sandwich I Am was sort of like a McDonald's sausage and egg biscuit but with real ingredients, and I mean that in a good way. Loved the pretzel bread bun. The hash browns were on point too.   I've gotta comment on our server, Jenna. She was awesome. Super friendly, gave thoughtful recommendations, all around great customer service. She even hooked it up with her favorite pancake since we're out of towners and don't have the pleasure of experiencing Snooze whenever we please. Super cool.   I'm legitimately salty that I don't live here and probably won't be able to visit Snooze AM again for quite some time. Keep it up y'all!  Here's my overall ratings: Atmosphere- 4/5 Quality/value- 4.5/5 Food- 4.5/5 Service- 4.5/5 Coffee- 4/5

We were instantly greeted by our server Spinsa, and she quickly returned with large mugs of coffee.  The menu appropriately features all you could want for breakfast, we both decided on eggs benedict specials. Plus, we saw their pancakes and had to split an order between us.  This place has it going on, and it is worth it. There was always a wait to be seated, but most were seated in a good time.  Great coffee, delicious breakfast, efficient and friendly service. We will return.

NLC1MzIm3Q-aV67VtV-jcQ.text: Came here for breakfast on a busy Saturday. I knew it was going to be impossible to get a table but my friend and I really wanted to try this place out since she came in from California. There was a 45 min wait and I said first available is fine. We sat outside in the blistering heat waiting patiently. One of the servers that was outside asked us if we wanted water because he knew we had been waiting for awhile. Tons of parties kept coming and going. Then I noticed we still haven't been called so I went and checked. The girl upfront I can tell was flustered and had a attitude for me asking. When I said my name she kept looking for it and I noticed 4 parties behind us with the same amount of people were sat and had their food. That pissed me off and then to top it off a guy comes up and said well we can do first available. Funny to think I thought I was waiting for that. Then he hits me with it will another 20 more mins. I said "again I have to wait after 45 mins" and the girl said well there's a table outside in the corner. Clearly they don't know what first come means. We ended up getting the sweet server who offered us water and he was very quick with getting everything out in a timely manner. I would give this place more stars but after that experience it's only worth a three.

f5TpA6zgcu0qaFQ5kQyNNg.text: I've been to both locations before and the food is always fantastic, so no complaints there. Because I loved it so much, I brought my mom yesterday to the Tempe location.   The food was outstanding as always, but the service was pretty terrible. In fact the last time I went to the Tempe location I had the same server and thought that the service was bad, but it was very busy so I cut the guy some slack. Yesterday, however, was not busy and the service was still poor. So poor in fact my mom doesn't want to go back because of how awkward and uninviting our server was.  As I'm writing this I looked on my receipt for his name and noticed that it says: Hotline Bling. Guess that's the kind of service I should expect from a name like that.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. The service from &#34;Hotline Bling&#34; was awkward and terrible. With a name like that I guess you shouldn&#39;t expect a whole lot.

8LQjvERZE8x1aPfWS4eImw.text: Let me make this very very clear:  This is the BEST food you will ever have in your life.  Ok, now that we have that established...let me take some time to convince you as to why.  The Pineapple upside down pancakes are so good that every other pancake for the rest of your life will be dry and tasteless in comparison. Unless of course you can convince the chef to make you coffee and donut pancakes. Also FREAKING amazing.  The sandwich I am, three egg scramble, upstream benny (or ANY of the benny's for that matter) are slap yo mama good.  Oh and the best part? A Colorado based company!! When I moved from Denver a couple of years ago, I was devestated (no, but really, I was) that I wouldn't get to make my regular weekend stop into Snooze. And lo and behold, they came to Arizona! This is the second location in the valley. The other location is off of 20th and Camelback.  Just a side note, the wait times can be a little long, but I GUARANTEE that every minute is worth it when you take your first bite. Guarantee it.

Ik4m6cnFqmIXJNe2utVthQ.text: Can you say overrated? Why people eat here will always puzzle me. I would rather go to Denny's because at least their food comes out warm and the hash browns have some flavor. Tried this place twice now and will not return.

Note to mgr: manage for excellent service, not for pretending you are having a party at your house and everyone is your best friend.

xX4NltNfTM3vrNsEIOoDtQ.text: Stopped for breakfast on a Saturday morning before there was a wait for a table. There was a wait as we were leaving. Everything was very good... great service, and great food. We enjoyed the Eggs Benedict, Pancakes, and an egg dish. All worth having again. The patio was hopping and there are tables where folks had their dogs too. We'll be back!

cdqJA70JRdfVdX0gh2OzPA.text: Inspired food. Insipid service. Should our first clue have been the waitress' vapid gaze or the mindless dribble of incoherent gastronomic buzzwords which burst forth like a teenager's acne? Perhaps the disengaged and mechanical affirmations to our queries and comments should have fostered more concern? Alas, I spend such little time in the presence of tweakers, I missed the early warning signs of atrocious service.  Thankfully this lackluster performance was repeated with such regularity at every interaction we came to quickly relish, in the way of a beaten animal, the trials and tribulations our brunch entailed. Our waitress' feat was only topped by the complete disinterest of her supervisor in resolving a minor billing concern. The supervisor did a brilliant job of failing to resolve our concern in any way and avoiding providing clear information to understand the concern. Such rousing leadership at Snooze's head affords the clear inspiration behind our waitress' sterling work ethic.  Our atrocious service was unfortunate for Snooze offers some truly impeccable dishes from unassuming well-seasoned hash-browns to the dare I say foodgasmic OMG French toast. Nevertheless, until such time our robot overlords automate away the humble waitress profession I must recommend forgoing Snooze's culinary delights in favor of any other establishment which values event a modicum of customer service.

-EvRg8l3c9SlN4xnf31j5g.text: I HATE to give poor reviews, but I must warn others that if you have a group of people, you'd better call ahead!  We decided to have a family brunch here and were really looking forward to trying it.  We expected it to be busy and had a great time with the kids playing ping pong and enjoying free coffee, but waiting more than an HOUR?    The staff did not come to us with the delay, so we had to go check on the hold-up and make sure we hadn't been dropped off the list.  Everyone around us was seated and eating by the time we were seated.  It then took another 20 minutes for the server to take our order.    Hubby and I realized that food wasn't likely to arrive any time soon, and decided we had to leave and grab McDonald's (yuk) in order to make our tee time!  We had a great time hanging with the family, but were so hungry by the time we arrived at the golf course that I almost lost a finger as I wolfed down a quick sandwich from the clubhouse!  We figured 2.5 hours is plenty of time to have brunch with the family before golf.  We sure got it wrong that day!    As we were walking out, I snagged the person who had brought our menus and gave her a heads-up that they may want to expedite the food order at our table as our nephew had to be at work by 2:00.  Checked with the family later to see how everything turned out and they got food quickly and everyone enjoyed it.   I would try Snooze again because the food looks delicious, but it won't be with more than one or two people next time!

OfHMMWNxlOdzpCk8QJWWEg.text: Came in around noon, and did not need to wait for a table. Hostess was extremely pleasant as well as my server. We ordered the mmm mimosa, a recommendation by the server. And it was absolutely amazing. I myself got the Benedict (chiliquean??) and a half order of the French toast. Food was amazing. I love the French toast

0ImXJpit1aPMsVzTPSCbyg.text: I've actually been to the original in Denver and it was one of the highlights of my trip so I was excited as hell to hear they had opened one near me in Tempe. Came on a Friday morning around 7am. Pretty empty since everyone around here is off to class or work. Sat at the bar. Service was excellent. Meagan was friendly and on top of her game. The rest of the staff was also very cheerful. Now onto the food, the orange juice is fresh squeezed and the coffee brewed to order which is not something to see a lot so that was a nice touch. I got my personal favorite, the OMG French Toast which was, you guessed it, OMFG GTFOH GOOD! Couldn't recommend it more. The sausage patty was a good taste, little bite to it that I liked. One day I'll try something else but it's gonna be hard venturing away from this French toast.

nvKr-c-kRK1SyRtKi66UbQ.text: First time to Snooze. It was Sunday morning and busy quoted 15-20 minute wait and met that. Very innovative menu with lots of choices outside the norm. Gabby was our very friendly and attentive server. Not too friendly or spookily attentive, excellent blend! There were 4 of us and had a hard time choosing so we ordered one extra entree. The OMG french toast was just that. I highly recommend that entree! We also had caramel apple pancakes, huevos rancheros, corned beef hash and the soft pretzel breakfast sandwich. Everything was excellent. Retro 70's decor and free fresh hot coffee while you wait give seated. Going back tomorrow for seconds!!

2SpZlzpoFjR4rkxZtCuQYw.text: Super friendly service and delicious food! A breakfast MUST if you are in the Tempe area. Such a nice patio area for open air dining! I recommend the MMM MMM Mimosa and any of the eggs Benedict dishes.

1pr7RSVz8bSiZ9BU8c3E0A.text: The food has been consistently good all the times I've visited. It's the service that's an issue. We got a table after a 15 min wait. We were seated in a table right next to the bathrooms. I usually don't have an issue with this but each time the doors swung open we caught a strong whiff of whatever was going on in there. I requested the server, very politely, for another table. She said the only options were 3 chairs at one of the communal tables or be put back on the wait list for a 20 min wait. There were tables clearing out all around us. There was no reason they couldn't have switched us to one of the other tables and given someone else our table. Very disappointed. I will explore other locations of snooze in the valley and give the Tempe location a wide berth.

x81lWkufmA1n2bgrsEb4xg.text: So disappointed in our experience at Snooze today! About halfway through eating my Bella Bella Benny, I found a hair. I alerted the server and she took it away immediately and said they would make me a new one. This was the chance for Snooze to shine, but nope. No manager ever came to our table to acknowledge the issue and guess what? They charged me for the dish!!   Sorry Snooze -- I was hoping for so much more from you!   Update: I heard from the business manager at Snooze right shortly after posting this. My faith in Snooze has been restored! I know mistakes happen but I am so pleased that this one has been handled as well as it has been. Thank you, Becky, for reaching out!  Snooze will have us as customers again soon.

N_OCt9hq7VXJAfsCePsehg.text: Snooze is a good place to go to, but I don't suggest going on the parent's weekend. Once our friends decided not to join, we were able to get in much quicker. My boyfriend enjoyed his pancakes, my smashed avocado benny was alright, I was hoping for something more..magical. I love eggs benedict, but their hollandaise sauce wasn't quite right, not much flavor in it. The bloody mary was just alright and nothing special. Oa8ZV4umYVqgfdzedkWrkA.text: first time at snooze.  This location is near downtown Tempe/mill. If you come here on the weekend, apparently the Parking Garage next door is free. Good thing to know if you're looking for a parking spot.  Pretty nice area and location. We had a group of 10, divide the group into 5 and 5 for seating, as It was a faster waiting time. It did take at least 50 minutes to an hour of waiting, and this was around 12pm.   Luckily we were seated into booth next to each other, even though it was back-to-back. Server and waitress were all friendly and pretty attentive.  For food, I had the snooze breakfast burrito. The burrito had hash brown, beans, eggs, and I decided to add in the chicken meat, which cost additional $1 or something I believe. Everything was topped off with tomatoes and their green chili sauce. What I didn't like about the burrito, was there was way too much hash brown in the burrito, which does fill you up, but I wish there was something else inside the burrito. Definitely wanted more chicken in the burrito, but maybe a few bites had a little bit more chicken.  Burrito overall was just okay, nothing special. Also the burrito was a little dry. I had to use their table green chili sauce for additional sauciness. And ketchup for the hash brown, wish I dissected it out.   But if you're hungry, the burrito will feel you up for sure. I only finished just a little over half of the burrito.  Pricing was around $13.   They do have inside and outside restroom.  Also when you are waiting, there is a person on the patio making mimosa and drinks for you while you wait. which is a nice touch. There is also a ping pong table outside.  --- I was able to try one of their pancakes as well. Not sure what type of pancake it was. But the pancake had a cinnamon / some caramel / mostly butterscotch syrup on the pancake. With a brown sugar butter cream on top. The pancake was actually pretty delicious. Would probably recommend having their sweet or pancakes, as opposed to the burrito for sure.   Also it is ridiculous that a single pancake cost $4.75.   Would I come back to snooze? If there wasn't a wait, maybe. But I will probably check out other breakfast/brunch places first before coming back to snooze. Their pancake was good though.

uHWSgRYtLOmJrlAy7lxGWA.text: This is a great brunch spot. They have a great menu and I couldn't decide if I wanted the pancake flight or the eggs Benedict. I had both! I shared the pancakes of course. We had cinnamon roll, pineapple upside down, and lemon poppyseed. They were all rich and great definitely good thing we got them for the table to share. NldL1ksFlctmf17oIVHYeQ.text: I love this place. It has a great vibe and refreshing atmosphere. I always order their egg benny, but honestly, all of their food looks really good. I would give them a five star if the waiting line is shorter.

G7jjI-uyqjmh1UJE8qTC_w.text: I just moved here from Ohio and I've been looking for good places to brunch. I found this place and the service was amazing. The waitress made me feel like we had been friends forever. The food is quality and the prices are reasonable. This is definitely my new favorite spot. I tried the Lox and Latka Benny and the pineapple upside down pancake. It was so good, I wanted to try everything on the menu, so I guess I'll have to come back often in order to knock it all out.

VSCrKL4VJ2U15TV3-qnyYw.text: Omg. Was visiting Tempe from DC and this was the best decision I could have made for breakfast. I got the coco banana pancake with the everything "bagel" (it's more like a roll) with bacon, egg, dressed arugula, and an incredible green cream sauce. Go here! idJrPaC5X91Y0O6kaL1zUA.text: Absolutely love this place! This is our first stop anytime we are in Arizona or San Diego. The breakfast sandwich on a pretzel bun is amazing! And you cant go wrong with the pancakes here, all of them have been delicious so far highly recommended

HbRPpuUDOhniuaaH3XVb-w.text: I've been to a couple of the Snooze locations in CA and I'm very glad that their AZ location is just as good!! Consistency is key when it comes to having multiple locations.   Came on a Sunday morning for brunch which happened to be on Father's day Weekend. It was SUPER packed, but we were able to get seats at their bar/communal first come first serve seating area within 15 minutes. I highly recommend doing that if you don't want to wait long. They have outdoor seating and a pingpong table with a mist sprayer which was nice for the AZ heat. Also, there's free parking in the ASU parking structure behind the restaurant.  I got my usual 3 egg white scramble with spinach, red bell pepper, and ham. I was also able to substitute the toast for a sweet potato pancake! Our server was on top of things and food came out pretty quick. Everything was cooked perfectly and they weren't skimpy with any of the toppings. The sweet potato pancake was SOOO good!! Not overly sweet, but enough to hit your sweet tooth. Pancake was nice and fluffy and big enough for the 2 of us to share.

V1eY02wi3J-u8rlY5KcrcA.text: I was excited to try this place as seen with good reviews. I was very disappointed. Our waitress took 10 minutes to get water. And then our food was just okay. The pancakes were hard. Very over cooked. Never got refills on coffee had to ask twice and still nothing. I would say there are better breakfast places and more affordable prices

qhD9r7qbr-uwaj8ZTmvj7g.text: The reviews are right!  While on vacation, I wanted to try out a good breakfast spot. Snooze had amazing reviews and a hefty amount of them. My boyfriend and I came early one morning and were impressed by the number of people already waiting outside in a line. We stood and waited to put our name in and were told it would be 25-30 minutes. We decided to wait because we wanted to try out the place.  Once seated, we went over the menu and had a hard time choosing! I started off with a cold brew, which was very cold and tasty. I then decided on getting the eggs benedict with hashbrowns.  The food came out very quickly and the waitress was always quick to fill up my drink. The presentation of the food looked really good. You could tell they cared about what people were seeing. I loved the fact that the hash browns were circular and looked like they used a mold to put it down on the plate. The hashbrowns were seasoned very well and the eggs benedict tasted delicious.   I would recommend everyone go, also because I'm sad I couldn't try the fun pancakes!

qXwmz1VjFO386aGm5wsb_Q.text: Love the creativeness and the deliciousness!! My boyfriend had the breakfast pot pie and I went with the chili verde benedict with barbacoa beef. So freaking good!! There was a party in my mouth with every single bite. Do not pass this place up!!

3cJx_1SircuEjVdPqxx1Mg.text: Park in the parking structure right before you get here. $3 for an hour.  Adorable little restaurant with patio seating. Servers and host are super friendly.   Apparently known for their pancakes and they have pancakes of the day. We came in on a Monday around 11 am and we're seated instantly. Server was honest about her favorites. We had the mmm mmm mimosa and a spicy bloody mary.  I ordered some healthier eggs Benedict with broccolini and pesto Rice and the hollandaise sauce is some kind of cream cheese yummy heavy sauce.  They have funny names for the dishes but I can't remember them all. My friend had a lighter breakfast and both were great. Server brought out hot sauce for me and the food came out quick.  Very trendy and fun place close to the university.  Definitely see why they are popular. Great breakfast or brunch spot.

Tyj4LGycIrnCYVpqgJznFA.text: After a quick AM flight from ONT into PHX, on a rainy Saturday morning, we decided to partake in the most important meal of the week - Brunch.  A quick look on Yelp for some good eats and SnoozeAM had all the stars and solid reviews to coerce us into taking the drive into Tempe.  The line was long, wait time longer but low and behold two seats were available at the bar. We giggled with glee as we swooped in on the coveted bar stools. Immediately we were greeted and given menus, and we already knew that we were ready for our Mary's. I had a spicy Bloody Mary and my Love had the Beet Juice Mary. Different but good. More on the refreshing side. Very nice!  I ordered the egg white frittata Florentine and hubby had the "pick two" eggs Benedict ... chilaquiles and pulled pork. He wasn't a fan of the chilaquiles but loved the pork one.  Earlier we debated on whether or not we should split a pancake. Our server must have overheard this small debate because she came out with this amazing complimentary pecan caramel pancake for us to share!  Fifth star earned!  Menu is full of goodness and we would for sure go back!  Five stars " brunch and beyond!" Review for SnoozeAM!

O0Z1IGk4DRIZkcr9Vzoc8w.text: Do not let the name fool you.  I am not a morning person and this place made me a happy woman from the time we sat down and throughout my day.  SEASONAL!! if they have the shrimp and grits, you MUST try it.  We're here on a mini vacation from northern California.  We've been here since Friday and have eaten out just about every meal.  We've had some great food.  But this place was the best all around we've had and we're hoping our plans can include a last breakfast before our flight in the morning.  I like to try new things but breakfast is always the classic potatoes eggs and whatever breakfast meat I'm in the mood for.  We were seated promptly (coming in after work and schools begin, my have helped with this) the decor takes you back back in time a bit but the casual and freedom dress of the staff keeps you in modern time.  Lyle (the most charming waiter ever) smiled from the time he greeted us and never stopped. He was amazing and very knowledgeable with all ingredients in the dishes we asked about.  When we asked about suggestions he recommended the shrimp and grits and the steak Benedict. They are seasonal and may not be available on our next visit down here.  Then he mentioned the pancake of the day.  Bourbon infused with  white chocolate chips pecans and.... Hmmmm he'd captured my taste buds at "bourbon" with maple syrup... My husband was torn on which Benedict he wanted and was thrilled about the option to choose 2 (TWO) different ones to make his meal.  I was torn between the bourbon pancake and the shrimp and grits.  I really didn't think I'd like this... (who eats shrimp for breakfast? And I never cared much for grits)... But Lyle described it so deliciously I opted for the shrimp and grits.  The  Coffee was good and HOT.  All of a sudden this golden disc of dreaminess was delivered to our table (compliments of our delightful server) THANK YOU LYLE!  You'd think this would be so rich you couldn't possibly eat more than a couple bites.  You'd guess wrong.  It was just the right amount of sweetness. Served on top of the drizzle of bourbon syrup, this treat kept its form, never got mushy and was just perfect.  Before we (yeah I shared it) were finished our food came out.  I'll let my husband rave about his Benedicts. My shrimp and grits was beautiful.  Now let's see how this tastes.  I don't get too emotional over food but this dish was Devine. The spice was perfect.  I could taste both the sweet peppers and the hot peppers.  I absolutely love that they dice all of it small.  The only big chunks was the very generous amount of shrimp that came with.  The grits ... Let's just say I will be adding them to my own breakfasts now.  The portion was just right for me as I'd even had some left over.  Oh I forgot to mention the eggs that topped it all.  It was delicious!  I'm glad I ordered out of my norm.  I wish it was morning already so I can go back and order something else.  I'm bummed Lyle won't be there but I have faith that we'll still be happy with our new favorite "breakfast nook"!

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Shrimp and grits (seasonal) very yummy.
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Bourbon infused with pecans and white chocolate chips served on bourbon maple syrup.... So good. Thank you Lyle.
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States

a4p3E0qiS0sj6kJjUSPsyA.text: Delicious food, great location. Be prepared to wait at least 30 minutes if not more. The breakfast tacos are so good - I would suggest adding some type of meat (unless you dont eat meat). The cinnamon roll pancake was also sooo delicious. Highly recommend this restaurant!

yJ_hIGcTOLqPAZOsUX97Aw.text: My favorite breakfast place! Great food, fun atmosphere, the only issue is the wait if it's a weekend and schools in, but that's expected most places. Well worth it.

c9JQWA4wpQyLfJQpQ5leYA.text: **Vegetarian Friendly**  Um, this place is AMAZING! It's my new favorite breakfast/brunch spot. Really cute indoor and outdoor area. I went on a weekday, and the service was extremely quick. I've heard this place is packed on the weekends so I would anticipate more time.   Entree: OMG French Toast It was such a great french toast. Four pieces, which is the perfect size to share, or eat all yourself. It comes with a salted caramel syrup that really pulls the entire dish together. I highly recommend it for anyone that loves french toast!   Side: Hashbrowns These are normally served in a cylinder shape, BUT I recommend ordering them "extra crispy" because they come flattened out, extra crunchy, and taste even better.   Can't wait to come back!

Ij-uIb0K4_jY9nbhDyZWeQ.text: Service was superb - and sitting on the patio in a warm spring morning was nothing short of inspiring.    I ordered the Snooze Spuds Deluxe with the green chili.  Everyone at the table ordered something different - i apologize profusely I don't remember their orders - but I do remember mine - very very very (did I say Very?!) good!  Wow - great combination of flavors, perfectly cooked, spiced just right, and the right amount to fill a big boy like me without overdoing it.  Server was there just enough to take care of us and ensure drinks were filled and any needs taken care of.    I'll be back.

hQ7k9AY94WLk6P7tJ6kI_A.text: The food here is always delicious!  We always order a few dishes so we can split our meals to try different things. The portions are big enough to do so as well. Great place.

xxZLOUaBSFpjwNv0h-wUNg.text: Delish shrimp and grits.  Sister LOVED her pancakes with strawberry and cream cheese frosting. Skip the lavender butter tho or try it on the side.  Coffee while waiting was much appreciated.  Reason for 4 stars was the wait--over an hour.

2MKHIzm0Ik6jvM5hpdOt8Q.text: So good, love this place. Great food, good drinks. Little pricey but worth it

B6glvMZeD5fUpiOBypaSRg.text: I am sort of torn between two or three stars. I have had really great service and meals here that I would rate as four or five stars, yet I have also had around the same number of experiences that were pretty awful.  If you come here on one of the good days, you can expect great breakfast food for a somewhat higher than average cost. Although, when they are on point the prices are completely worth it for the meal.   Be warned though, when they fall short of loose dining standards, your experience can be very negative. I'm not sure if they have off days or times or what, but if you are unfortunate enough to come on one of those days here is what you can expect (and what has happened to me several times now): a server whom is either incompetent or rude (they read the same sometimes), wrong or missing items when you receive your meal, undercooked or overcooked food (ex. Bacon can be slimy and transparent or burnt black and hard), an empty water and coffee cup the entire time you are there, and an overwhelming sense of dissatisfaction when you just spent $30 on a breakfast that Denny's could've put to shame for $5.   All in all, try this place out. When they do things right this place is awesome. Just be weary of those "off" times.

pwOjgSGhK-dSBlZPYa0gWg.text: My wife and I were in town on business and arrived on an early AM flight. Needless to say, we were starving and needed breakfast STAT!! We looked up some places on Yelp and found Snooze. When we arrived, we were seated right away, despite the amount of guests already waiting for a table. Our server, Lolita, was pleasant, welcoming, and made some recommendations for us. We ordered Eggs Benedict done two ways - you get to choose 2 different Egg Benedict off their menu. I got the Ham Benedict and the Bella Bella Benny and my wife got the Bella Bella Benny and Chile Verde Benny. Let me say, we were blown away!!! The Bella Bella Benny had the right balance of acidic and savory favors. And yes, the hollandaise was very creamy and light. Poached eggs done to perfection. We also had the coffee and doughnuts pancake and man, that expresso syrup with the cinnamon on the doughnut shaped pancake was the bomb.com. You love coffee and doughnuts? You will want to have this. For real. So the big surprise, was when another server came over to our table and dropped off an OMG French Toast, courtesy of our server, Lolita. She said we've been great and wanted to have us try it. My wife and I aren't big French Toast fans, but if there was a day to make us believers and French Toast fanatics, this was the day!! OMG??? Yes, it earned every bit of its name. It was fluffy and not overly sweet. The marscapone, slices of strawberries, and the vanilla cream and salted caramel topping all just came together so beautifully. We ate everything. Ev-ery last bit of it. Yum!! We left this place with our stomachs and taste buds satisfied!!! Great service (thank you Lolita!!!) and a nice atmosphere. Highly recommended!!!!!

gpjCrUupyNUjNBM_90GOOA.text: Lovely place with cool, retro decor, good size patio.  All staff we encountered were quite friendly, as was the GM who stopped by the table more than once.  Great menu options with a combo of traditional favorites with a twist for more modern options.  I had the OMG French toast which was amazing.  AM cocktails looked delicious, but I opted for an iced tea.   The only issue we had was navigating my friend's stroller...but it is a HUGE double stroller, so not really an issue.  Will definitely be back for more!

BJsQ8ZG6kKSVP0E9Q2Ex9w.text: Wow.  So my husband picked this place for the good-looking menu and because he and my son LOVE breakfast.  I'm more of a lunch person, but I'm a convert!  The service was EXCELLENT!  To start the culinary ecstasy we tried a cinnamon roll pancake with candied pecans and cinnamon butter...holy cow!  The pancake was the perfect texture, super hot and the whole combo was the best pancake I've ever had.  My husband doesn't care for pancakes and he was blown away.  My son had the pineapple upside-down pancake and it was insanely awesome!  I had the breakfast tacos with the most delicious green chili hollandaise sauce topped with fresh cilantro and bacon...made me a breakfast believer!  My husband had the Cuban breakfast sandwich that was everything he wanted and more!  We are driving, so couldn't experience the bar drinks, but definitely will next trip.  Great coffee drinks and the whole vibe of this place was friendly, customer-oriented and amazing!  Can't wait to come back!   Well worth a trip!

N4-3_b1aHC2z02wq7UIjeA.text: I can't stop thinking about my amazing breakfast!!  This was our second time at Snooze. Though I felt the service was just ok our first visit, it was incredible this time around. There seemed to be a super long wait (10:30am on a Sunday), but when I went to put my name on the list, I was given the option to sit immediately at the breakfast bar, the best of inside and outside; a seat in the restaurant,  fully open to the patio and street traffic. A nice spot for just the two of us, maybe not ideal for larger groups.   Our server, Kaitlyn, was awesome - super friendly and helpful. I had the spicy Bloody Mary to start. One of the best parts of the menu is the ample vegetarian offering. This time I had the Snooze Spuds Deluxe with Soyrizo and Poblano Peppers mixed in, scrambled egg added on top. Heaven! Between this and the bloody, my hangover was cured. Unfortunately, I'm plagued with an obsession over this food and can't wait to go back!!

R5s7KzlgrN0Si3PivOiiIA.text: This place is the best! It's perfect in every way. Their food is delicious, unique, and fresh every time I have gone. Their staff is super friendly and inviting and prompt. The vibes of this place are great for any occasion, it's really open and has a great atmosphere, they offer beer too which is a plus! The only even remotely bad thing I could say is they are really slow about bringing you iced coffee haha. And you have to park in a parking garage but it is well worth the stop in. It's just as affordable as places like IHOP or Denny's too so why wouldn't you skip them and come here instead? They never mess up a meal either.

e7BAWvtkcnokLqHWtl2PEw.text: 30+ of us met here for Breakfast during ASU Family weekend 7AM on a Saturday and despite them forgetting my meal it was phenomenal! _IFbjTCDy5zzdwcTFniEoA.text: Recently checked this little place out and I am so glad I did! It's a bit hard to get to, since it is practically on ASU campus. My advice is if you see a parking space even vaguely nearby, take it.The meters take card and are cheap, but the garage next door has always been somewhere in the range of $10 cash. Blah. Onto the food! Amazing! I ordered the Snooze Continental that consists of a grapefruit brulee (a half grapefruit with caramelized sugar over the top), 2 pieces of toast and greek yogurt with house granola/drizzled honey on top! Delicious and pretty healthy too.Seriously some of THE BEST breakfast food I have had. The latte was good and the environment was nice and for being on campus, it isn't deafeningly loud like a lot of college places are. Service was great and friendly! Will return, and if I can get over the parking situation, I can see it becoming a favorite! A plus too when they didn't talk smack over my U of A card ;)

UcaxF06fYokjGFV8XoH5AA.text: Snooze absolutely blew my mind:  It was a regular day that my friend and I were going to yoga.. There happened to be an ASU football game going on making it difficult to find parking. So we did what anyone would do and decided to have breakfast instead of exercise. Snooze was just starting out at that point and we didn't know what to expect. We were seated at the breakfast bar and chatting about nothing in particular when we noticed two displaced (homeless) looking people with Starbucks cups walk by outside. We really did not think anything of it until one of them seated himself next to us. We kept talking about nothing in particular when this man interrupted us and commented on my friend's sparky shirt. He asked many questions, proceeded to become accusatory and generalizing college students, making us seem brainwashed or unaware of the world, and began on an endless tirade of conspiracy-like theories. At first I was intrigued and then realized that this person would not hear logic and did not want to discuss, more of lecture. It began to get uncomfortable. He would not leave us alone. In my mind, this man could have been a paying customer so I did not expect Snooze employees to get involved, but they did. They went out of their way to ensure that our experience in the restaurant was nothing but positive, even in situations seemingly out of their control, like this.  At first a server made eye contact with my friend, my friend made the "save me" eyes at the server. Then, a manager approached us from one side and asked us about our day, what we knew about the restaurant, and basically distracted us pleasantly while another server approached the gentleman to our left. This server asked the gentleman to wait at the front to be seated like everyone else. The gentleman did not want to leave and insisted that we also wanted to be engaged in conversation with him. At this point we were talking to the manager about all the restaurant locations, restaurant history, etc. My friend and I addressed the gentleman and told him we would like to eat in peace and thus the confrontation was over, thanks to the manager and server.  I was so pleasantly surprised that they would take the situation in their own hands, I assumed that it was our responsibility to stand up for ourselves and tell the gentleman we were done with the conversation, after all, we are adults. I was incredibly impressed by Snooze already and would not stop raving to my friend about what great customer service that was. Then, a completely new server came by and apologized for the situation, and offered us a sweet potato pancake (it was amazing). Later, another server came by and asked us what happened and apologized and we laughed about it. Then the manager asked us if they could get us anything off of the menu and we politely declined, they've done so much for us already! Finally, we asked for the check and were ready to pay when our original server apologized for the situation and told us they covered our bill!! Like, what??!! We were so shocked and impressed and thankful that we tipped (more than we would have paid for the meal) because that's what great customer service does to you, it makes you feel things! And write novels on Yelp! And endlessly talk about a restaurant and refer all of your friends there! This entire situation was out of Snooze's control, but they made the decision to control the situation. They didn't aim for us to have a satisfactory experience, but an unforgettable one.   And to think, it all started with us not finding parking for yoga.

eOxF5CEhJRThV0Md2rWB2g.text: Great mid morning get away- tell them it's your first time and get free pancakes of your choice

tTE050JPtYMJjYkJRMHfng.text: Good food, service is a little slow.  Somewhat pricey.  The variety of pancakes is awesome!

Xl55xnoy9a_B6PeXfJIaiw.text: I'll start by saying this would have been a five star review but unfortunately we found a hair in our pancake so I had to take it down because of that.  The manager came over and apologized they of course took it off the bill. But even with a hair I will be back. The atmosphere is very welcoming the food is delicious and service was great. We tried a few different things on the menu. I had the snooze spuds deluxe which is literally a mountain of hash browns topped with cheese and your choice of meats. As simple as it was it was delicious. My husband had chilaquiles Benedict all I can say is AMAZING!! This is not your traditional Benedict but they nailed the flavor it's almost as good as the ones we make at home. He also had the chile verde Benny which was also delicious! Since this was a new restaurant for us we decided to go big or go home and decided to share a blueberry Danish pancake and OMG it was heavenly....had there not been a hair cooked in the middle I would have eaten it all and licked the plate clean. This place also serves alcohol and that made our brunch even better :)

fISlSb_yOQFIkglWTG9_Iw.text: Stopped for breakfast this morning. Very efficient waiting process and notification when table was available. Breakfast, however was less than expected. Given the strong bitter flavor, could be the St. Germain didn't make it into the drink. My daughter was served the wrong omelet, my fried eggs were to be over easy, but were hard rocks. hbvR1cGNWZ_I02DWbQcuzQ.text: on the real, this place is tits. the chocolate chip pancakes will put you in a food coma that will render you completely useless for the remainder of your sunday afternoon. the wait time is pretty jewish, but the delicious grub and abundance of trim is well worth it.

uf1A6a4wtB_I-tu0yvKUrQ.text: Every time I go, I am always pleased. Delicious food, great service.

44X0NIFv-07yGRE05nvN5g.text: I never post, but I have to this time. First time at snooze for me and my wife. We set down and order a coffee & a drink. Then we order our.  The table to the left orders a few minutes after us. The table to the right orders a few minutes after them. We are excited because we have heard that they have some great food. 15 minutes goes by and the table to the left gets there food. About another 5 minutes goes by and the table to the right gets there food. Each table one person order the exact same thing we did ( Duel Benne). No food waiter not in sight. I finally see him and asked him about our food. He then said he will go check. He goes back into the kitchen, he comes out with some food in his hand and goes the opposite way. Then walks back to the kitchen. He walks by our table and does not say anything. After serving some drinks he walks up to us and said our food is next to be cook. At this point it has been 40 minutes. My wife said politely can we just have the check. She gets the check and he said I am sorry. My wife is generous and tips him $3.00 for nothing. The sad think is the waiter did not even try not to make a excuse for the situation. We walk out and will never go back. We then stop at the Waffle House order and got our food in 5 minutes. Now that is service.

nQkC_V1Kd7LJ2PVLi2UDLQ.text: incredibly long wait, but would possibly return for another bloody mary.

The hashed browns were so dry and didn't have much flavor in them. The price was expensive but the restaurant was adorable and a fun place to be. The drinks were great! Maybe next time I'll have to get something else from the menu.

rblUZAboUlhNoGH586rsXA.text: To whomever made my pineapple-upside-down pancakes the other day:  marry me.  Marry me now.  They were delicious ... and I loathe pancakes.  I do.  I ordered them because of a few recommendations from locals about their pancakes.  What is all the fuss about?!  Now I know.  Well done, Snooze; well done.

Ddfp-71GmKF9pz0TIURDjA.text: I can't believe this place is rated so high?!?! I was there for Easter, we showed up about 7:45 am. The restaurant was only about 1/3 full when we arrived, so we were excited that there was no wait. We were seated at a table very quickly when we walked in. Soon after the whole experience went in the toilet! We were seated at the very end of the restaurant furthest from the front door. This was not an issue, there were several tables that had patrons as well as the tables on both side had families. We looked over the menu and waited patiently for the server. We sat for 15 minutes before I got up to find the manager. It would have not been so bad if the servers taking care of the tables around us had at least acknowledged us. When I did get to talk to the manager I completely unloaded, I ! I went back to the table, just as a server showed up. He took our order and was trying to make things better. After a little while he showed up with a special treat to make things better, it would have been great if our food had not showed up at almost the same time. Oh wait, they took our food to the table next to us and started setting it down, as the people told them they had already eaten. To finish this long post up the food was ok but it was probably made worse because of the beginning experience. I won't be recommending the place to anyone I know, especially since we never spoke to the manager after I let him have it. He never came back over to check on us.

eduu-xSS2DNnZqCa-FS0Mw.text: OH yum!!  Breakfast was never better! The variety was amazing! The hollandaise sauce was superb!  The server, I am sorry I did not get her name (lots of cute tattoos!) was on top of us filling drinks and asking if there was any more she could do. Will go back soon!

46SPt2TKlho45oQkMEP3SA.text: This place is very good for breakfast but the wait time is almost unbearable. The food is good and the atmosphere is awesome just know you will probably wait a good 30-45 minutes for a table.

ROcI9kK-qB0pLu_FonKzNQ.text: Other than the hip decor, Snooze's service and food left TONS to be desired. I get the feeling that Snooze coasts on its great location and outdoor seating, thinking it can just mail in the rest. One of my biggest pet peeves about any restaurant...but especially one of this caliber and price point as opposed to a Waffle House or Denny's...is when an otherwise great server takes your order then hands you off to food runners who make no attempt to confirm the accuracy of orders when they're brought out, which is exactly what happened. The customer is put in the uncomfortable position of having to re-explain the order to a completely new employee oblivious to the original order, wait to eat the corrected order while everyone else digs in, and in my case eat the very dull and lack-luster final product that wasn't anywhere near worth the wait. In my case, I had breakfast tacos, featuring bland corn tortillas, barely heated and snow-white colored hash browns, and a scramble with little seasoning. It's just not what one expects of a place like this which I hold to a higher standard than Denny's or Waffle House, both of which I've eaten better (and cheaper) breakfasts at.

aFLMK4zcKooo7yli8SL1fQ.text: Great food, cool place, the benedict choices were great.  Would recommend to anyone who is a breakfast lover.

yuYLODs4rymIF2ButWcVjA.text: My wife and I ate at Snooze in Tempe this was our 3rd experience at Snooze (each in a different location including the original in Denver).  As usual the food was great it's nice to get a breakfast that is high quality, something different and a good value.  the staff was great assuming it was a manager whom greater me but based on his pride and smile you would of thought he was an owner (in a good way) as for our server, Parker, she was friendly and very helpful.  All in all as a restaurant owner myself I'd say this location hit it on the nail.  Will definitely go back (especially in the summer when we can walk right in!)

T9g9TKidKzbV8u8QB7__vA.text: HIGHLY RECOMMENDED!!!!! Food is amazing!!!! Friendliest wait staff ever!! I will def be back :)

69G8-j2BFTHR7xLdxUi0yw.text: Five stars for our server Kaitlyn, she was excellent. It was busy, as to be expected on a Saturday or Caturday as all the girls wear t-shirts with cats on them, but she was still super attentive. My husband and I shared Juan's Tacos and a flight of pancakes consisting of Pineapple Upside Down, Blueberry & Strawberry Shortcake.  The toppings on the pancakes were all amazing, Blueberry was my favorite. The pancakes themselves were ok, I would never order them plain, they are small and something you could make at home. The tacos came on corn tortillas, we added bacon (which was done to perfection), with eggs, pico and a tasty green chile hollandaise. We added sriracha to make them even better. My only complaint about the tacos were the giant chunks of onion in the pico, they were so large it was like I asked for extra onion.  The place is super loud as many other reviews have stated, so don't expect to have intimate conversation, and it's decor is cheesy ultra-hipster.

D5_QJ0a2cQcd69Bz4Gy0KQ.text: A friend told us about this place so we drove up.  Sunday brunch the place was packed but we were seated within 30 min which was good. Service was great. Food was fantastic. My husband had the potpie and I had chilli verde eggs Benedict.   There were no leftovers that's for sure.

8mtH7pwnH-q9hx-Z1wjr6w.text: The food is to die for . .between the unique pancakes and the incredible corned beef hash . .we will be eating there every time we are in Tempe!  Well Done!!

j4bRQmCf884HgjhkwXpZuA.text: I love snooze, especially the one on Camelback, but this place wasn't that good, at least this time.  The wife and I were returning books at the ASU Tempe campus and decided to try this place out to see which one is better.  Needless to say, it wasn't that good.  The server was nice, but it took forever to get our food.  The restaurant wasn't even that packed, so I could imagine if it was.  Now on to the food, which was really good and yummy, but not worth the price.  I had the OMG french toast, which costs almost 10$ by the way, and I was disappointed with the amount of food they gave me.  At the camelback snooze, I got nearly triple the food.  For 10$ I expect to not be hungry when I leave, but I guess that is the Texan in me.  Then to top it off, my wife found an eyelash on top of her pancake.  I know this kind of thing happens in the food business, but it surely made our visit less pleasant.  Overall, if you want snooze I would avoid this one and go to the one in Phoenix instead.

zf118AVnYvDwDGofowTRoA.text: Snooze easily tops my list of best breakfast spots in the area. The atmosphere, service, and food are all excellent. p6kDChqx-RQixl04OgXJEg.text: We went on a Sunday morning around 8:30am and waited an hour for a table outside for 5 plus a high chair. The wait wasn't that bad. There was enough space to sit out front and they sent you a text once your table is ready. We didn't get our food until 10am. I ordered the tacos. The menu said it came with a sauce, but there was no sauce on the plate. I didn't say anything. I just wanted to eat. It was really good food. We sat right next to the condiments, so we didn't have to ask for much help. We asked for a cup of ice and didn't get it until we got the check. The hashbrowns are really crispy and flavorful. Everyone's food looked really good. There was a lot of color on the plate. I ordered a side jalapeno and it was hot! Be careful! We all finished our meals and didn't offer to share! I would go back again, but on a weekday. Be careful with the cutlery. My knife had dried food on it. I didn't need it, so I didn't ask for another one.  Go early with people you can talk to for hours without eating much before hand. Invite me along! I need to find more people I can be around before I've had breakfast!

2d0tCUQ4xXcBAB6dTFl7nw.text: Wonderful breakfast experience. Great patio, heaters, dog friendly (outside) wonderful music selection and friendly staff. What a great compliment to all the eateries that have recently opened in Tempe! The food has been wonderful! The hash browns are delish!

3pEFawXZB-vH4RnDyL1W0w.text: Just in town one day and breakfast is a must in my world. I always try to find local joints in which to eat and the reviews on Snooze are outstanding. F-av39IyefpwcEREvfHwCg.text: I'm loving all the new restaurants that are opening in Tempe and Snooze is no exception!  My boyfriend and I visited for breakfast and it wasn't too busy so we were seated right away - it's a pretty big place. We opted for seats at the counter by the window so we could stare outside (and we had a good view of the ping pong table, which was entertaining.)  I ordered the late harvest benny which is sweet potato polenta topped with more sweet potatoes, eggs, fennel and kale and served with hashbrowns. My boyfriend ordered the breakfast pot pie. We both really enjoyed our choices. I love the combination of the sweet potato polenta with the eggs paired with the hashbrowns. Plus, the cream cheese hollandaise gave a nice sweet balance to this savory dish. All mixed together it made for a tasty breakfast hash. And it was very filling.  Overall I really liked the atmosphere, the service was good and the food was yummy. It will be great to go here when it's nice enough to open up the large windows.

JHUvR89wySAs7xXMID-d8g.text: There's a name they give their regulars and while I may not be one in Tempe I am at their location off Camelback. The service staff is the best especially when seated at the bar, you get casual and attentive service and the managers usually swing by to say hey and make sure life is good. _XlIQkxVjfU5bVLUGgqOkw.text: Very good breakfast. We didn't want to wait 20 minutes for a table so we grabbed a couple seats at the breakfast bar. The ham Benedict was delicious. The environment was fun, retro decor and lively colors.
