IUVdBRwGC0xL68AGgMFqgg.text: I have been wanting to try this place for a while now and still didn't really get to try it. I went there with my pooch and sat on the patio. Despite my flaky friend not showing up I decided to stay. It was a cloudy day and a little chilly so I ordered a hot almond milk latte. (I love places that offer more than the normal milk n soy options.) One of the staff members was very willing to turn on one of the outside heaters for me. Almost immediately after ordering my Latte it started raining. They rapidly put up the umbrellas in an attempt to keep my pooch and I dry. This is when i received several drama filled phone calls and stirred up emotion for me. I was crying, wet, and had a miserable dog. I got my latte to go.   I am writing this review Because of the great smiling service I received. I had multiple check ins by several different staff members. They truly did everything they could. Thanks guys- keep up the good work.   Can't wait to try your food.

Also the host working was very good about communicating and was very courteous.  Only complaint was that the music playing made me feel like I was shopping at Forever 21. I wish breakfast food could be as delicious when ordered to-go, because the ambiance there was just not for me.

wVVQaWSJDdCld0Du9ReM1A.text: Brand new and looks great! Great patio!  Start with the Pancake Flight and share with your table.  Try the pineapple upside down pancake for sure. The variety of eggs benedict are extensive and they are tasty, the best part is you can mix and match them so that makes decision making a bit easier.  Try the Chili Verde and the Late Harvest.  No bike racks yet but there are some down the street. If that is something you are interested in, tell the management, the more demand the better.

oyQIDfwUTJ_w881uv5XbpA.text: Came here for breakfast and after a short wait we were seated. I like that at the host stand there is free coffee for guests waiting to be seated!  Our server was friendly and efficient, and the food came out quickly. I tried the Bella Bella Benedict and the Benedict III (the half and half option where you can try 2 different Benedict styles). Both were fantastic but the Bella was more unique with the balsamic glaze drizzled on.   If I lived in Arizona I would eat here all the time! The menu had a ton of options.

Vypw_ud0VsEQ5ULCZXGwRg.text: Have been to this location several times and have felt differently each time. I've tried new things every time I go there, but this last time I was there I found my favorite menu item. To be honest I've never really understood the hype about the pancakes here. Don't get me wrong they are tasty, there just isn't really anything that excites me about them. What does get me excited though is the Breakfast Pot Pie. The rich gravy perfectly compliments the flaky puff pastry with your choice of eggs and a side of hash browns. If you're looking for something savory but still rich this is the option for you. Will definitely be getting this again when I go back.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Breakfast Pot Pie

IzWOF6DOuyg-AfG4unazOQ.text: My fella and I are bonafide breakfast lovers. If my husband could eat eggs at least 2x a day he totally would. Me? I take bacon super seriously, if it was acceptable to eat it every single day, I totally would.   My husband found Snooze through yelp and we gave it a go this past Friday. It's located right near ASU campus and a couple of blocks from our hotel, it was a good thing we walked considering the amount of dishes we put away. Lol  Upon arrival, there was about a 10 minute wait, the place was packed at noon. I'm pretty sure this particular location takes reservations but I'm not a 100% sure.   We were seated promptly after a tiny bit of wait and decided on the Pancake Flight ($10.25) and the Snooze Spuds Deluxe ($12). The Pancake Flight gives you a choice of any of the pancakes available- my fella chose the Pineapple Upside Down pancake, a traditional blueberry pancake and the Pancake of the Day- the Tropic Thunder (I think it was called) Holy crap were the pancakes delicious! The PUD pancake had chunks of pineapple in it and a small scoop of cinnamon butter, the Blueberry pancake was way better than standard with tons of fresh blueberries mixed into the batter, I can't remember what was in the Tropic Thunder pancake but I think there was coconut in it and topped with fresh blueberries and raspberries with an icing like topping- the Tropic Thunder was my least favorite but that's not saying much since it was just too tough to go up against the PUD pancake and the Blueberry.   Then there was the Snooze Spuds Deluxe. It's a dish of hash browns I ordered crispy with your 2 choices of protein- I chose the chorizo and bacon all topped with shredded cheese and 2 eggs over easy. This dish was by far the best breakfast plate I've had- I'm pretty sure ever, it was so damn good. The bacon was perfectly crisped and the chorizo was perfectly seasoned and added a nice savoriness to the dish. Get it, you will not be disappointed!  I think in the excitement of the first 2 dishes we placed in order to try the corned beef hash ($10.75) and eggs. This dish was good but really nothing about it stood out, so that was a bit of a bummer. There was a ton of onions in the hash and not enough hash and that was off.   We didn't try any of the cocktails this time around but I would love to someday. We loved this place so much that my fella almost ran out to grab breakfast again early Saturday morning before we were due at the airport. It's a good thing we didn't we might've missed our flight. Lol   My husband discovered there's a location in Tustin so we will happily be back next time we're in SoCal!

K4FTFJxfHfwiGtBy2X56Zw.text: Snooze delivers a superb breakfast experience. I went here originally in Boulder, and when I came to Phoenix I was really happy that they also had Snooze. It is a great place. The first time, I got a benny duo with the traditional (dat hollandaise was amazing) and the verde pulled pork (also gr8). The second time, I got the pancake flight. There was a sweet potato pancake which was not my thing but the blueberry danish pancake was amazing and delicious and next time, I am getting just that probably. The menu is diverse and great and expensive but I think brunch is worth spending big bucks on so I recommend it to all my fellow brunch lovers.

-0n0-6sD90dNBABy1uEXig.text: I'm a Denver-ite, so I'm of course a huge Snooze fan/regular. I'm easily won over with decadent pancakes and incredibly boozy iced coffee.  Visited the Tempe location with a friend and was not disappointed. We got chilaquiles benedict, salsa verde benedict, OMG french toast & a PB cup pancake. For starters - WAY too much food for two people but, we're gluttons for punishment and breakfast foods so we stuffed ourselves into oblivion. The sweet eats are always my favorite - but the benedicts were damn good too. The chilaquiles was my favorite of the two.  Only downside is the wait times are almost always SO. LONG. But, that's a sign of a good place, no? We put in for two and were told about a 30-45 min wait, which is pretty standard around late Sunday brunch time. They serve coffee in the standing area while you wait though, so that's a nice occupier. However, if bar top seating comes open it's first come first serve and we scooped up two spots about 15 minutes into the wait. Scoooooore! It's also located on campus, so take that for what it's worth - we figured it would be filled with boozing college kids (because you know, we're SO old & far removed from that lifestyle in our late 20's ha!), but it wasn't at all an issue.   Eat the pancake flight. Get the AM Manhattan. Then go home & take a nap.

NYQVzrH08mgRk4LZr1XHfQ.text: My first visit I ordered the breakfast tacos and they were delicious. My second trip I ordered the breakfast burrito and the green chili had a little spice. 8ZLEdNs5EdzFLYcM2QrZqw.text: Go Cubs Go!!!   First of all, a lot things went right with this place. For starters they have a really nice patio area overlooking part of ASU. In addition to that they have a nice ping pong table and bean bag game out there as well.   The joint is right on ASU campus in Tempe with some additional restaurants in the surrounding area. Came here on a nice warm sunny Wednesday morning in November with my cousin for breakfast. I ordered three eggs with chicken sausage and hash browns and substituted toast for an upside down pineapple pancake.I will have to say that the pancake was a good size for being a single and oh yeah it tasted awesome! The eggs and chicken sausage were nice and hot the way a great breakfast should be.  As I was enjoying my breakfast I realized how much this place reminded of a breakfast place that I frequent in the Chicago suburbs named Jam N' Jelly. Snooze AM had the same awesome feel to it with the exception of having much nicer November weather than Chicago...duh right?  In addition to all the greatness mentioned above I picked up really quick on how a few of the servers there were wearing Chicago Cubs shirts and that right there earned them an extra star!  If you happen to be in the ASU area and are looking for a great, friendly, tasty breakfast place that has outside dinning, a long side a cool ping pong table, and bean bag game. Then I highly recommend this place and definitely go for some of the specialty pancakes they have on their menu.

vPVj15KMsNUgrpRFwHluMw.text: We had the cutest server ever today named Madison!! Took my family here for breakfast and even though we were a party of 6, we got sat pretty quickly for how busy it was! 6bNcGU5qbp_YuuYdVxzZ0Q.text: If you take away one thing from this review let it be: PANCAKES.  Inside the restaurant the music is extremely loud plus the abundance of chatter makes it very difficult to hear your brunch mates. Perhaps that makes me sound old, but I don't get to see these guys all the time so when I do I'd like to be able to converse with them.   Sitting outside isn't really much of an option in the summer either. There didn't appear to be much shade or misters to try to beat the heat so unless you enjoy becoming a melted burnt mess inside you go.  The service was alright, but the servers definitely seem overwhelmed with the crowd of people. We barely saw the poor thing who was busy running around. Did I mention the place was slam packed? 'Cause it was. That being said the wait time to get in was only about 20 mins.   I wasn't overly impressed with the food I ordered. My potatoes were not crisp. (I like my hash browns to have a crispy seer.) Also, there were some gross soggy pieces of bacon fat in my dish. I took the most of it home and reheated it in a skillet with some butter and that did turn out delicious.   The pancakes are where it is at though! We split a pancake flight and I have to say all 3 different kinds were fantastic! They were light and fluffy and full of flavor. They each were so good individually I don't think I could even pick one favorite of the bunch. I highly recommend trying the ones we had: Strawberry Fields, Blueberry Danish and Peanut Butter Cup. I have a feeling the rest of the pancakes and the french toast are probably equally was tasty as well.   Oh yeah, did I mention the pancakes? Get the pancakes!!

dLf28WdTyJhrjmdjpj7Yyw.text: Lets me start with, Savannah is great.   My visit was spur of the moment, and selected based on best food photos lol. We ordered the pancake flight-- blueberry, french toast and pineapple upside down cake. Although we did ask for one plain pancake. So idk how that happened but score for us. We also ordered the breakfast pot pie w hash-browns. I was kind of sad that I saw the OJ coming from a container after I was already drinking mine.  I immediately dug into the pot pie, the gravy was more of a cool temperature. I had my friend try it too to make sure I wasn't being overly critical, or maybe gravy comes cool? Anyway Savannah came back a little later, I told her "I think this is supposed to be warmer than this?" She immediately said she would have them remake it. Round two came out and this time it was at least warm in some areas. My only suggestion is to make the gravy hotter or make it from scratch when its ordered. The pancakes and french toast were BOMB! I loved the blueberry the most.  Every employee said a parting greeting as well. I thought that was a really nice touch. Ill be back and this time I'm ordering the Chilaquiles.

S4LYFEvwEGHgk5-HY6JHaA.text: I was pretty excited when I heard that Snooze opened up in my area, and have to say it's a great addition to the ASU area as well. If you are worried about parking there is a public parking garage just right next to Snooze, however they do not validate parking, so you will have to pay, I didn't mind because it meant easy parking and no having dig for change for parking meter, or feeding the parking meter my credit card info.   It was a Wednesday morning and I was in the mood for breakfast so I grabbed my son and daughter, who happen to both be home, which is rare and told them lets head off to breakfast.   I went with the Chiaquiles Benedict, barbacoa beef over tortillas in ranchero sauce, melted cheese, poached eggs, roasted pobalno hollandaise sauce, Pico de Gallo & cotija cheese with a chocolate chip pancake.  I have to say these are some of the best tasting benedicts I have had in a while, I just loved all the flavors and textures, and the hollandaise sauce is what makes this dish blend perfectly.  The Chocolate chip pancake was great too, just what the little kid inside me was craving, fluffy, and chocolaty good!   My daughter and son loved there dishes as well, and my son was surprised that I knew about Snooze, sometimes I think he doesn't know me at all haha.   Another great breakfast at Snooze!

3ZQy0XqQD15mzrXIhD2UCg.text: Basis for my starred ratings (which skews heavily to the food or drink): 1 star:  Never again. 2 stars:  Poor food, poor experience, extraordinary measures in order for me to come back. 3 stars:  Average, nothing really special, nothing particularly bad. 4 stars:  Very good, would definitely return. 5 stars:  A favorite, one of the best.  Really surprised by the nearly 5-star review.  Ignoring the spotty service that we received, I give this place a 2.5-star rating, not needing extraordinary measures to come back but really, really hesitant to.  And that's just based on the food.  Ordered the Benny Duo with a ham and chile verde benedict.  Also ordered a side of bacon, chicken sausage, a side of eggs, and a chocolate chip pancake.  The Benny Duo comes with a side of hash browns.  They have apparently changed the way they serve has browns here.  They used to be scattered on the grill, now they come from a cylindrical mold.  Makes for more space on the flattop to cook other stuff, but also leads to no crispiness at all in the hash browns.  The top of my hash browns were just barely browned and what was in the middle was cooked through but on the mushy side.  The side of bacon was marginally saved by the fact that they use well-sourced, thick-cut bacon - but not crisped at all.  Limp and greasy all the way through except the last bite of the last piece.   The ham benedict was superior to the chile verde.  The chile verde comes with pulled pork on a tiny stack of green chile tortillas.  Very little green chile flavor coming through.  The pulled pork was moist but lacked flavor.  To their credit, both eggs were well poached.  The ham benedict would have been pretty perfect but for the hollandaise, which was way too thick and lacked tanginess/citrus.  I'm sure that sauce will never break but it's not a good hollandaise.  My wife was also disappointed with her chicken sausage (which is a patty, not in a casing) and her chocolate chip pancake, and I concur.  Pancake was not fluffy, lacked butter, with the chocolate chips being the only thing going for it.  And they would have been better off serving a pounded out piece of chicken breast instead of the chicken sausage patty that they served - which had marginally more flavor and was dry.  A paillard wouldn't have required them to grind down chicken meat in the first place and it would probably taste better.    The atmosphere is quite nice, it's trendy, and staff was friendly - but that didn't make up for the mediocre food that got.  Again, 2.5 stars, would have been showing 3 if service were more even.

k_wS2GPnYTGxs1rDrY17NQ.text: Got there on Thursday morning at 9:30 AM.  Place was packed.  Lots of University traffic.  Ended up sitting out side.  There was four of us for breakfast  - but was hard to talk because the music was too loud. I asked the server to turn it down, but I they just ignored my request (otherwise would have given the 5 stars).  All that said, the eggs benedict was fantastic.  Will go back.

S9ibfkynbKD2GbQq9KnZBQ.text: My wife found this place on our last day here Tempe. It was 6 minute drive from our  hotel. We went during brunch and had roughly a 35-45 min wait. They had complimentary coffee and allow you to go to the bar to get drinks while you wait but you cant sit at the bar as other patrons are eating there. The atmosphere is chill with a great outdoor patio with FUNCTIONAL MISTERS.   FOOD: We both ordered the same dish with only one difference. We had the Snooze Spud Deluxe with bacon and sausage. My wife has scrambled eggs and I had Poached Soft eggs (done well). Our server Nick was attentive and knowledgable about the menu. He asked us where we were from and we told him Texas. We told him that we were here for our 1 year anniversary. He allowed us to get the Sweet Potato Pancake on the house. OMG, that darn pancake was so Soft and buttery. IT LITERALLY MELTED IN OUR MOUTHS.   DRINKS: I had a Brewmosa which was delightful for an early morning kick off and my wife had a Mmm Mmm Mimosa which was a great classic one, kind of light on the champagne but still good none the less.  Next time we are in town we will be back

Tuo-sw5VBs1yF4I7dNVkeg.text: I find this restaurant overrated and overhyped. They have cute decor and a nice patio but I think the atmosphere is better than the actual food. The mimosas were good, hard to screw that up, but our server was pretty aloof and  my sister had to literally flag him down to let him know he forgot to order hers. My dish was good not great, and my sisters (marscapone?) pancakes were way too sweet and rich.  I think there are way better brunch places in Tempe and you won't have to deal with paying for parking (they don't validate) or long waits.

O8dk6xqV3WjBkHERnLUEqg.text: I've brunched at Snooze a handful of times, and ranked it 4 stars...up until my last visit. We had been waiting for almost an hour for a table (you can expect this if you come any time before 11:30 a.m. on a weekend), and when we were seated, the manager comped us a "pancake flight" with three full-size Snooze specialty pancakes - just as a thank you for waiting! My group inhaled them faster than I could snap a picture, but they were incredible. Service is always great here - you can tell that the servers and hosts really enjoy their jobs, and it's a fun and quirky place to be!

LwG687u0vgrEXFKAWcP3iA.text: If you love breakfast food, Snooze is the place for you. Familiar with their restaurants, I first visited one of the Snooze eateries in San Diego.  When I found out there was one in Tempe, I told my friends that we had to eat there while we were in town on a work trip.  Three of us showed up around 7:30am on a Sunday and there was no wait at all, but I didn't expect there to be that early which is why we showed up when we did.  From past experiences at the other Snooze I'd been to, I knew the place would be packed before too long, especially on a Sunday.  I knew I wanted a pancake flight for the variety. You can order any 3 flavors available for $9.75. I chose the Bourbon Street Pumpkin, Blueberry Danish, and Chocolate Chip. The guys both got the Breakfast Pot Pie with rosemary sausage gravy, puff pastry, egg, and hash browns.  After getting a taste of this, I wish I'd ordered it, too, because it was amazing!  Not that I was disappointed with my pancakes at all.  I especially liked the Blueberry Danish one. My tip for Snooze is get there early or expect a wait and share your meal with your loved ones so you can try more good eats.

778ieHwkPEjVmWvQY65grg.text: This is probably the worst breakfast joint I've been to. The service was way below par. The pancakes while high in calories were mostly covered in sugar. And the "Huevos Rancheros" were the worst thing I've ever consumed (they didn't even look good.) That salsa that comes with the Huevos Rancheros was god awful and wouldn't even qualify as salsa in the bottom most pits of hell. Lastly somehow this place manages to screw up ketchup, with some devil brand of ketchup I've never heard of before that is fantastically bad.  In conclusion, Avoid upon pain of death.

Z1Pzh9uUiB-C8YUx6OrNlg.text: Snooze is my favorite breakfast spot.  The food is not your traditional breakfast recipes.  Everything is made with a flare which is just delicious.   It's so hard to decide what to order each time because it is all so good.  I only wish they offered a sample plate so you can have a little of everything.  They actually offer the eggs Benedict that way singly can order two different types.  I recommend the Chile Verde Benedict and the Bella Bella but if your a potato lover the Snooze spuds are awesome either the pulled pork and jalapenos.  Never a bad meal here.

5ynMbSCYYRxCNE6YbT4Cpg.text: This place has everything you could possibly want in a brunch spot. The staff is really friendly -like not just-doing-my-job nice, but genuinely-glad-you're-here nice. GsyFFvUZP87HdOX8T-1iDg.text: Really love Snooze! This was my third time and each time has been a different location (Houston, Scottsdale and now here). I've loved them all!   I've tried the sweet potato and blueberry pancakes and both are outstanding.  Service is friendly and efficient although there can be a wait.    I love that they really let you be creative with the menu and make your breakfast your own.  Seems like they'll do just about any substitutions you want!    The kids menu is great- a decent size pancake, fruit cup, hash browns and juice or milk for $6. My daughter loves it.    Today I tried two different types of eggs Benedict- one was classic and one Italian although I forget the names.  Both were delicious.

zHKjGIhMSfHg6bIW_2XT1w.text: My son was in town visiting us with his girlfriend. They wanted to go somewhere for breakfast after I picked them up from the airport. VDSt54gYfKV0_hrJIgtlJA.text: I was looking for a good pancake spot so I invited some friends to join me at Snooze for early breakfast. As a newer location, the decor resembled their other restaurants. The signatory yellow light fixtures corresponded with a good number of round tables. The structure also facilitated a row of stools facing the large windows, and a full bar in the back. By extension, the sidewalk patio added character and spaciousness to the restaurant. Fortunately, we arrived early enough and did not have to wait for a table.  The Grilled Cheese and Tomato Soup ($7.50) came with a conventional bread and cheese sandwich, tomato soup, and hash brown. There was a light crunch on the bread, but not enough cheese to translate into that gooey experience I was looking for. For the price, I was expecting better value and taste on the sandwich. The tomato soup was rich, hearty, and had a slight kick in the end. The hash brown was soft and needed more crispy edges. It was not the best grilled cheese, but it did hit the spot.  The Pancake Flight ($9) came with our choice of blueberry pancake, sweet potato pancake, and the chocolate ganache pancake. All three of us agreed the sweet potato pancake was the most impressive, as the buttermilk and caramel flavors accompanied a touch of ginger butter and handfuls of pecans tossed on top. The server endorsed the blueberry pancake, but it tasted rather conventional. I wished there were wholesome blueberries embedded, and that these pancakes were easier to cut into. The dark chocolate ganache concoction was without depth and the least impressive.  Service was very sporadic and not warm or welcoming as I expected of breakfast places. Overall, the food were nowhere close to the experience I previously had at their sister restaurants. The food hit the spot but there was no wow factor whatsoever. Additionally, I thought the execution on the Grilled Cheese was very poor for the price and a restaurant of this caliber. The server also gave approval to a blueberry pancake that was rather sub par. Overhyped. I will not be coming back.

2svRhI0v86oJclfYP_NSng.text: I love Snooze and my brother and I had been planning to go here all week when I came to visit. The reason for 4 stars and not 5 is that they sent out an omelette when I'd ordered a scramble and had to wait about 10 min to get the correct order. Otherwise the food was delicious (albeit a cold pancake that sat while I waited for the rest of the food to come out).  I always get the pineapple upside down pancake (gluten-free). It's the best pancake they have IMO. Also (eventually) got the egg scramble with goat cheese, spinach and mushrooms. I could have done without the hashbrowns. I tried just get the pancake instead of the toast and hashbrowns which I think is a fair trade out, but apparently you have to pay an additional $4 for the pancake whether you want to trade out both or just one of them (which doesn't make sense to me, but oh well).  Their lattes are good. I asked for a latte with almond milk and a little honey and cinnamon. It was delicious.

ZNPE3wFc4vDcxdg-PLDWRw.text: Breakfast was awesome. Benadicts are unique and you can get 2 kinds if your unsure. Pancake flight is the way to go to experience 3 tastes at once. Service was good. They have an outside patio seating

DBIoOS3HXZlOa3P0ZjlOfw.text: Traveling for work (alone) so I avoided the long wait by sitting at the counter. Food was decent. Prices were reasonable. Service? Well, if two pretty girls hadn't sat next to me I might have gotten some attention. -5re1R8kzzqZVKMzHSY5YQ.text: Walk right in a grab a seat at the bar or high tops to save you a 30 minute wait.  Good food and the pancakes are bomb! Blueberry are hands down the best and grab a bloody buddy or mosa.

InUY8THZCuS0SE17er7h7A.text: Always a great breakfast.  Highly recommend giving it a try. You will leave fulfilled...and maybe ready for a nap.

lq1o-ABQNejD7yITMdOwPA.text: Amazing place for breakfast. My family and I can't get enough of it. The hashbrowns are amazing and my kids can't get enough of them. I can honestly say I haven't had anything bad here and I've had at least 4 or 5 different dishes.   If you're looking for a hipster, cool, delicious place for breakfast, this is it.

BwfGeh5me_z5X_bykh6DYw.text: So yummy!! 2nd time here and not disappointed! Lox Benedict and Bella Benedict did  not disappoint! Peanut butter pancake....worth the calories!!!

CCFuCsX4R9kWtqPbQboDOg.text: Best ham Benedict I've ever had.  I also like that they provide coffee for you when you're waiting for a table.  Get there early to avoid a long wait.

gqZAVEltgLFTh7GhDb0tRw.text: I had the Sandwich I Am and enjoyed every single bite. Good portion and flavorful.  Hubby has the Pineapple Upside Down Pancakes and said it was just ok. He prefers Butters breakfast (located in Scottsdale) over Snooze.  Our server did not come to table often enough. We had to waive to get her attention. At a place so busy I would assume they would want to turnover the tables quick so it would make sense to come to table often to check up on guests.   Additional information: We came around 1030AM on a Sunday and street parking was easy to find. The wait was about 45 minutes.

tpN-I-us0zqcFslqTXxBtQ.text: Delicious, fresh breakfast foods. Food came out just as ordered for our party of six, and quickly. The unique takes on breakfast aren't too "hipster-ish or granola" so I like it. They definitely boast a different menu of the classics without adding fresh mountain alpine arugula or southeastern Cuban coast seaweed to every dish. (Refreshing in a time where people are trying to hard sometimes.)   Atmosphere is very fun and friendly. We experienced a theme day the Sunday we went. It was beach day so the servers were wearing floaties and sunscreen noses. Very nice touch.   Service was phenomenal. Very good team effort/vibe, coupled with quick, attentive service and thorough but timely check backs from our server. It was a small 10 minute wait but this was the off college season. Throw in free weekend covered structure parking right next door and it's well worth it.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Party of six with great food!

K2W-yj2QuYsza-v_q39vJg.text: I've been wanting to go to Snooze for months, but they get so busy on weekends! I begged my husband to get up by 7am so we could head there early. We arrived with plenty of open tables. I had the pancake flight - pumpkin, sweet potato, chocolate peanut butter cup, and my husband had the corned beef hash. I also had a mimosa with orange juice and the dirty drunken chai. I was drunk before 8am. :D The food was fantastic, staff is super friendly, and I love the ambiance. I can't wait to go back!

lq838l0RED06upRxLETGDA.text: Awesome breakfast options, super healthy, and good coffee. Can't ask for anything else!

vHgXMMy-M4S-UOYPTl-7kw.text: Reasonable prices and best server, Tori, who is cute as a bunny.  We went for breakfast on a Friday around 8:30.  It wasn't busy then but it was  really starting to jump when we left.    I tried one of their 'known for' dishes, corned beef hash.  It was excellent, not dry, and had a beautiful crunch.  The eggs were cooked perfectly also.  I tried a bite of my boyfriend's caramel apple pancake and now I'm obsessed with trying to recreate this at home.  Back to Tori...very sweet and efficient and offered to get us to go cups of our coffee/tea.    I'm hoping work will bring me back soon so I can visit again!

jj9TH-y-3KYZ-Stc_-ZJ5g.text: so many options for eggs benedict! i checked the menu the night before and knew i had to try the elote version. we were told the wait was 45 - 60 minutes but ended up being seated much faster. the palomimosa (a mimosa paloma mash-up) was delicious - you can have tequila for brunch, right?? my order came out wrong but they fixed it quickly and were very apologetic. our server and the host were very friendly and the food was delicious. i LOVE this place! i'm a little sad that i found my favorite brunch spot while on vacation 12 hours from home!

VSDch8X33qEgEe2mBl6b2g.text: Always love coming here! I'm not a big sweets person (especially for breakfast) but OH MY their pineapple upside down pancake is ahhmazing. I definitely recommend checking this place out if you haven't yet. Just be cautious that there's usually a wait (and for good reason).

BTEES0jRXY1B4D7KRXyyPg.text: Came here while I was in Arizona for a work trip. I went on a Wednesday morning so there was no wait but the place was still full. Service was quick and friendly. The menu is quite extensive but I went with the classic breakfast plate. (Should've gone with my go to eggs benedict lol). Anyway, food was amazing...I especially loved the hasbrowns they have..seasoned very well! This is probably one of my favorite brunch places I have been to...now they just need to open in Northern California!!!

cQvPg7H1Aw671V4AFRTmkw.text: Best brunch I have ever had!! The French toast is amazing and the eggs benedict is delicious! Excellent bloody marys and complimentary coffee while you wait for a table! My go-to brunch place for sure!

iuJLfpXh43GZr8msqvM90Q.text: I went to Snooze a few weeks back for brunch with a friend. Of course, I made the mistake of going on a Saturday morning so it was incredibly busy, but that was my own fault. I was told it would be a 20 minute wait but was seated in 10 - hooray! However, I do not like their "text" feature for alerting you when your seat is ready. At all. I much prefer the traditional method of calling out your name... Anyway, was seated and greeted by my waitress promptly, but it became apparent over the course of my visit that she was very overwhelmed. There was not an empty table the entire time I was in the restaurant. If I were a waiter there, I'd be overwhelmed too. It took quite a long time for my friend and I to get our "specialty" order drinks - chai tea - and it was not very good. Extremely bland and at $4 a glass, I had hoped for more. The French toast was delicious but the serving size was small for the price. My water was only refilled once and I left the restaurant very thirsty. All in all, I'd go back. I really would. But not on a weekend morning when the wait staff is too busy to refill drinks.

54AW_rL5-gxDNnVTYiWueg.text: On reading my prior review, I was contacted by someone from Snooze and they offered to pay for me giving them another shot at their Benedict. They sent me a handwritten note, which impressed me- few people do that!  I returned and everything was perfect. The dish was seasoned very well and cooked to perfection; the atmosphere was buzzing and the servers very prompt and friendly. Such a cool location too.   I'm stoked I found another terrific brunch place in Tempe!

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Cool interior design

P660zqNXmhUbU5VANYWxLQ.text: Go here!! If you haven't been, you're missing out. I wanted to lick my plate. I had the three pancakes and let me tell you...compliments to whoever created the menu...whew...I want some right now just thinking about it. Ok so I had the pineapple upside down pancake, the sweet potato and the blueberry streusel...yall...so damn tasty. Mimosas and other cocktails, great service, outside seating. I have nothing bad to say. I think we'll go there for breakfast tomorrow.

Tstqq_fJXwWndjkQZ5OYrg.text: As an ASU student, I've gone to Snooze many times during my 4 years of college. I may even have skipped class once or twice to feast on Snooze...but that's our little secret.   This past weekend, I re-visited with some friends in a group of 7. We checked in around 9am on Saturday and were seated ~15-20 min later, which was surprising, as I've waited 30+ minutes for 2 people before! They have a main menu and then rotating pancake/holiday options which makes it fun to return again and again. The cost is average for brunch place in Tempe at $11-13 per plate, but you definitely fill up!  This time, I ordered the sweet potato hash from the "Like a feather" section. I had no idea what the Gochujang sauce was, and I was nervous that it would be a hot sauce when they brought it out, but it's actually pretty tasty! Not spicy at all. More sweet. I felt full and satisfied without being bloated after my meal. Sweet potatoes aren't technically Keto/low carb, but this was still a great, healthy alternative!  Parking: there is metered street parking spaces across the street, or there is the Fulton parking garage which is free on weekends!   Venue: Snooze is a trendy, retro themed restaurant. The workers wear casual clothes with different Snooze graphic tees. It's very casual! If you have to wait, which is very likely, there are only a couple seats inside by the hostess stand. Most people stand outside, but they text you when your table is ready either way. I personally like to sit at the tables across the street until I get my text!

_J4nsFaB9PGk51WabK6zgg.text: Met a friend in Tempe for bark park fun and came here after for food because of the dog friendly patio. Others had the same idea as we had a short wait.   The menu has a nice selection and some cocktails. I had a grapefruit mule that was fantastic. The waiter brought the puppies some bacon. So sweet.   My friend got the Benedict and it looked amazing and she loved it. I had the breakfast tacos. Wow very good!    I'd recommend it if you're in the area and the patio weather is good.

wsHT2KLzb8C_uXuoaaj7Mw.text: One of my favorite brunch spots. I tried the Havana Daydreaming yesterday and it was delicious. I loved the pork with the hollandaise sauce combination. The hash browns are to die for. Very flavorful, not too crunchy, not too soft, perfect! I have also tried their Ham Benedict before. I LOVED it. I've tried eggs Benedict at other brunch restaurants to compare, and honestly nothing compares to the Benedict's at Snooze. I highly recommended coming here. There is always a wait, but it is worth it every time!

KGRpuQfQPGNbA9pSJCBPlQ.text: Had the worst experience here. I have a dairy allergy, so I ordered my Chili Verde Benedict without cheese. When they brought out our food, there was cheese melted in between the tortillas, but I didn't know until after I took a bite. I could taste it, so I lifted up the tortilla and there was very obviously cheese underneath. Called the waitress over and she began to argue that there was no cheese on it. I was shocked and just decided not to eat the tortillas. I was hungry because the place was busy and service was slow, so I just decided not to fight it and just eat everything but the tortillas.   Somehow the manager found out and came over and talked to us. He offered to remake it and comp my meal. I was so pleased with how it was handled until the food came out. They literally just took the food I had already started to eat and put it on top of two soggy, cold English muffins. It was so awful that I didn't even eat them and they basically just wasted time that I could have been eating.   At this point, I was just done. I felt like I couldn't complain now because I was getting the meal for free. I discourage everyone from going here.

hWZVa0xqrzXAefrYDO9kqQ.text: This is a great spot for breakfast. Indoor and outdoor shaded seating. The pancake flight was super good and the service was good as well!

JjlSYSdz86qQPGXuS-Qzsg.text: My god, take all my money. This place is an utter gem and everyone should visit.   Yup, there's always a wait on weekends. It's so good, people want in.  Mimosas: excellent variety. Something for everybody.   Breakfast: SWEET. POTATO. PANCAKES. Get them. You will never be disappointed.   I also did the pick two Benedict's. Delicious!   Service: attentive but not overbearing. Just the way it should be.

hcPk0QSFqw8hC0oKI4Qn7Q.text: Went for an early morning breakfast. Ordered the bravocado toast and a half order of the porridge & a half order of the grain bowl. Everything including a vanilla latte were delicious! The server was excellent and gave us one of their daily special pancakes to try for free because she said we were nice :-) it was a sweet gesture and it was yummy! I always recommend people stop for a visit.

W4Zryg9_-Z-uQXJFKATL1g.text: I was in town for a week and stopped here twice.  The first time we ate on the patio and we were promptly greeted and served.  Upon asking, the server recommended a delicious sweet potato hash and even suggested to add some corn tortillas (highly recommend doing this), others had the breakfast burrito and pancakes.  All were large portions and kept us full all day.  We drove from Tempe to Sedona, hiked for several hours and didn't eat again until almost 8 hours later.  The second visit I wanted a pancakes but I didn't want only pancakes so I had the hash again (yes it's really that good) and ordered a flight of pancakes for the table.  I must say that the flight of pancakes is really a must have.  Our waitstaff was amazing both times.  Great vibe, clean, efficient, friendly.  Highly recommend.

EB5iMppfXsPNUmKaTQtbLQ.text: My dad selected this place based on reviews and local recommendations. It was absolutely amazing! Our waiter, Kevin was great and knowledgeable on all food items. We also received a starter pancake called "Sinful" something but isn't on the menu. It's made with white chocolate chips, cinnamon butter, bacon/pork belly, pecans and a syrupy glaze. OMGeee we couldn't stop eating it - it was heavenly! See individual food reviews below - we also got bloody mary's: Spicy made with habanero + jalapeno vodka and Boss Hog made with bourbon. Both were great, but I will choose a "standard" spicy BM over any kind of "wild" BMs. We would recommend this place again and again for anyone who loves a really good breakfast!   Chili Green Verde Benedict: loved the pulled pork and barbacoa with verde sauce and pico de gallo....I could eat it every morning. I couldn't even finish my hash browns, but the small amount I did eat were cooked to perfection.    Bella! Bella! Benedict: fresh, nice twist on the standard benedict, eggs were farm-fresh and excellently poached.

uSNg3wv1DZ2T9crUOX20pA.text: I have to say I wasn't a fan of eggs Benedict but NOW I AM!!! I have to say this is my new breakfast place. I am so glad I stopped by this place. If you like breakfast this is the place to get it. There Belgian waffles are great and the eggs Benedict is to die for.

U4ko3XpEUbtua1r4OdeJtQ.text: Went here after ASU graduation ceremony.  There was 15 mins wait.  The menu offers wide selection and the service was great.  Food tasted good.  I would recommend this place.

LarcVYwEmRGZwLmqunAzlA.text: I visited Arizona and came to this place every morning! Literally EVERY MORNING!!! I was so pleased with this restaurant, from the food to the customer service and atmosphere. I had like three different waiters, I remember Abby! She was super sweet and accommodation. I never had to wait for my water to be refilled and she made sure my food was perfect.   The food was delicious, especially the bacon which was thick cut and amazing and they had these really good sausage patties.The scrambled eggs were cooked perfectly, light and fluffy. I also had some French toast which was pretty good. It can get crowded though because it's near Arizona State, so there were a lot of students in line. My experience at this restaurant was great, I definitely recommend it.

The hash brown was ok too. I wasn't disappointed in the food, but it didn't wow me either. To me, it's just a breakfast place.

GPwLuuFGgKDolaFJEyV4PQ.text: Ooo. M. G. Pancake flight and Steak& eggs benedict. Everything was to die for!  I mean literally I thought I died and went to Breakfast Heaven! Whoa! We sat outside and they have LOTS of misters and a big patio complete with a ping pong table which was fun. The vibe is fun and modern with bright happy colors and open spacious feel. 67AL6tfJ8JpM19ZRkNrx3g.text: Always amazing!! I'm a big fan of breakfast, and Snooze consistently delivers. We had pineapple/orange mimosas and a few other drinks to start out. I love the option to select what juices to use in your drink; a fresh oj mimosa always hits the spot :) Between the tree of us we shared two eggs benedict (no idea which two tbh) and the sweet potato pancakes w side of chicken sausage. The pancakes were FANTASTIC, crunchy and sweet and buttery while not overpowering the sweet potato. YUM. The chicken sausage I get every time I eat at Snooze because its too flavorful and hearty to pass on. Our waitress went above and beyond for our table, was very attentive, and even brought us a complementary pancake she said was her fave. If I'd had room to eat more, I would have ordered a stack haha.. I'll just have to stop by again ;)

ga5NMuBFBQE5MNWFr0dyrQ.text: This is my favorite place to have breakfast. At first I thought the portions were a little small but I realized the portions were just right. The food is healthy and delicious. The staff always makes sure to make their customers feel special.

8m6fN8uFEJP0Ng2SpXlsmA.text: First time here! The service was great and the food was fantastic. We'll definitely be back

5_1BnwljkxODHd69fcr-tQ.text: I've tried getting into this Snooze a few times but the trick is to come here super early on the weekends and there won't be a wait. We showed up around 9am and there was a line out the door. My friend is in a wheelchair and it was next to impossible to maneuver her around the crowded tables of people without disrupting their meal. I had the sweet potato pancakes and it was not at all what I was expecting. I decided to try their regular pancakes and they also fell flat.  My friend had the break pot-pie but the eggs seemed way too gooey for my taste. I guess I will pass on Snooze from now on and just go next door.

y8sOXUSY3oMC764foA6plA.text: I've lived in Phoenix for over a year and I can't believe it took me this long to go to Snooze! I've heard a lot about this place and after going here for the first time, I understand exactly why it's so popular and why it has such a high rating on Yelp.   I came here at noon on a Saturday and it was move-in weekend for ASU, so it was pretty packed. Regardless, I was able to get a table in about ten minutes, so I didn't have to wait very long at all. Score!  The service was pretty good. My waitress was attentive and friendly, so nothing bad there.   What I especially love about this place is the variety of sweet and savory. Going into a breakfast spot is really difficult for me because I never know what to get and this place had it all! They also had about five or six different types of eggs Benedict, which I feel like is unheard of! I went with the Bella Bella Benny and it was DELICIOUS! Their hashbrowns are seriously so good too. The iced hazelnut latte really hit the spot too, plus they offer dairy substitutes (soy or almond milk).   All in all this place is fantastic. The Camelback location is more convenient for me but I'd happy return to the Tempe location! If you do, be prepared to pay for parking in either a garage or using a meter. As far as I know, Snooze doesn't validate parking.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Bella bella benny!

A1iYzFIf6aAG8DNIszZfEw.text: Really cool retro ski cabin feel. I dig it! Great location. They have a corn hole game on the patio, nice touch. The most decadent pancakes!!!   Now I'm vegan and unfortunately their Veg options are pretty sad. Tofu scramble consists of big plate of whisked tofu (unseasoned or sauces) and a sprinkle of cooked veggies with toast :(   Hopefully they update their menu to offer more Veg friendly options soon. Miss that place.

bi3OGCWstJyykdZKbR9S4A.text: This place has the best breakfast burrito of ALL TIME. Service was on point, I think my servers name was Nick. That dude had great recommenfations was attentive and super friendly.  Props to this place and it's workers, will definitely be back soon.

U_t9fo0bh1dCpDq5vQ8XqA.text: Snooze is just what I need when in Tempe.  On hot summer's days I like to get my fill to prepare for the sweaty day.  On this particular day at Snooze, coffee was ordered and so was what they called a breakfast pot pie.  And HOW GOOD IS THIS sausage gravy?  So delicious! The biscuits were flaky and I ordered the egg over easy (this was alright...)  The real surprise on my plate was the circle thick hash browns...it appeared to be cupped and cooked.  The environment was fun and we didn't have to wait too long to get a seat.

The service has been very good, with a large staff that is always eager to please. Our breakfast choices have been shrimp & grits, corned beef hash & eggs, a breakfast burrito, and huevos rancheros. Every one has been excellent. If we're ever in the area again, this is our go to spot for breakfast.

Standard and decently priced. Ambience of the restaurant was nice and the size is what you would expect for being right in the middle of a college campus. Weekends this place is packed but when we came after 12 on a Monday there was plenty of room.

XKVVMnbem6GA1KY_uXmC1w.text: Vegans and vegetarians, steer clear of this joint. I was excited to show my boyfriend this breakfast place that is vegan friendly, after going to the Gilbert location and having a wonderful experience. Service here was slow and food came out luke warm, despite being one of the few tables that had customers. My soyrizo tacos were baren, my boyfriend's hash browns were sad. The worst part; we found a piece of PORK(?) in his TOFU scramble? We showed the waitress, who walked away and avoided the issue entirely. Why have tofu and soy products of your going to just cook it where meat, and meat grease is? Disgusting. I definitely won't be going back. I don't understand how this place has so many good reviews while reading what horrible service and bland food is here.

V4G-rgm0qC9h09TmCO8Z-g.text: Decided to give snooze a try today. Overall the experience was good, but had to give them 4 stars because the Hashbrowns were bland and our server Abbie was kind of slacking. Did not offer us any condiments; order a chia tea latte never got it, even after reminding her a second time. Maybe she was having a rough day. But let me tell you, Travis is the man! He was great and very helpful to make sure my two little kids had shade from the sun. On another note the pancakes were delicious!!

a1oXxlcVxmz4aRL_zKkLGA.text: Went for Sunday brunch recently and was glad that I did. Menu options seemed endless and I was struggling to decide what to order. Luckily my friend ordered the eggs Benedict two ways so I was able to taste test those and was delighted with the corned beef hash I ordered for myself. Fresh ingredients, friendly and attentive service.  Get there early if you're starving. I arrived around 945 AM and waited 15 mins to be seated...not too bad considering the line was out the door by 10 AM.

xdJ7ag2ttrFnajWhcvZm0w.text: Snooze is an alright breakfast place. The pancakes are definitely the highlight. But they're still small. I always leave feeling hungry. I've tried the sausage Benny, really small portions as well. Snooze has a fun atmosphere and great employees but the food is disappointing. It's right on ASU's campus so many college students can come here. If you're in the mood for sweet pancakes, it's a good place. Any other type of home cooked breakfast food is a no.

CXBPplt12fVkDSjDHGJ5xw.text: Pretty long wait on weekends but the food and service are amazing every time and there are so many options.

exCzkzpQ65OBPQUUjhtSeA.text: My friend and I went to breakfast here today. I know they're packed on the weekend, but during the week it's almost empty first thing in the morning.   I had the OMG French toast. It was dessert for breakfast: French toast with mascarpone, caramel sauce, and strawberries. My dining partner had the breakfast pot pie - it looked delicious.   Our coffee cups were always full. Our server was attentive but not overbearing.  I may not be back on the weekend because of how busy it gets, but I'll be back.

qnUomeNYDMVVOAHI4QaagA.text: I love this location! The food is consistent and the staff is amazing. Especially Myhanh! She is awesome!!!!

OQYWeAf7MFlDxzcAiASQmg.text: Very friendly service. My Benny was delicious with perfect poached eggs and stacked hash browns. My table mates got pancakes and chicken sausage. They were yummy too but too sweet for me. Perfect location near campus.

hQo5aEC3f3M_MjfWt7Rlxw.text: When I visited Denver over the holidays I tried eating at Snooze but the wait was too long before my flight. So I was wonderfully surprised and delighted when I found out Snooze was coming to Tempe!  I am so glad I never got to have my first time experience at Snooze in Denver because I don't know if they would have been able to live up to the hospitality I received at the Tempe location.    The food was remarkable. Absolutely delicious. I sat at the bar and the servers Adrianne & Tori were fantastic. They even brought us a peanut butter cup pancake on the house! I am a pancake fanatic so this made my dining experience that much more enjoyable!   Two thumbs way up for Snooze! I will most definitely be back.

3gTFQVRGNulWzEHelRMq1w.text: Great food, amazing and friendly service and the mimosas are the perfect addition to a great breakfast. mAYJGHSs8K-JazlV7DONeQ.text: I just tried this place the other day and got the continental breakfast, ( grapefruit, yogurt, and toast). The yogurt was amazingly yummy! It was super busy when I went in which is always a good sign and I look forward to going back and trying some new items!

pF3120QKRxF4jpZ7q9hEhg.text: Snooze is my favorite brunch place. I'm so glad one opened up in Tempe. I always get the breakfast pretzel sandwich. My husband gets the Ham Benedict. We LOVE the sweet potato pancake and OMG French Toast. I hope this place never goes out of business!

7yi_NZb4t-dB-F6S3qin0A.text: This place is great for breakfast! Staff is very friendly, they are fast at getting food out. Definitely want to come early because they get packed fast! Ordered the eggs Benedict and it was delicious! Also ordered the Ruben sandwich and it was great too!

ugQ-4BiMRqNOUzQjaAziXw.text: Very fun place to go for breakfast or brunch. Their "OMG! French Toast" is SO YUMMY! And they have delicios mimosas too! Sometimes I've been and received slow service; but always enjoy their food.

C4uE88MrQwevs7aJqK5CpQ.text: Delicious all around! Celebrating my husband's bday while visiting from Chicago and this was a perfect spot for brunch! Food, drinks, service - all around wonderful. Thank you Snooze!

fMCqibQSE6829T7UefH7eQ.text: The food is pretty good, nothing too special. It's very expensive honestly, but it has a nice atmosphere and it's something new for Tempe. I would recommend the pancake flight, which is three mini pancakes of all their pancake choices, so it's a great way to try new things!

MyFcdwpayC7XraEIuIQi6A.text: We met our daughter here for breakfast for the first time since she started attending nearby ASU! Their breakfast menu is loaded with numerous tasty sounding options and with a big mug of great coffee, a patient waitress and such a comfy and fun environment, we took an unusually long time to make our decision! Breakfast came fairly quickly and no one in our mixed group was disappointed! Everything perfectly delicious, very unique and beautifully served!  I ordered the "pancake of the day" and a good day it was! Sweet potato pancake with cranberry compote, caramel butter and a drizzle of cream, with a fabulous cranberry syrup! AMAZing!! The casual and chic ambiance, the indescribable selection of amazing and unique menu options available made this an excellent breakfast choice for any occasion or group! I want to try something new, but I'm already craving what I had this morning!! Can't wait to go back!

GbrHNEaB2dcTO0zcatqQKQ.text: This has got to be one of the cutest places I've been to for breakfast in a long time! Besides the fact that I have a special place in my heart for local businesses,this place blew me away!! I went around 9 AM with a friend on a Tuesday morning and was quickly seated out front on the patio. The view is beautiful and the staff is lovely. Although I can't remember exactly what I ordered from the menu, I remember that it was absolutely wonderful. An added bonus was that they're dog friendly!

nDJTjSRJJ_pKWNPabruUKQ.text: Heard this place had a best French Toast so I've ordered Just a French Toast Neat with a pouched egg and sausages on the side. This is not your typical eggs and bacon food- They take the basics and step it up with the presentation! So if you aren't willing to wait you will be sorry...you won't find this food in any other breakfast joint.

The boyfriend got the ham Benedict and that was really tasty. I would definitely come here again and try something different.

Overall this place was ok in the food department

KUpWjQ2W1M07H4nkwvB3eg.text: Love this place! Great French toast and great service. They don't take reservations so be expected to have a wait of 30-45 mins during peak hours. But it's worth it! Definitely a favorite.

zcwTLtvzdOT2R7pj8NCkAw.text: I've been here so many times and I always leave with a happy stomach. Warning: There is always an extremely long wait on weekends. When I went today, I got the pancake of the day which was a strawberries and white chocolate one (you can order single pancakes). It was super fluffy and I got a bite of strawberry with each bite. I also ordered the BEAT sandwich, and the bacon tomato aioli was to die for. The ciabatta bread was nice and soft, and overall it was delicious. My all time favorite pancake is the sweet potato one. Whenever I bring someone new there, I force them to try it and they never regret it. If you prefer french toast, I highly recommend the OMG French Toast because it is amazing.

UUKWPt1FDRt-egJjIhutWg.text: The decor in this restaurant was so cute; it was very retro.  The breakfast menu was extensive making it hard to make a decision. We ended up with the breakfast burrito (very good, the green chili made it) and the homemade granola (awesome) along with 1 flight sized pineapple upside down pancake, which was the best pancake I have every had!  I also like the option to get a flight of pancakes to try all of their wonderful varieties.  The coffee was also very good and our server was very friendly and helpful.  I cannot wait to visit AZ and hit this place up again!

I also tried some of the sweet breakfasts like pineapple upside down pancakes which are killer. 4 stars?  Well, we waited a long time for our seat, I suspect you will too...

Second, it was a little light on the hollandaise sauce, which makes or breaks the entire dish itself.  A co-worker ordered French Toast and side of bacon. Both were on point!
