GipxCUj-iCd_vHR_ampopQ.text: This is what I ate/drank:  french toast, side of chorizo, cold brew coffee and a bloody mary.  I liked it lots.  My server was polite and efficient in carrying out his duties regarding the service of our food and busing.  But...he failed to defend my eating companion from a curious little wasp who was all up in her biz trying to sniff around the eggs and such.    NOT COOL MAN. DON'T MAKE ME WAVE AWAY A WASP; I DON'T LIKE THEM. That's it. I recommend it. The wait wasn't too bad.

jxfuhMk80LnrtOKnlTJ_bg.text: Ordered 2 breakfast burritos -   One of them had ranchero sauce which taste basically like tomato paste - no flavor at all, no spice at all.   The other was ordered with green chile - equally lacking in flavor but better than the ranchero.   The green chile burrito was also ordered with avocado, a 2.50 cost, and there was no avocado present in the burrito at all.   Both burritos contained more black beans than any other ingredient - there were maybe 1-2 scrambled eggs in each burrito but how could you taste the egg when every bite contained mostly black beans?  Both burritos had hashed Browns in them, however, my definition of hash browns is crispy fried potato strings and these were virtually raw sliced potatoes with not a single bit of brown showing on them.   For my total cost being 16.50 for the green chile burrito and about 13 for the ranchero this is just a huge huge waste of time and money. I could have eaten at Chelsea's kitchen and had an amazing chilaquiles with breakfast mimosas for the same price and been far far happier.  Honestly this is the biggest most overhyped breakfast restaurant I've encountered with prices that are on par with a resort and food on par with a high school cafeteria.   Save your time and money and go elsewhere.

86eK0-601kBRtAJmcHpXMA.text: This is our go to place for fancy breakfast. We try to get in as early as possible because they get so packed usually with a long line. If we are too hungry, we opt out to eat at Postinos right next door:) I always get egg benedict and my husband gets breakfast burrito. Cute, open atmosphere and yummy food!

KYJbz_HQ0gXFO1jp-1Z0-g.text: As a few other reviewers have noted, this place is extremely overhyped.  I was super excited to try it and was disappointed both with the food and the service. They told us the wait would be 30 minutes, we waited over double this. It took over an hour. The thing that particularly frustrated me is that toward the end of my wait, I watched two people just waltz in in front of us. Apparently they had some open bar seating available that was first come first serve, and no one mentioned to us that this was an option.  By the time I got to my seat I was a little annoyed, but the menu looked good and after the wait I really wanted to enjoy myself. The server took our order, and literally never came back. Someone else brought out the food, and we practically had to beg the guy to take our money since he had evidently forgot we were there.  To add fuel to the fire, neither of our meals were good. I wouldn't say it was awful, but it definitely wasn't anything worth going back for. The food was plain and cooked poorly. I was really disappointed in the entire experience and won't be going back.

II8Z_IbNloExybtIo-3uTw.text: Snooze made my day! Right after they opened I ate outdoors.  The atmosphere, music  and view if the mountain were perfect. I had the choose two Benedict option and I had one Benny Goodman and one with the shredded  pork and green chili. The sausage Patty had an awesome brown crust and great flavor. The hash browns were perfect , I requested them crispy and they had just a touch of spice/heat. I found the all of my food to be seasoned just right.  Gloria was our server and she was super attentive, was happy to share her knowledge and had great suggestions.  I will be back again tomorrow to do it again!

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States

ackzcldn64X5CCFrErTbQA.text: Best food,  service,  music and location. Highly recommended. So delicious and sitting outside on a Saturday morning was fantastic.

V_dhUu3QwkhAoBOEVKh9jQ.text: I love snooze, this isn't my first time coming here but I think it's time for a review! I usually end up getting an omelet but this time ordered the snooze spuds deluxe and the OMG French toast, and this will be my go to combo from now on to share with a friend of course! Everyone is always so friendly here and the ambiance keeps us coming back!

d5TiTBH2g0nkFrGVLKsgOw.text: Excellent cup of coffee = five stars!!!  However the food was just as good.  Bacon not overly salty, egg poached perfectly, service rocked!  Definitely add this your list of breakfast places!

FNnrJ90jcVfhvs1yU69y7w.text: Ordered in breakfast this morning and it was AWESOME. We did a pancake flight w the blueberry Danish, sweet potato, and pineapple upside-down pancakes. SO tasty!! We will absolutely order them all again. We also got the snooze spuds deluxe and were ecstatic to see that they have soyrizo! The most satisfying and delicious breakfast we have had in a long time. :)

gFCuHrnxu7LOGkZFwSx4Tw.text: Absolutely the best breakfast I've had in... ever. When we got there we saw the line was out the door and was told the wait would be about 20 minutes. We ended up waiting about 30-35 minutes and Adrian, the manager, made sure we were compensated for that by giving us 2 complimentary pancakes. Adrian was great, she wasn't our server but she was still very attentive. We were greeted and served by about  5 different very friendly people can't even remember all of the names.  The food was phenomenal. Hubby got a benne duo, one late harvest and one chilaquiles. The beef barbacoa on the chilaquiles was tender and had wonderful flavor, and the late harvest was full of delicious fall veggies and was on top of a smooth creamy grit cake. My pancake flight were the best 3 pancakes I've ever had in life. Drunkn punkn, sweet potato, and the pancake of the day was buttermilk with Bacon pieces inside topped with strawberries and nutella sauce and marscapone! So along with the pineapple upside down and blueberry danish which were complimentary, I tried 5 different flavors of deliciousness. They were all great. Bottomless cup of coffee and really good lemonade too. Nothing to complain about on the food.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Benne duo with late harvest and chilaquiles and blueberry danish pancake
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Pancake flight; from left to right punkn, pancake of the day, and sweet potato. Small plate is blueberry danish.

3FoYZQ6cm8olvq4eIzaNhw.text: I'm visiting from out of town and found Snooze on Yelp. From the service to the food and drinks to the atmosphere, I give this place a 5 star. They gave me a complimentary pancake so I could get a feel for the type of food they offer, with it being my first time here. It was so decadent, melt in your mouth good. I got the Sandwich I Am as my main item and it was amazing. I will definitely be coming back. Thank you Snooze and the employees for a wonderful experience.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Sandwich I Am. It was amazing.
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. This was the pancake of the day some banana cream, cocoa powder,pecan, brown sugar concoction. It was incredibly scrumptious.

4ZJ4Aouhs6-KKKWmwrkS0A.text: There was a little wait, but what do ya expect on a Sunday afternoon! :) Everyone was friendly, from the hostess to my waitress, Dee was awesome! The food was eggcellent!

T-TJFnHtxwo0fhz921vx1w.text: Snooze is always a great place for the family. They have very good flavors of pancakes. I always recommend the pineapple pancake. They are a morning eatery. They get very packed on the weekends especially Saturday. The staff is very nice and helpful.

A0Yue2UxVlsp2VFi34aGjw.text: Great food and atmosphere. Our waitress was amazing! I had the breakfast pot pie, it was fantastic! Definitely will be back.

46C3VITc7cMwNx0zboRd0A.text: A good place to eat breakfast, all in all, but I have some reservations.  I again ordered the Breakfast Pot Pie, as I did in Denver. It is good, but not great. There isn't anything filling about it and the gravy was skimpy at this location. After cleaning my plate I left unsatisfied. It's a clever dish, just not dialed-in in my opinion. For the price there needs to be a better meal put in front of me. If I come back I am trying something else because all the other people at my table had ample portions, so much to the point they could not finish their food.  The coffee, man, what the heck? For a coffee they tout they have gone to great lengths to assure the integrity of it is about as flavorful as a cup of Folgers. One of the biggest disappointments for me in a breakfast spot is the lack of attention to the coffee and how it compliments the food. This coffee is simply not there.  The service was spot on. Great staff that were energetic and accommodating. I am positively impressed with their care and attention to detail. And to tell a table at the height of service on a Sunday to "take your time, no hurry, do you want more coffee?" is as about as welcoming as a place can get. Great job, folks.

mLTS8AwoMiZRil9lRTZHmg.text: This is my second time here and my first time experience was great. Our waiter was very friendly and helpful. But for the second time I'm here, I'm not happy at all. I ordered a cold brew coffee and asked for cream and sugar when I ordered it. And I asked for it again when my waiter took my food order. After a long wait, I asked for cream and sugar for the THIRD time. Then my food came up and my cream and sugar was still not here. Then the waiter finally brought them to me. No apology at all. After we finished our food and he brought us check so fast and I even did not ask for it yet. Anyway, I will not eat here ever again.

WX2CLrozqw6YHWFgnFFp_Q.text: Took a trip to AZ for a baseball game (Go Dodgers) and one of the locals recommended this place... and OMG, this place is delicious! I want to go back to AZ just for their hash browns! Eggs were yummy too and the whole meal was inexpensive. My friends enjoyed their food too, including their mimosas. Ambiance is pretty chill. Nice, clean and great service.

8CFvVbW6QuZkJt7ecEpmjA.text: Excellent food, fun menu, great brunch location and beverages. Cons are paid parking, and there is usually a wait because food is so delicious.

jpocBzSLLrx4dwka-nxgyw.text: In town for a wedding and we showed up around 10 on a Friday.  20 minute wait but it was totally worth it.  Not only was this one of the most flavorful and delicious breakfasts Ive ever had, but our waiter Flip (I think was his name) was above and beyond.  I've honestly never had a waiter foresee the needs of the table so quickly and instantly.  You'd thing this was a $200 a plate steak house.  Amazing service and amazing food, I will definitely be returning!

Ld3jLFHkzI36AIn9hy8aZA.text: Delicious! Eggs benedict mix and match? Yes please! perfect place for a relaxing Sunday brunch with delicious mimosa options.  Definitely making it a more regular spot.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Bella bella / caprese Benedicts

k7ARSgdEk7RFzQ89kX-B-w.text: reliably fresh, reliably friendly, reliably not boring food. thank you!

2kpvEytOn9qvrt5zsB5wNQ.text: My hubby, daughter and I enjoyed a lovely brunch at Snooze yesterday. We are excited for them to open in Scottsdale, near where we live. I must say the art deco, bright ambiance gives the proper anticipation of a fun meal. I started with an MMMmmm Mimosa which was light and lovely. Carlene, our server, made the entire experience excellent. She even had a whimsical bacon and egg hair clip that she made. Shows you right off the bat, she loves her work. Since it was our first visit she brought us (on her) the pineapple upside down pancake with cinnamon butter. I don't even like sweets, but it was DIVINE! We all scooped it up. Our sweet daughter had the tomato soup and grilled cheese, which she loved. The soup almost tasted like a marinara. Very fresh and delicious. I had the lox, rye, capers, herbed goat cheese, and arugula plate. It was very good. My husband had the corned beef hash. It came out cold and they immediately retired it and made it right. The manager( forgot his name- glasses and a ponytail) did a great job of assuring that it would be perfect the next time.   All in all, we are not going to want to wait until the end of August when Kierland opens so we will be back. BRAVO! Laurie and Rodney Malone

VIPaJ2pbre1sBxnZJ-z_hA.text: I came here again with a large group of people on a Sunday morning. Our seating was a bit awkward in that staff moved a u-shaped table up to a booth so we all could be together. I'm not complaining about that as that's just how things work when a place is busy. My biggest complaint in my original review was the awful music. I upgrade this to 4 stars as the music was a bit kinder and gentler this time around.

AJasAKAECQOVRqGb65uoqw.text: Nice hipster breakfast spot in the heart of Tempe. We went Saturday afternoon around 1pm. Our hostess was very pleasant and seated us right away. 5 Star for Kaitlyn our server she was on point the entire time. Damn I'm still buzzed from the cold pressed coffee. The wife got Juan's tacos with bacon and they were awesome. The bacon was crispy and meaty. They carry Sriracha and that's the extra kicker I needed. I had the pancake flight, pineapple, strawberry, and blueberry. They were all good but the blueberry was by far the best. The portion size was small for $9. I would have paid whatever for bigger portions. If not for the taco my wife shared with me, I would have left hungry. The reviews are spot on about how loud it is. It's hard to carry on a conversation and not be overwhelmed with overhearing your neighbors plans for the day/night.

aH7stAxFaYEcRJGJ0zxEAA.text: First time at snooze this morning and it was excellent!  We had Kate as our waitress, she was sweet, prompt and knowledgable!  I tried the eggs Benedict, one with salmon the other had pork and green chili, both were excellent!!  We had a party of four and everyone enjoyed their meal and we all left satisfied.  Definitely going to be back again!  Only thing that could have improved our experience would have been a misting system on the patio!  We opt out of the wait by getting seated immediately on the patio..  It was covered which was nice, but a misting system would have made it that much more enjoyable!

9GVESTtlMZqtHyQY3fPsqQ.text: We loved the Snooze in San Diego and I'm happy to say the Tempe snooze is just as good !

Td368qBFsTWUih1fO-IWXw.text: Amazing food and device. We're visiting from Out of town, and this place was recommended to us. I wish it was here when I went to ASU. Allyson and Kate provided excellent service at the bar. It's sometimes rare to find this type of service in a college town. The pineapple upside down pancake was to die for. Will definitely be back!

Zp-hJqiaT5-bnTuK3DzN3A.text: Service was great. I had the strawberry fields pancakes and found them very enjoyable. My wife had the pot pie that used filo dough. It was very good although it could have been served a little warmer. The menu here offers some unique items. It is a little pricey but that doesn't seem to bother the crowd. We are looking forward to Snooze AM opening up in Gilbert. Two things kept it from getting 5 stars from me... the pot pie could have been warmer and prices are a tad high. We were pleased with our serving sizes for both items we ordered.

ktN98U3OSfxoyTj1FCpDDQ.text: Delicious. Some of the best breakfast food I've had. Get the French toast. It's to die for!

k-gMPzWGdiKkROjgtoWG5A.text: This place is a little pricey for me personally (I'm pretty cheap) but god is it good. The Spuds deluxe is to die for but I'd recommend a half-order if you don't plan on sharing. Also highly recommend treating yourself to a mimosa. Friendly staff, good atmosphere/music. Don't really love the patio but its pretty necessary as the place is quite small.

t149z3-3tV6ALfpV0GpFxg.text: I tried the omelet and it was excellent.  There was so much good stuff on the menu this place merits multiple trips just to try it all.  My wife got the blueberry pancakes and they looked to die for.

kCZ5meSjhxH528J4ANl4nA.text: My girlfriend and I came here for the first time the other day, and the food was awesome! I got the grilled cheese sandwich with tomato soup, and a cinnamon pancake (random, I know), and she got the OMG French toast. The only reason I'm not giving 5 stars is because there was stuff floating in my water, and there still was even after they replaced my drink. Definitely give this place a try!

_nnZ0THdJG7S2JyM49kWdg.text: Fantastic food, service, and atmosphere!  Takes awhile to get a table, but even that was a great experience with games, seating, free coffee.

g8Y17CbT3uifGf8FGJSAVQ.text: This is my favorite place in Tempe. They are dog friendly, which is awesome. There are no bad options on the menu, and the prices are reasonable. Great staff. Always friendly.

z3o21rkZ5Hx0ocV2HVPksg.text: Great place. We wanted to try a new brunch place , near Tempe and saw this one on yelp. Great place, great food. Staff is friendly. U have to reach early coz usually waiting is 20 mins. About food - its awesome. Pancakes are mouthwatering. One must try pancakes definitely. The options on menu are lot. Will visit again. Soon

hxTEHj_B3YOlJpgwocvdxw.text: The best breakfast in town.  I have not had a single bad experience at any Snooze location.  If you are a meat and potatoes person, they have a pile of hash browns with whatever fixings you want!

EFeQX4Q_bGosxi46Tw1ZlA.text: I heard a lot of great reviews about this place so I decided to check it out because of their famous pancakes. When I arrived the line was so long so I opted to take out. One of the waiters was very accommodating however the one of the ones up in front didn't seem to care if I was there. I waited about 30 minutes and when I finally sat down to eat my food. The beacon was burnt the egg was under cooked and the pancakes were alittle dry and hard. I hate to say the food didn't even compensate for the service. I was disappointed. Unfortunate for the first time experience.

NpUxR97Fzg4-zyuhgQg_YA.text: Was in yesterday for brunch and am super dissapointed. I ordered the corned beef hash and what came out was a thin layer of burnt hashbrowns with an almost undetectable amount of hash. I expressed my concern to the server and she told me they were working on the recipe and would bring me out another side of hash. It came out about 10 mins later and was much better than what I originally recieved. I was charged for both my meal and the side which ended up costing over 15 dollars. I've been in the food service industry for 6 years and believe this situation was handled improperly. Definitly won't be returning and will be advising everyone to do the same.

zKdb-4cPBpwcokMnHM7kXQ.text: I've only heard rave reviews about this place and had been encouraged for weeks to try this with the ever efficient quote of "YOU Would LOVE This Place", and part of that is True.  We went on a busy Sunday morning which is always a nice time for brunch and people watching. we also had just done a vigorous hike prior and were starving! We arrived around 10 am and we were Finally seated around 1045. only 20 mins past the given wait time, and without even an "I'm so sorry the wait will be longer then expected" or even a general nod in our direction. We were told to download an app and wait for our name to appear, we were never approached about our table being ready.  After being seated our server came by with waters (no straws) She was training a new employee and kindly introduced us to her. She then left the table and didn't return for about 5 mins to take our drink order. 1 beer and the hopes of a taster were ordered. the person who ordered the taster had to wait an extra 7 mins to place her drink order because our server was no where to be found. We were starving and wanting to order, seeing as we had 45 mins before being sat to browse their menu we all already knew what we were after. We finally were able to flag down our server and were able to order.  THE FOOD (actually came out pretty quick) man!!!! I wish I could review the food. I ordered a BREAKFAST BURRITO with the soyrizo (soy Chorizo) instead of eggs. my girlfriends ordered veggie omelets and scrambles, which looked amazing, and pancakes.  I had asked prior if the soyrizo was going to be spicy and was instantly put at ease that it was mild and full of flavor. I had one bite of my burrito and my mouth was on fire. if there was flavor it was masked by the intense amount of spices that were bombarding my taste buds. My girlfriends hash browns was more like wet mush in a ring, and the scramble was almost too much on the wet side for the eggs to have been cooked all the way thru. Too bad our server was also MIA yet again during our ENTIRE MEAL. I would have liked to have tried something I could actually eat considering my stomach was probably growling loud enough for our neighboring table to hear (even over the blaringly loud club dance music they were playing).  THE SERVICE I work in the F&B industry and have been a proud provider of excellent customer service for 15 years ( so I do sorta know what Im talking about, not saying Im the best.... I just understand what makes a complete experience) well we definatly got an experience alright.  Our service LACKED every quality of a good experience.  1)Drink orders were taken 5-12 mins after being seated.  2)we had top flag down our server after being sat for almost 20 mins to have our food order taken 3)NOT ONCE did the server stop by, after getting us the required condiments we had asked for in our food order, to see if our food was even to our liking!!!!! that is ELEMENTRY!!!! my plate was pushed to the side with one bite taken out with a napkin on top of it for close to 38 mins before our server returned. 4) SHE DIDNT EVEN ACKNOLEDGE the uneaten food when she did return 5) When the server was informed that the food was inediable she had the manager take care of it..... funny the manager didn't stop by.  Zero Stars for: Service was POOR and SLOW (the girl she was training was more attentive to the tables) Zero Stars for: The Food well they would probably get more stars if I had even been able to try any of it.   They do get one star however for Decor and Such, this place is super HIP and FUNKY with round booths and an open air concept. This is a place that wants to be seen.  All in All this was a disappointing experience and I wont be returning to give it a second chance. If any friends or relatives ask about this place I will highly discourage them from wasting their time and money.

CrQ6YO8Opd2S8pSE7P0yZQ.text: Never disappoints. Got the Breakfast Pot Pie this time.

36Drz-p-wWM7SO5lz4zFWg.text: Great atmosphere! Our waitress Lizzie was friendly and informative. Being a vegetarian I'm always looking for new soy and tofu products, and I highly recommend the soyrizo! Even the carnivore in our group said it tasted just like real chorizo. The food was great and the service was quick! The pineapple upside down pancakes were to die for. 10/10 would recommend

nA2oQSMIYlkeRENnDSm5KQ.text: Love the pancakes. Definitely encourage the three pancakes options, don't miss the sweet potatoes and pineapple ones. Amazing.

fbI6SW9HYX7PnUxIEoPjZA.text: This is a really great breakfast/brunch spot in the heart of ASU. If there is a wait...trust me...you need to wait. From start to finish the service and food are phenomenal. Tori and Adrienne at the bar are awesome and friendly. We got complimentary samples of hot chocolate, as well an amazing creation called the pineapple upside down pancake. This is seriously the best pancake I've ever had. Oozing with cinnamon butter and pineapple sauce and perfectly crisp. And that wasn't even the food we ordered! I had the Winter Harvest Benny Benedict. Nice twist on a regular old Benedict. It's a polenta base with Brussels sprouts. Tasted amaze balls! And the hash browns that came with it were just as good. Start to finish, from the friendly service, fun decor, and the food is seriously on point. Do yourself a favor and forget whatever place you eat brunch at and go here. I'm stoked to return for all the goodness. Snooze makes me want to be in a continual food coma. YUUUM!!

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Winter harvest Benny! On polenta cakes....off the chain.
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Pineapple upside down pancake! Seriously one, if not the best, pancake I&#39;ve ever had!
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Free hot chocolate samples!

cosa1Y-bmy4HzteFSIMAVQ.text: Sweet or savory. No matter what you order from the menu, the food is delicious! Great staff with wonderful service. We drive out of our way to visit this Snooze location because we get treated by the manager, Travis.

0f7jqMZWxU8nRJkcrSeDNA.text: I was BEYOND impressed with the service here. After I placed my order, the waitress overheard me telling my boyfriend how I wish I ordered the sweet potato pancakes because they looked SO good....so my waitress was kind enough to bring me one to try! It was the service of the employees and the AMAZING food that made this experience unforgettable.

17ExuVhLxCm7WNWhU2nwkg.text: Our favorite place for breakfast/brunch in the valley. The breakfast burrito was the first thing I tried and it was AMAZING! Had to take some home in a doggy bag because it is big. Have also tried the French toast and pancakes. Everything is so great on their menu we keep going back for more! I like that you can sip on coffee while you wait for a table and the service is excellent. Will definitely be making this a regular location of ours.

fDbhZWNS73GJjz0090EbEw.text: Went here for the first time this morning. I was meeting a friend with a baby so I went 25 mins before we were to meet so that she didn't have to  (I had seen in reviews that Saturday mornings were terribly crowded). I arrived about 8:40am and had a table by 8:45! I was so surprised. I told the hostess my plan and they went ahead and seated me anyway. The staff was great and the food was really tasty. I had the breakfast tacos. They were really good but I didn't finish just because I had gotten full from the pancake flight we shared.   The retro decor is also super cute. I can't wait to go back on a day I don't have to work. Mimosas!!!

3gK_BN5uxzD556eWpSjX3g.text: First time here had Kylie was our waitress and made this visit amazing. She was kind, courteous, very attentive & had pretty good knowledge of the menu which is a huge plus! Ask for Kylie!

FL205w7dZ-kQjnbBRcZ46Q.text: Hungover from a night of rocking out with Roger Clyne and the Peacemakers at the Yucca Tap Room, we woke up in the morning in search of breakfast. Travelocity pointed us this way.   Sunday morning/ish, we crawled across town, found parking, and approached the packed eatery. We shared a high top table with six other people in almost a cafeteria feel, appropriate for a college setting, and quickly realized we were the oldest people in the joint.  Who cares. Coffee. Please.   Waitress was adorable, sweet, helpful and fast. Got us that coffee and some water (good for your hangover) and I ordered the Breakfast Burrito (must have in AZ or NM when you're coming there from Boston) and my husband got the corned beef hash.   the burrito was outstanding. Got the green and red chile sauce in Christmas style, and had sausage added. Ten thumbs up. It was as big as my head and I ended up sharing about 1/3 of it with my husband.   The girl sitting catty-corner from me asked what it was and we struck up a conversation about the food and options. I didn't feel old anymore - I felt like just another breakfast woofer amongst a bunch of students, and then realized there were some parents there with their college kids and the place opened up to a bigger family feel in my mind.   I thought about a morning cocktail to keep the roll going, but we had to make tracks. The menu looked fantastic for such treats, and I kind of regret not getting one ...   maybe next time.   Wish there was a Snooze here in Boston. I'd so go.

VTwCs6tRXMFAWr01YNCtLg.text: This place changed everything. I went in the middle of a huge argument with my girlfriend over what would be our power couple name would be but as soon as we entered the restaurant, it all went away. It's like we stepped through a wormhole leading to breakfast heaven. The candy apple pancakes restored my faith in humanity. A choir of angels sounded as I took my first bite. I watched a blind man get his sight after one piece of bacon, and the chickens came out to personally introduce each egg. There was something cool about the coffee I don't remember, but it tastes like liquid nirvana. Long story short, don't go here if you hate good food, a friendly staff, or life in general.

W3UgJ8yMf-LX0wECK0Hz2g.text: I'm a big fan of this place.  I love breakfast and they do a very good breakfast.  It is a bit on the expensive side for a breakfast place.  Sometimes I miss having Jam's next to campus.  The chocolate pancakes are decent but if you really want something different opt for a barbacoa omelet.

xzlVubr9Kg8CtVnEbMgZCA.text: If you are vegan the choices are limited. They do offer a tofu scramble that is very good. It is served with hashbrowns and toast. Other things on the menus that i saw was the porridge(i haven't tried that yet).

6PdFyWd5_kipZWVn8au2eA.text: Had breakfast there with my parents, my husband and kids.  All the food was so good and I loved our server,  Bobby. kXGTnZc7V77lnPpfuge2RQ.text: Sunday morning breakfast .... Get there before 8:30am or be prepared to wait. Food delicious Spouse had pancakes and we are pancake snobs, no one ever can meet our expectations.  These were blueberry pancakes and they were as close to homemade as I've tasted. DElicious Mom and I split an egg/spinach sandwich on ciabatta with holland aide aioli. Kitchen split in two plates for us always a very classy touch. Aioli served in side instead of sandwich ...great move so each ca put as little or much as they want. Ciabatta was fresh and soft, aioli was just the right flavor smack for the sandwich. Only complaint is they should have soy creamer not just soy milk. Our Sunday morning was late March so at that hour it was beautiful and cool.  But all they have is garage doors open and patios with umbrellas. Owners are from Colorado ... Obviously don't have a concept of 120 degree weather.  They should be made to eat an entire lunch meal on patio from April in and rethink their cooling strategy  Sales will certainly tell.  No matter how delicious the food is, it can't be enjoyed under little shade and no cooling

qvTaMBkZ9x1RMGQKN5E14Q.text: Unique and delicious food. The staff was wonderful and let me bring my puppy in due to being out of town on vacation! The continental is a flavorful choice with Carmel brulee grapefruit and agave nectar Greek yogurt mmm

e7mTLwYPsiZ6OzQR6WIZ_g.text: My friend and I had just flown into Phoenix from Indianapolis by way of Cincinnati in the early morning. We had a lengthy flight and had been up for quite a while without sleep or food. While picking up our car rental from Turo, the car's owner recommended this place for some coffee and breakfast, and I'm sure glad he did. The service was spectacular, the house blend coffee was fantastic, and the food was delicious. Our server, Angela, was as polite as could be and even brought us out a free sweet potato pancake fresh from the kitchen for us to try. She made us feel very welcome from the get-go. The food was simply incredible. My friend got the Snooze Classic and I got the half-and-half order of Eggs Benedict with the Chili Verde and Steak & Eggs. Everything on my plate was fresh, flavorful, and cooked to perfection. The steak was cooked a perfect medium-rare which suit the dish very well, the grilled asparagus and onions were an excellent compliment, and the pico de gallo tasted like it was picked fresh from the garden. The menu has plenty of options for every palette and the cocktail bar will satisfy anyone as well. I would definitely recommend Snooze for breakfast if you're in the Tempe area, I'd eat breakfast here every morning if I could.

oDJQtRqZErUTNVO7w2kGKA.text: I went in today with my friend for a late breakfast and it was so amazing!! I got the ham Benedict III and my friend got the breakfast pot pie and they were both amazingly delicious. Our server (can't remember her name but we were on the patio around 12 if that helps!) was fantastic. She brought me a hot toddy and it was presented in the cutest way I have ever seen. I can't wait to come back :)

gX91FxbScJqHkGE45OvyhQ.text: Mmmmmm... so good! You can't go wrong with Snooze. I love their eggs benedicts -- all of them are absolutely delicious. My friend recommended the chilaquiles one, and she had the great insight to substitute the corn tortilla with English muffins. Yes, it makes it less authentic, but corn tortilla just don't soak up that deliciously runny egg as well as English muffins do. It is absolutely heavenly!  My very first time at Snooze as at the Gilbert location, and that day, all of our orders were incredibly salty. I've also had some rather curt servers there. However, the staff (servers and chefs) here at the Tempe location know what they are doing. The food came out better than I expected and the servers were friendly. Although we waited an hour to be seated (this was a Saturday morning at 10 am), it was definitely worth it. Next time I am feeling in the mood for brunch at Snooze, I will pick this location over the Gilbert one.

aPlDyXTslW3lnC3oyndGww.text: The three of us went to Snooze last Sunday and we were looking for something special.  After waiting 45 minutes for a table we were seated and then waited 30 minutes for our breakfast to arrive.  When we received it, all three dishes were lukewarm.  This is a big turn off to us.  My wife had the Pancake flight and she found it just OK, there just wasn't much taste over the sugar.  My son was satisfied with his breakfast.  I asked for an omelet with chorizo, sausage and two orders of cheddar.  What I received was a lukewarm omelet swimming in a sea of grease.  It was awful.   When I received the bill, I understood why.  I did not get what I ordered, I received an omelet with sausage crumble.  And the bill. . for three of us, about $50.

We recently moved here from Seattle and I loved all of the hype surrounding Snooze so we have given it a try on multiple occasions but am otherwise underwhelmed with their menu and overall experience.   My family has gone to the downtown Tempe location multiple times and have enjoyed it but find the hype a little overrated for what we were met with. Being there at brunch you know it's busy but the waiters have been so maxed and are literally at the table to take your order then you're on your own which is a bummer. WeVyk-BXCXAvx_ygJYlYVw.text: If I could give this place a 10, I would! FOOD!  Now the food.. my god! The flavors in our meals.. were just the BOMB! I had some benedict.. with a green sauce, pico de gallo and tortillas..can't remember NAMES RIght now.. but let's just say I didn't leave one BIT behind! DkJXOnt1D8QVlRUvrKgJLA.text: Corned beef hash = a smash! Service so gracious, in a dining room that's spacious Enough for baby to take a stroller snooze.   I was in Tempe for work and had my infant with me; of course she woke up on East Coast time and I knew I would need a hearty breakfast and espresso to start the day. Snooze was a short walk from my hotel and opens at 6:30 am (thank goodness!). My waitress was so sweet, tucked me and the stroller in a corner, and was very attentive throughout my meal. My cappuccino was really good - miles beyond espresso in New England brunch places. The corned beef hash was spicy, filling, and delicious, and the young man who brought it to my table said, "I hope you enjoy!" What more could I want out of this experience? I just wish there were a Snooze in Providence!

0M9VdYblJCgEzdaqyI-q4A.text: -Snooze Spuds Delux with chorizo and bacon - super hearty. My soon to be son-in-law who doesn't know it yet, loved it and the thick slices of bacon earned it 5 out of 5 stars.  ~Pancake flight with pancake of the day (blackberry), blueberry danish, and pineapple upside down. My daughter loved the blackberry the best .. hidden caramelized walnuts in the pancake gave it the oohhh-what's-this surprise. Upside down and blackberry pancakes were excellent as well. 5 out of 5.   ~Benny Dua with chilaquilles and chili verde: very nicely done and well presented. It was an interesting take on eggs Benedict. It wasn't as saucy so the flavor would permeate but it was delicious nevertheless. 4 out of 5 ~OMG! French toast: never came. So we got this taken off our bill. Glad though because we didn't realize that was hellalot of food after we had put in the order.  ~Fall greens- I had to represent the healthy side of the family. Would order this again. Greens were fresh and the sweetness of the beets and the saltiness of the thick chunks of bacon perfectly complimented the naturally  lightly bitterness of the baby kale. 5 out of 5.  Flip was our friendly server. Not going to blame him for the OMG French toasts because we didn't need them anyway.  The restaurant was well lit, open, and clean. It has a welcoming aura to it.   Restroom is clean.

s2QsYWLPK3H3gFO4-AQvnQ.text: Visited on the second day they were opened. On the recommendation of our server, Vinny, I ordered two different eggs Benedict. 2JTHMJewuoky1dAV-wCYwA.text: My first time going to the Tempe location.  Although I didn't mind waiting outside (it was a beautiful day), the hostess quoted 20-25 minutes of waiting.  Luckily, there's free coffee while you are waiting.  We did not get seated until 45-50 mins.  I would say 4 stars, but minus one due to the inefficient timing.  The food was good and we didn't wait long for it.  I ordered the green chili benedict, which was good.  I am not a fan of their hashbrown style.  it comes in a puck.  I also split the Pancake Flight.  We had the sweet potato, the blueberry and the pineapple upside down.  All of them were delicious.  I'm glad I split them, because they were quite sweet.  I'm glad they made their way down from Denver!  I can definitely see my self going again while it is nice out.

34lhlbOyXsSOIiaVork0ZQ.text: Breakfast pot pie was the best!! 6 friends and I and our pups sat on the patio and they are very dog friendly and even provided water for the dogs!! Love this place and would recommend to anyone who loves good breakfast food!

y7uvbfhbnOFtTK38j1AYLA.text: This is another fantastic Snooze Eatery!!! Heather, Zach (Asst Mgr) and Alec were wonderful!!! There were 5 of us and all of our breakfast was delicious. ASU is fortunate to have a great restaurant right in their midst!

d2pr4i3-vzddEnBU-RhvIg.text: Came here with my boyfriend for brunch while we were in town for a music festival during Halloween weekend. The place came highly recommended, and being such a foodie, I had to check it out. We came in a little later (around 1) after their rush and were seated right away at the community table. The staff was all dressed up in costumes being that it was Halloween which was cute (the bartenders were all characters from Orange is the New Black which I thought was pretty awesome.. it is a major college town after all.) After a long night, the first thing we went to was the cocktails. They had multiple Bloody Mary options which is always a great first impression for us! We tried the Gazpacho (lighter and refreshing spin on a bloody with cucumber) it was good, but the best one has to be the Bangkok! It has fish sauce, cilantro, lime, basil, sriracha, and a spicy, salty rim -- AMAZING! Arguably one of the best bloody's I've ever had and that's really saying something. Onto the food... everything sounded amazing, but we both decided on some benny's (there are a ton of them on the menu and they have an option of a "duo" benny which is nice because you can do one of each.) I ordered the duo of the "benny goodman" and the "bella! bella!" because I couldn't decide, but unfortunately when the food came they were both the goodman, but I didn't complain because 1) I work in the industry and know that's annoying (although they did mess up my order.. I hate to waste food and I know if it's sent back it's thrown out) and 2) it was delicious! I would have liked to try the other one, too, but if that's the worst thing that happened at this place I can live with it. The goodman is like a lox bagel style eggs benedict and it was to die for! My boyfriend got the chilaquiles benedict and really enjoyed that, too, (but he said mine was better). Service was good, but not memorable. Maybe it is different if you are at a table instead of the community, but either way it didn't take away or add anything to the experience. The menu was so great that I want to come back and try everything on it! The best news was when I realized they have a location where I live! New regular brunch spot for sure!  Definitely check it out! And you have to try the Bangkok Bloody Mary and the Benny Goodman. So so good!

wYZV1S719csByka8_Vr8DQ.text: Finally Tempe has a breakfast spot.  Snooze clearly prides itself on being more than just an eatery.  Great food, atmosphere, and SERVICE!  Highly recommend the corned beef hash and danish blueberry pancakes!  Every member of the staff was dancing and smiling, again, truly an enjoyable experience.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Snooze on College

Ft9UWCxGLHoVMRe_CIzebA.text: This was the best food ever! Our server Lolita was super nice. If you plan on eating here be prepared to wait. The wait is totally worth it. They have a good system in place where they text you when your table is ready. We tried the pinapple upside cake and I about melted it was so delicious. I would definitely recommend it.

Uq22y4bKLHeo5nhEEhEFHg.text: Noise is overwhelming, from the clatter of dishes to the conversations and the non-stop blare of hip hop music. Breakfast burrito was good, but was served 10 minutes after my boyfriend had finished his breakfast. Waitress comped the drinks! Very friendly wait staff.

5BG05TRqid0akjCKVy4mcA.text: Pretty disappointed in my visit. I usually go to the location in Phoenix and was excited they opened up a closer store!  Order a 3 egg scramble with bacon and avo. It was SO greasy with so much thick "bacon" in my eggs. It was entirely over powering. The pancake was good but over cooked.  I probably won't go back for a long while after that experience.

snfp4biPvwxOg7ZcmjAwvA.text: So so so good! Best breakfast with a fun environment in Tempe. We have been there multiple times and enjoy it every time. Always enjoy there pancake flights :) so yummy!  There is a long wait if you go on the weekends so plan ahead for that.  Service is always nice and friendly. The even gave us free pancakes once :)

3-wzTipbH4gQfgoVSTuNuQ.text: Delicious food.  Fresh squeezed orange juice and benedicts to die for.  Love the ham benedict, but can't eat all that food so they let me do a half order.  It is always crowded, but I sit at the bar which is just fine.

aOY7DGrC7mVllPNtvlip0A.text: Been meaning to write this since Sunday when we came in, just now getting a chance. I came in with my girlfriend and her sisters for the first time. We heard good things and wanted to try it out. I am not a university kid, I am a community college, rock n roll kid and I couldn't help but to scoff at some of the belligerent college bros stumbling out of some of the locations near by. No big deal, they need to have fun too I suppose! The wait was about 40 minutes, but the weather was nice and they gave us coffee. Some of the staff were nice, some seemed blah, but Kate (gosh I hope that is her name!) behind the bar was serving us and she was an A fucking + server. Best server I have had in probably years. Her suggestions were amazing, her knowledge about the food and drinks was ample and her smile was so contagious. Great service, nice mid century feel, and good food! The food was great, but not amazing (I know it is hard to do that with breakfast food) so Snooze gets 4 stars from me. If I could do 4.5, I would... Just cause the service was so good.

1h6EzTKgjf0CXsf3y9JW2g.text: Super yummy!! Great food, service, and environment.

S8BTG32QdYzYxopgBbAgIQ.text: Had a layover in Phoenix for a few hours and decided to explore the area and grab something good for breakfast. This place is great! Awesome creative take on traditional breakfast items, breakfast cocktails, great indoor and patio seating near ASU campus.

euoa2jDwezlke8mnQjpw3g.text: The food is amazing and the indoor and out seating is good. The prices are a little bit high and the wait is normally long but the food is worth it. If you are in Tempe you need to try this place just make sure you bring change for the meter and bring a friend so they can sign in while you find parking.

TGwVT12uyDXJAAgWT0X1EA.text: Friendly staff and pretty good food.  Gets busy during the school year, so plan for that.

S0G2TWysaPe6DDsY7QHydg.text: Amazing place, food will not disappoint!!! Pancakes are fabulous!!! Every flavor you can imagine!!!! There shouldn't be one bad review, discard those. Oh and if want mimosa or any other coffee liqueur drink they have it!!!!

7lqpoEIgPITEKcAFOrT3sA.text: The food is excellent and the staff is very friendly. There can be a long wait time so I would recommend going in very early on the weekends.

lTyy1wi30mp6Kwt5XPBFYg.text: Good food /friendly staff -I really appreciate that they serve coffee while u wait for your table when they are busy !

eUg2qeq5ohwFh_OGO7s4Gw.text: Well food not bad but good also, take long time and also was cold really cold, friend also have cold food, 5 out of 10, coffee was cold if I want a ice coffee I would ask for it 5 out of 10, us timer service awful, all waiters was on all the tables, is like it to many hands to making a cake, keep asking for service over all 2 out of 10, won't come back

0a1kn6IMOUvzmDiY7pnDBg.text: Snooze is top of the food chain for breakfast. One of the best breakfast places in the country without a doubt. Everyone who works here seems incredibly happy. Wait times get long, so plan out when you intend to come. Aka don't come on a Saturday morning and expect seating right away. Pancake flights are out of this world!!

Nx963ZO_iUWSmFgV0Qng4g.text: Definitely a destination eatery for me in Denver and now in AZ too!  Super cool good food and service.  Price and wait is worth it.

Nu70mvST4RQT0f3k9KcTbg.text: My favorite breakfast restaurant i usually have the huevos rancheros with over medium eggs the the flying pancake are the best great food great service very clean restaurant

w1vK90eGGHwu5M1uVwT5Iw.text: Had brunch today! Was delicious from Bloody Mary to the B.E.A.T sandwich. Service was excellent!! Bobbi was polite and very friendly. There was a brief down pour; which being from Oregon wasn't a real issue but Bobbi insisted on opening an umbrella to keep my party dry.... Thank you Snooze for a wonderful experience...

DxKvRr86dc0z7su8TgTgIA.text: THE BEST GLUTEN FREE PANCAKE I'VE EVER HAD!  Oh my goodness, the large crowd and long wait time didn't matter. Their sweet potato pancake was so amazingly fluffy and flavorful. Kate, my server, was super friendly and brought everything on time.  It was a great experience, I'll be back!

s-UW4onHyejyLhXaK5GMrw.text: Weekends expect a 40-75min wait. Sounds ridiculous which kinda is but TOTALLY worth it! And you get free coffee as you wait. Otherwise come during the week! Suggest hash browns! The pancakes are pretty sugary but really good. Breakfast burrito is HUGE but so good. They are pretty cool about the menu. They will split almost anything for you. I suggest the breakfast tacos!!! And you must try a bloody Mary and their brewmosa!

8y6UPjHbIOL_o_2w-Q15VQ.text: Great service, cool atmosphere, great location right near campus.

Uc-_Me6psDZTbFkZ-516gA.text: Great brunch place, amazing pancakes and mimosa's just a little bit on the expensive side. Very loud with crowd chatter and awesome outdoor patio sitting. Just wish they had a little more shaded areas with umbrellas and they have a very limited menu items. Overall, great place to grab brunch!

iSIzEx_fRwP3O2-9Js6r9g.text: I give the cooks 5 stars for the amazing food.  I am sorry that I had to drop an overall rating because of the mismanaging of table flow.  Over an hour wait, when initially told 30 minutes is a lil off. The free drinks were a nice compensation, but really over an hour???

3txWuR-Kr33fVbZoBbgitw.text: Overrated.   Nothing really special.   Eggs are eggs, pancakes are pancakes, bacon is bacon.   If you want a plain breakfast, you can go anywhere for that, otherwise you are just paying for location and atmosphere.

8xgo06t_dJDTsqlgx_2z3A.text: Solid food, decent wait staff, would def go again.  My omelet was very good, but would go with the breakfast burrito next time!

GOniVvGDBZA2LnBHTLc_aw.text: As someone who lives in the area, and hears about this place all the time, I was super excited to try. However, it was underwhelming. The wait was long, the food was overpriced and frankly, it just wasn't that great. I don't get the hype, definitely overrated.

AwVamj1_YZEAfyyp6zu64g.text: Long wait but boy is it worth it. The service was perfect, the food left my boyfriend and I craving it for weeks. First time we sat on the patio and enjoyed the weather. Perfect spot for a mimosa or bloody Mary and brunch. Second time we waited for an hour and sat near the bathrooms, which awkwardly enough have a bit of a view to the men's room.

F3-EnlXYZmHqLdCRJG08lg.text: Such the perfect afternoon to go. I took my partner here for his first legal drink which of course was a mimosa. It was delicious. And the food was sooooo amazing. I definitely recommend coming here if you like breakfast/brunch food. Good options. Also the pancakes  so sweet and delicious.

ZQ0WvvxdPdAFrlMmSRuXXQ.text: I had previously left a 4 star review so I came back in hopes of another great experience. This visit wasn't so pleasant. While I was seated quickly, I had a very strange food experience and less than stellar service.  I ordered a pancake and when it arrived it was stone cold. I flipped It over to see if it was undercooked or something and It revealed big slash marks in the pancake which put me off the rest of my breakfast. I couldn't wave anyone down because my waiter forgot I was there so by the time I was remembered, it was too late. The waiter explained that the cuts were to make sure it was done?!?! Uh if you have to destroy one side of a thin pancake to determine the doneness, you shouldn't be making them. I made perfect pancakes when I was 10 years old and never had to do that nor any other place I have ever had pancakes had the underside look like that.  On the positive, they did apologize and remove the charge from my bill. I just will refrain from the pancakes at this location going forward and continue to flip them over in the future.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. This is what I discovered on the other side of my pancake.  I will just stick to toast from now on.
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Egg White Frittata. It&#39;s topped with dressed arugula, tomatoes, pepitas, a little manchengo cheese, and some roasted corn. Delicious!

Q1HKmF876y_duXdur69X3A.text: This has to be the coolest place to go get breakfast! I get why the people wait! It's totally worth it! The vibe is .. positive..you can feel nothing but good vibes from everyone in this establishment, the staff and people who are eating and waiting for a table. Everyone is just so flipping relaxed! A great relief from the every day stress! The food.. interesting choices and yummy foods that I've never seen before.. so I decided to try pineapple pancakes.. the dude next to me had a breakfast burrito that was the biggest burrito I've ever seen.. and let me tell you.. I've lived here for a very very very long time and seen my share of breakfast burritos! If we had time to spare we would have waited to see if that guy ate the whole thing, because he said he could., but in good consideration I just couldn't find it in my reasoning to stay and watch.. knowingly that there are other people who are still waiting for a table! This is also a great place for outdoor seating if you have your fur baby! There were plenty of well behaved dogs on the patio! Mine was at doggie daycare having a blast instead:) because I was going to be shopping afterwards! I highly recommend this restaurant! This is definitely the coolest breakfast spot I've ever been in Arizona!

2uL_Z0Shs7XM67l4BFwDVw.text: Yeah just like most Snooze locations, it's really hard to go wrong when dining at one. If you're a fan of brunch and breakfast, then this place is for you.  Pancakes? They got 'em. French Toast? They got that. Other breakfast and brunch stuff...yeah, whatever, they go that too. There's just too much good stuff on the menu.  Just like any other Snooze location, their decor is sleek, colorful and modern...and classy. Well, at least that's how I feel each time I dine. On top of that, I've never had bad service at a Snooze location and this visit was no different. That's pretty good considering that I think the entire staff is probably attending ASU which is literally across the street. Like seriously, across the street. Anyway, the server was very friendly.  "So what did you have, Jeff? I really want to know. That's why I'm reading this review."...said no one ever. However, if you must ask, I had the Drunken Monkey French Toast. Why? Because I love French Toast, and the name was intriguing...and the description sounded good.  Funny story, it was good. The End.  Okay not really the end.  Although the portion size was a little smaller than your typical Jeff S. standards would consider worthy, the fact that it was a nicely arranged dish of carbs in the form of sugar, bread,fruit...and sugar, it was good enough for me to overlook the less than Herculean serving size (i.e., mere mortal serving size). Yeah, the rest of you normal eaters will probably be fine. I'll be sure to include the obligatory picture.  So would I eat here again? I'm pretty sure the answer to that should be pretty obvious, but in case you are fairly dense, the answer is "yes". Why? Because I love the food, the atmosphere and well, breakfast food in general. The only downside is that currently I don't find myself in this part of town that often, but no need to worry, I'm sure at some point in time I'll make my way back and this place will be at the top of my breakfast list.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States

xedLHG7Uqcs34zghFqNqww.text: Me and my girlfriend have become really big on having good breakfast whenever we get a chance to be up early. We came in with the plan of getting some eggs Benedict and some coffee to get our day really moving. The server was great and friendly, we got our coffee while we looked at the menu and found what we wanted. My girlfriend and I both got eggs Benedict with hash browns and it was really delicious, we had been craving eggs Benedict and the way they are done at Snooze is just great. I can't wait to go back! For anyone in town, I would highly recommend trying out snooze in Tempe. Parking is a bit tough to find, but well worth it!

-Jn5tJtavNmy7xbETg7QWQ.text: So many gluten free options, one of the only places I'll go for breakfast. The eggs Benedict and French toast are delightful but super Rich, I recommend splitting foods and trying as many as you can!

3MurYwRl0YX1_dO-wn4oXA.text: Super yummy food! Great atmosphere and music. Friendly and helpful staff. My friend and I sat at the community table and loved it! 10/10 recommend anyone visiting to try this place out!

AfBzZ76kbCYVhvgB-2P2Fg.text: Great place for breakfast and brunch. I like the breakfast burrito as well as the eggs benedict. The lattes are also very yummy and bloody mary's. They have indoor and outdoor seating area. We waited for about 35 min to get a table. It does get very very busy in the morning so i recommend planning ahead.  They do close at 230pm so make sure you make it before. Highly recommend!

bjDdjQZYCnt25FjKbGvWug.text: I was in Phoenix for a holiday and tried their OMG French toast.. Loved it.. It was so good

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States

K6k2yXJUr5zu6d0bjfT2-A.text: I finally decided to stop in and have breakfast here on a Sunday. I was not surprised by the wait and line once I arrived. I knew that this location is ALWAYS busy. Surprisingly, I got a table within ten minutes of checking in with my husband. Yay! Once we arrived at our table our waitress came to take our drink and breakfast order. Minutes later...our food was already delivered at our table. Talk about FAST! Our food came out so delicious. So delicious that I don't want to order anything else on the menu because I already fell in love with the first item I tried. I recommend coming early because they don't take reservations in advance, they're kind of a first come first serve type of restaurant. They're dog friendly. So, come and bring your pooches! If you're unable to find parking, the best option is to park at the nearby parking garage. Not many restaurants offer military discounts, but this Snooze location does!

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States

3p5KENa0baQcOaDZL40kSw.text: The food was just amazing.  Everything was fresh and tasty.  The coffee was top notch.  Our server was friendly, prompt, and courteous.  I can't believe this was the first time there and we cannot wait to go back.  They allowed us to split a breakfast meal and even put it on separate plates for us.  We each had a different Benedict and I will say the Elote Benedict is as incredible as it it unique.  We split a pineapple upside down pancake for dessert and loved every bite.

ERPKpJBGxxMhc2XcAu3JeA.text: Really good, high quality food. It is one of my favorite spots for breakfast! I have been here a few times and they never disappoint. The ambience of the restaurant is very hip and open. Others too like this place, so there usually is a long wait on the weekends-we went on a Monday afternoon and there was no wait and plenty of space for our big party.   I had the Breakfast pot pie, with a side of hashbrowns. Everything on the plate was delicious, it is a dish I have not seen anywhere else. If you haven't been here or are a regular, it is something to try on their menu. The portions seemed rather hearty, so come hungry; if not, sharing is always an option.!

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Breakfast pot pie is a must

H8j_veWCzeyCvS7EtLfa5g.text: A great hipster breakfast spot with friendly service, delicious hash-browns, and a no-frills atmosphere.  The service was excellent and the waitress was attentive. She was pleasant, fun, and on top of refills!  As for the food, this is one of the few places I've been to that cooked perfect over-easy eggs. No burnt edges, and an oozing yolk that was perfect for mixing in the fantastically seasoned hash-browns, or to dip the toast in.  The only thing that kept this from being a 5 star was the chicken sausage. It just didn't have that breakfast sausage flavor. While it may seem silly to say that chicken should taste more "sausage" and less like chicken; for chicken breakfast sausage, this should be the case. Whatever seasoning they use really brings out the flavor of the chicken and doesn't make it taste like a breakfast sausage alternative. Maybe more thyme and sage was In order?  Despite the chicken sausage, I would definitely come back. One gripe is overshadowed by the fantastic service and mouth-watering hash-browns. Plus, they can cook eggs like champs!

vr5PpLnc-szOxeq0J0Au0Q.text: Reviews didn't lie this place is awesome!! Eggs benny chili verde with Barbacoa beef was fabulous. Great atmosphere and energizing vibe. Don't miss it if your near Univ Arizona campus.

Z8lRaOoJt9puc6aFjjzFvA.text: Let me start off by saying that I don't like writing negative reviews. The customer service was on point, our server Sophie was wonderful! The atmosphere was also nice. The food however fell flat for me. After waiting quite a while (which I was willing to overlook since it was so busy) when our food came, it was flavorless. I ordered the breakfast taco and the eggs Benedict, and my son ordered chocolate chip pancakes. My breakfast taco was just okay, but the Benedict not only had an eggshell in it but the flavor combination was off. My son's pancakes were burnt and also didn't have any flavor. I was really looking forward to eating here after seeing the wonderful reviews. Maybe I'll go back to give it another shot?

La_4n6v1MeOz1190wNPXSA.text: Best breakfast I have ever had! I just wish they would open up on the East Coast! Will definitely go back the next time I'm in Phoenix!

STP7bx7wezVDiDNUf7d4eg.text: I love this place and have been to the 2 San Diego locations.  This was my first time at this one but it might as well have been at any of them.    Excellent service, really attentive.  Food was great and came out fast.  My "over light" eggs were cooked to perfection and my order of "not crispy" bacon was just right.  Solid good coffee and real cream (maybe half and half).    I sat inside but the patio looked nice and had misters.  If you've never been to a Snooze, go, you won't be sorry.

A6u_AFaaDNK_v-BQwPahBA.text: I recently moved to Tempe from Minnesota  and I cant believe I hadn't come here until now!! The food was absolutely delicious and our server Alex (the one with a beard and man-bun) was so welcoming and knowledgeable about the menu.

fFfYsMh7fdk8n6ZXxgvD5g.text: One of the best breakfast spots in the east valley! It's ALWAYS packed and they don't take reservations. However, since the location is downtown you can easily pass the time at the farmers market on weekends or walk around and look at the cuteness of downtown. They will text you when your table is ready. The lattes and mochas are excellent, breakfast tacos (with flour tortillas, the corn falls apart easily) and all their pancakes are out of this world. Try the pancake flight so you can choose 3 different pancakes to try at once! You have to try this place at least once in your life!

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Pancake flight
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Breakfast tacos with added avocado, grilled onions and garlic

zZbJJPb2M7nNN5kRG5EsXg.text: WOW I can honestly say I'm blown away with the top notch quality of food and service here at Snooze! From the second you walk in the front door you are embraced in such a friendly and inviting atmosphere that feels like a good old fashion dinner meets a modern classy space vibe! The food here is  just genius! Literally whoever is the chef behind this masterpiece of a menu is a modern day Einstein in the kitchen! Let me start with the steak & eggs Benny!!! Literally heaven! It's seared steak medallions atop roasted poblano cheddar grit cakes with asparagus, roasted mushrooms and tomatoe topped with poached Cage free eggs with a smoked cheddar hollandaise and gemolata..... words can't describe the amount of perfection with the balance of flavors and the steak is insanely flavorful and delicious! Now onto the pancakes!!! BEST PANCAKES IVE EVER HAD! Ask about the pancake of the day it's different everyday! Today it was vanilla batter with white chocolate chips, ganache, spiced ginger chips, granola, and sprinkled in powder sugar my waitress Kate was soooooooo sweet and adorable and she just made what was already and Amazing experience into a perfect one! I am here visiting from California but will be back every morning I'm here visiting! Love this place to pieces

AWQKWaNj90Wfhqvxe2Us3Q.text: One of the best breakfast experiences I have had!    After a bit of a wait on a busy Super Bowl Sunday morning, we were fortunate to be able to grab some seats at the bar.  While you're waiting, be sure to grab a complementary cup of Snooze's smooth blend of java!  The bartender was quick to wipe down the bar area in front of us and provide us with menus and placesettings!  Then we got down to business and ordered up the Steak and Eggs Benny and a trip of pancakes that included pineapple upside down cake, cannoli cream, and the pancake of the day - a blueberry mocha concoction!  The Steak and Eggs Benny was THE BEST benny I've ever had!  Just WOW!  I could eat that every single day!  Benny perfection!  And the pancakes were all deliciously as well... but that Blueberry Mocha POTD was a heavenly flapjack that was light, fluffy, not too sweet and an incredible example of pancakery-ness at its finest!  Top-notch service, creative culinary delights, and a cool environment will bring me back every time!  Can't wait to go back for that benny!!  *****FIVE STARS*****

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Drink menu!!
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Pancake heaven!!  Cannoli, pancake of the day, pineapple upside down!
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Steak and eggs benny!!

06peFNt53MKhX0XPR1qC3g.text: I was snoozin' this past Sunday morning when my bf mentioned that he wanted to go to Snooze...man, I'd never gotten up and ready so fast since we've been together!!  Our wait time would've been around 30 min had we not scored 2 super cool looking seats at the bar after roughly 15 min of being there. How can anyone complain about wait times when they give u FREE fresh brewed coffee while u wait?!?!  I can't remember the last time I had a steak & eggs benny, but it sure didn't taste as divine as this one did at Snooze! I could taste the caged-freeness of my chick with every bite!! The combination of eggs on steak was just bursting with so much flavor that there was never a boring bite!   The pancake flight was the perfect ending to our breakfast of perfection. The pineapple turnover was my least favorite of the three. The sweet cannoli & the pancake of the day (blueberry mocha with a splash of nirvana) were definitely my favs!! I suggest you don't inhale them all in one sitting as eating half will satisfy even the most sweetest of tooth cravings.  Get yourself to one of their locations quick!! Don't snooze on Snooze!!!

-_od8ENKmU54wLIpRb-5MA.text: So this location is on the college campus and not the best snooze we have ever been too. Parking is downtown parking, metered and multiple spots available. Maybe not close to the location depending on the time of day. The food was okay but the service was on the slow side. I came on a Saturday morning at 7:30 AM with two little kids in tow; the kids pancakes took about 20 minutes to come out as did my omelette despite being one of only six tables there at that time in the morning. By the time the food did come out, it was a tad on the cooler side. However dining with 2 kids under the age of 7, we just ate it as the kids were getting restless. It looked like they were training a few new people so I don't know if that was the cause for delay? Overall the food was okay but not as good as it has been at other snooze locations.  We would come back but we would probably go to the other location in Kierland. They have adequate seating indoor and outdoors. They have a full bar as well for those wanting a drink.

rhf5EJ7_YnX3xOez3PnYLQ.text: Finally made it to Snooze!  Even if it is in a different state.  Husband and I flew into Sky Harbor and it was along our route to visit some friends.  It was easy to find parking at a meter right across the street and we didn't even have to feed quarters into the meter since it was before the time they started charging.  The wait was about 30 minutes on a Saturday morning and they got us in and out in a little over an hour, including the wait.  We were not only impressed by the service, but the food was worth waiting for.    I opted for the flight of pancakes - an indecisive person's dream - with a pumpkin pancake, blueberry lemon, and pineapple upside down.  All were good, but the pineapple may have been one of the best pancakes I have ever had.  Husband had the Snooze Spuds Deluxe, which was basically like a skillet with potatoes, two sides (i.e. bacon, sausage, ham),  cheese and eggs.  It was a solid choice as well.    I can't wait to try Snooze in CA!  Since all of their locations utilize local goods, I'm hoping each is a little bit different.

hnZo74KN8K1LR2h8mBRuCg.text: I am normally in charge of finding restaurants, but my wife discovered Snooze on Yelp and just had to give it a try.    We arrived last Friday around noon to a very, very busy dining area.  The hostess took our cell number and advised they will text when our table was ready.  Was supposed to be a 25 minute wait, but they texted within ten minutes.  Our order was taken quickly: a pancake flight, chicken sausage, and a chai tea for my wife.  French toast, chicken sausage, and hash browns for me.  A "Sandwich I Am" (soft pretzel roll filled with scrambled eggs, cheddar cheese and a sausage patty, served with a side of smoked cheddar hollandaise), and a hash brown for my son.  My wife's pancake flight (chocolate peanut butter, pineapple upside down, and the flavor of the day) was fantastic.  She wasn't a huge fan of the chicken sausage, but loved her chai.  My son loved his "Sandwich I Am" and thought the hash brown puck - see photos - was just okay.  My French toast was perfect, I liked the chicken sausage, and the hash brown puck was not the best, but I still managed to finish it.  The hash browns just need a little something else to make it great... so close.  A little cheese, and some onion powder perhaps.  Our waitress, Abbie, was fantastic.  The atmosphere was great.  Volume/noise was acceptable.  The interior decor was gorgeous - very bright with lots of vibrant colors.  Location was great as it was next to "A Mountain".  Very good experience - would return when in the area again.

juwQMIlOLgIFLTFIdOwcgw.text: Snooze has such a cute bright and friendly atmosphere. It's a great place to meet up with friends in the morning, whether it be to catch up after a long night of partying, or for a post hike meal. Just know that if you plan on stopping by during the weekend after a morning work out, make sure you get there early enough to avoid the crowd so that you can get your protein in asap. If you come later in the morning, you will be sure to find yourself a line.  What's cool is that they take your cell number and text you when your table is ready, so you don't have to worry about staying too close. They have a coffee bar in the front for those waiting, as well as corn hole in the patio to keep people entertained.  They have a nice selection of foods on their menu. So far my favorite has been their OMG French Toast.

8Ddxcj1cUpG8Nlv-vWtRAw.text: Went there this morning before we had to rush to the PHX airport to catch our flight.  Was about 945a on a Tue morning.  It was only about 1/2 full as we were seated outside.  We waited a good 10-15 min before we had to ask a waiter to get some service.  We saw at least 2 other tables that came after us that were served before us.  Anyway, the waiter apologized and offered to give each of us a free pancake.  Overall, the service was good once you can get their attention.  Keep in mind, the place is only 1/2 full, and there were plenty of servers walking around, so I'm not sure what the excuse would be.    Food wise, my friend got the omelet and I got the hash beef.  As these are simple breakfast items, it's really hard to mess them up.  I think it's because we were short on time, the speed of the service was certainly lacking.  By the time we got our bill, we had to wait another 5 min before our bill was pick up by our waiter.  Granted, we probably should have told him in advance that we were limited on time, but the fact the place is not that busy, we didn't think it would matter.   Bottom line is that the service was good indeed, just the speed of the service could have been better.  As for the taste of food, it's just the basic taste of breakfast, nothing unique to say this is the place I have to come back next time.

1F-g05AmfORpTSqZQbH8Ag.text: I had never been to Phoenix before and I tried Snooze for breakfast. A great menu with vegetarian options. Outdoor seating, trendy atmosphere near college. Service was friendly, food great and the special mimosa hit the spot !

2skbpT7R8DCTOoAvqcX7WQ.text: As you drive down the street to Snooze AM, not many places appear busy, except this place. It was packed, many standing around the hostess stand waiting for their text that their table is ready. Love the text idea and great they don't spam you with ads and such afterwards. We waited quite a bit to sit, longer than they quoted, but they are super friendly and have water and coffee out and offered to you as you wait, worth it!  The atmosphere and decorating are great, super modern, progressive and clean, bright and fun. The service was extremely friendly, from the host/hostess, wait staff and bussers.  The menu is enormous and everything sounds amazing. Ingredients are fresh, local, highest quality and dishes are creative, full of unique flavor and extremely well presented. Everything we had was absolutely delicious. We ordered way too much food because everything sounded phenomenal, and it was! Prices are a little high, but well worth it, really.  It's not close for me to go, but absolutely worth it. The pairing of excellent service, stellar, fresh, balanced, tasty, unique food, good value, and a really fun, bright, clean, active atmosphere make this a fantastic breakfast choice on any given day. Go, enjoy, you'll be glad you did!

IVq8eUIQ2BT2IH99RbBbCQ.text: Food is good. Mimosas are flat and the service is slow. The atmosphere is great. I would come back to try their pancakes. They looked really good. My husband had the BEAT sandwich and he loved it. I had the late harvest and it was ok. I wouldn't get that dish again. Overall I wasn't amazed with this place but I would give them a second chance.

RIpsFGgdqiujoOloSueSzw.text: OMG!! This place is amazing!! First, the service is fantastic.  Our server was so nice and since it was our first time in, she gave us a pancake sample to try.  The food is delicious.  And there's so much of it!  The breakfast burrito is huge- could easily feed two people.  The eggs Benedict was a smaller portion, but really tasty, and you can mix and match from their options.  I wish I could come here every day!

IdT95LPHokK0LqHNJcI6fg.text: I fell in love with Snooze as soon as it opened its Biltmore location, so I was over the moon when they came to Tempe! This location is just as good as its Phoenix sibling, and the wait was not as long. My group of five arrived at 9 am, and we were immediately seated. I guess all the college kids were still in bed. You snooze, you lose! LOL. The place had a considerable line by the time we left around 10:30 am. The menu is solid; pancakes, eggs benedict, and breakfast sandwiches that will blow your mind. This is my favorite morning restaurant, and I can't wait for the Gilbert spot to open!!!

sulU7P4JnmhvwRbL-boLfw.text: Great menu selection for food and drinks. Nice patio. Quality restaurant and innovative when compared to many of the other local restaurant choices.

Dx6RPJmTa9KkSIv8X5v4Og.text: First time here, and the place is fantastic.  Very nice, open, bright interior.  The staff is great. And the Peter Paul Rubens sandwich is fantastic!

SIguUfh64SMxb4RRXK5ZQw.text: Best pancakes as we tried the blueberry Danish pancakes and the banana french toast!  Not to mention best service from Lolita!!

wH-mCTptR7y7OwfgHjaGIg.text: Decor is adorable, food is ok. I don't feel like the quality of food matches the prices. My French toast was a little on the soggy side.

cNpt-_HLBmGsHDk5ps9Rkg.text: Hmm...trying to understand all of the 5 star reviews. I definitely need to give this place another try, I think. We came in late this morning (ok fine it was closer to noon) for some brunch. The place was hoppin' and we were told there was a 30-45 minute wait. We grabbed some coffee at the complimentary station (a plus!) and took a seat to wait. After about 15 minutes the hostess offered up 2 spots at the "communal" table to anyone who wanted to take it, so we snatched it up!  It took quite awhile to get a waitress over for our drink orders, and this lady was NOT happy. Couldn't crack a smile to even fake it. So that was a bummer. After about 20 minutes, the food came out. The food was pretty good, I'm missing where all of the rave food reviews are coming from, but I don't doubt that other items on the menu are fabulous. I got the eggs benedict (one traditional style and the other "Bunny! Bunny! Benni" I believe it was called, which had shaved prosciutto, arugula, balsamic...I was not blown away by any of it. The hash brown cake that came with it was kind of bland and a bit under-cooked. My fiance (!) had the breakfast burrito. It was gigantic and he devoured every bite and loved it. Will try again, order something else, and hope for a server who can muster up a smile :)

Bq8G8tT3YAggIwaayFhvdw.text: Visiting from WA. Was told our wait would be about 20 minutes. Took my number so they could text me when we they were ready, which was really nice. Wait wound up only being 10 minutes! :) Great service and the food was super tasty! Kiddos both got an assorted pancake platter, ones favorite was the pineapple upside down and the others was the chocolate molten. Tasty bacon and hash browns on the side, with perfectly cooked eggs. I had the corned beef hash and my daughter kept stealing it! Good coffee and great size! The kids want to go again tomorrow and I agree! :)
