xMYHH5Qj4sQ-rZFmW_Z5aQ.text: We came here for a Sunday brunch and decided to share something sweet apart to having our Benedict eggs. We wanted pancakes but then something on the menu called our attention: the O.M.G. French toasts. We decided to give it a try, admittedly a bit skeptical. We were blown away and we were constantly mumbling "Oh My God! this is amazing"! We had to come again the next day before leaving Phoenix back home. This time I wanted the full order for myself so I didn't  have to share it!   I would give it 5 stars because of the OMG French toasts, the Benedicts were great and tasty. The MMM mimosa was great too. The service is great and friendly. However, my only complaint was that I ordered an OJ and asked the waiter whether it was freshly squeezed OJ, he said that it was, but when I tried it, it tasted like tropicana orange juice, which is good but not what I wanted or had in mind. Other than that it is the perfect place for your breakfast and brunch cravings.

WM5Nd0m30BIuGzUoTYy2Dw.text: First time here - followed the Yelp reviews and wasn't disappointed. Highly recommend - will be back.

apsZbPTC3WJlVhNCfbWMGQ.text: Ok. There are really good breakfast places and then there is Snooze. Fresh is the operative word. Had the breakfast tacos. Add some veggies. The roasted jalapeno pepper is great.

xbWTWgoIyWbjZkivSQYaEA.text: If you want a below average meal, this is the place for you! I ordered the standard ham Benedict. The whole meal was cold. The English muffin was rubbery. The ham was super dry. The poached eggs were overcooked. The hollandaise sauce wasn't enough to even cover one of the sides of the dish, and it was nearly flavorless. The hash browns were bland and undercooked, and definitely came from the freezer. What a disappointment. I can only suppose that this restaurant has so many good reviews because the majority of people there were college students who may not quite yet know what good food is supposed to taste like! Two stars instead of one because the waitress was awesome.

ptd0fGMbqEqcReScp_Fxmg.text: Creative and satisfying breakfast. Menu covers the spectrum. Really comfortable atmosphere. Get here early on a Sunday morning.

I didn't realize it when I found them on yelp, but was delighted to find out that this place also has locations in SanDiego, and was the same place I had raved to my friends and family about when I got back from visiting there. kwKUGQJnGsbTdZgFIe6otw.text: Great atmosphere and service.  Not too busy mid-morning on a Friday.  I opted for a "lighter" breakfast with the egg white scramble and was not disappointed!

The entire dish was grossly unsalted making the entire dish bland. And the plate it was on was tiny so I couldn't even cut my food properly without food falling off my plate. MQdQ3Dru1MzVwALlqJQkMQ.text: One of my favorite places to get breakfast food near ASU's Tempe campus! It's often a long wait to get in, but I think the food is worth it. There are so many great options I recommend the BEAT sandwich, Eggs Benedict, and pancakes with a side of bacon/sausage and I always leave here pretty content. While getting noticed/seated can be a bit of a hassle at times, service is otherwise spot-on. Sometimes the servers are really nice and give you some random pancakes on the house, too. My star off is due to to-go service and the drinks. It's honestly annoying that they don't have plastic utensils here for to-go orders. Of all things to not have! Sometimes servers say they'll bring utensils but never do, which has led me to be 99.9% sure they don't have them. Also, the drinks here, non-alcoholic and alcoholic, are not amazing, not to mention pricey. I suggest just getting water and spending your drink money on some sides (i.e. breakfast meats, fresh fruit, etc.) instead.

O8Lmd7SMd91iKvbVN-dnJg.text: This on campus breakfast restaurant was so casual and fun! The staff looked to be all students but they were all super friendly. Even when I snuck away from my group to pay the bill (of course my family is one of those who won't let you pay if they see the bill first) and couldn't find my waitress, but I was able to find another waitress who said she would get my card to the right girl, and she did! So awesome! The food was delicious and fresh, our waitress topped our coffee cups off often, we couldn't have asked for anything better :)

bp_CILd-X7GXKSWbc83Msw.text: Hands down, my favorite breakfast spot.  When you walk in you will notice a fun light atmosphere. The decor is bright and clean, the staff is friendly and appears to really enjoy their job. The menu has enough selection without being overwhelming. p88F3YSeHZ9JCdOl8tmRiQ.text: One the best breakfasts I've had. The service was great; everyone was helping out each other so a drink was never empty! Lizzie was great in offering advice and seemed very knowledgeable on the menu. She was also very honest on her suggestions which I appreciate. I hate the "everything on the menu is awesome" response.  I had a half order of the corned beef hash and the half and half eggs Benedict. You're able to order two Benedict's which was perfect for me. The steak and eggs benny is by far the best thing I ate. Perfect seasoning, texture and the steak was cooked perfect! Also got the avocado smash Benny which was also delicious. My wife got a giant burrito smothered in green chili and loved it. My kids both got the French toast house and cleaned their plates. This is our new favorite spot!!

AgLI2sJttIWbthIcfhlrMg.text: Awesome breakfast/brunch place. This restaurant concept is really picking up in the Tempe-Scottsdale region with every place offering something a little unique and different. My favorite thing on the menu at Snooze is Juan's breakfast tacos. Three tacos with sturdy tortillas that don't crumble after the first bite.   The atmosphere is so relaxed and fun. They have yard games to play while waiting for a table or if you'd like to hangout and drink mimosas all morning.   Plan ahead if you are coming on a weekend. They don't take reservations as is the standard in Tempe; and the wait can get up over 2 hours! Have patience because the food will be worth the wait!

AnmOsFS6fkh5SHdrQP2ykA.text: This place is amazing! I don't typically like pancakes but thought I would give the blackberry double stack a shot & I'm glad I did! The staff was over the top nice & incredibly welcoming & the environment is very hip. Definitely a must visit if in the Phoenix area! A++

2SVBeg9NS4cxXxgmcpbGxw.text: Talk about a perfect breakfast restaurant!?! This is it!  Options, quality, creativity!  They have it all!  Service was also quite good!  Only challenge is that it gets so busy, it can be a little loud!

yN5g7RBHGsj0HVJLjxZUAQ.text: I love this place. Sincerely. The staff is so wonderful and helpful with everything. It may seem a little pricey, but that food is so worth it. You can tell they know what they are doing when it comes to breakfast food. Also recommend getting their coffee here!

zqCgp3EQjuIDZ6SOLlot2w.text: I've been to the one in San Diego and this location was just as great. Service was great as they are well staffed. There's always a line but it goes by fairly quickly especially if you have a group of 4 or less. I like how the menu is slightly different at each location so it's definitely worth checking out different locations. I generally stuck with the egg benedicts. They're super delicious. Although, I wish their portions were a little bit bigger or decrease the prices since each plate rarely ever fills me up compared to other brunch places I've been. Nonetheless, I definitely recommend Snooze if you haven't tried it yet.

j5u527hQw1qaKnBOvNh48g.text: I wanted pancakes but I also wanted Eggs Benedict. You see, this is the problem when you travel by yourself. You can't get two plates and share. Well, you *can* still get two plates but then you're just being a pig.  Since I was so indecisive today, I got a "Benny Duo" where you can have one Benedict of one type and one of another. The first was with smoked salmon on a slice of pumpernickel. Tasty and excellent. The egg was perfect. The second was with green chile and a potato base of some sort. Also excellent. The chile had a little bit of a zing to it and it improved with a bit of Cholula.  Service was excellent, sitting at the breakfast counter. Coffee was refilled and it was good coffee.

2NBCjpg1l3SKpBT_mSXjPg.text: Soooooo upset that you took away the Benny Goodman  The absolute best thing on your menu...please bring back or I'll keep hitting snooze on Snooze

xm1mRflnRcAifbhKUDJAjw.text: A group of 4 of us went here for brunch on a Saturday. It was BUSY. The hostess estimated a 20-30 min wait. We were hungry so we were hoping it would be closer to 20 min. The waiting area inside is small and there were a lot of people waiting. Outside, there's a bench but that's pretty much it. It ended up taking closer to 45 min for us to be seated, unfortunately. While we were waiting though, we looked over the menu so we would be ready to order asap.  I got the Snooze Spuds Deluxe because I love potatoes. The 2 Flavor Saveurs (included in the price) I chose were bacon and caramelized onions. I didn't feel like the onions added much and I normally love caramelized onions. Next time, I would just get 2 meats...probably bacon and chicken sausage. The 4 of us all got different dishes (can't remember what everyone got) and we all really liked it!  When it came time for the bill, our server brought out a device that would let us split the bill and pay it ourselves. You just select which items you want to pay for and swipe/insert your card, and pass it along to the next person. Super simple and really useful and practical for groups. It seemed like this was something new they were trying out because our server asked for our feedback with using it.  We all enjoyed Snooze and I would come back, but probably only during a less busy/popular time just so I wouldn't have to wait as long.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Snooze Spuds Deluxe with bacon and caramelized onions and 2 poached eggs on top

a1kMbsUsh0YSt0ewtX3u5g.text: I've been often (probably too much) to the Gilbert location, so I thought that I'd give this place a try as I was in the area on a recent Saturday morning.  Identical menu to other locations, which is a good thing. Extremely tasty breakfast food. Fun staff. Cool decor. Nice that it's open so early (6:30am) for the early birds.  Outstanding bacon.  I'll strongly considering returning.

kA6PGmBBDObgFX6bOapE7A.text: Super cute brekkie place, and I really appreciate their sustainable practices.  I went on a Friday around 8:45am, and there was no wait. I sat at some bar height tables facing the street (the perfect place to people watch / read a book.  I got the Snooze Spuds Deluxe (poblano peppers + chicken sausage add ons and sunny side up eggs on hashbrowns). It wasn't anything phenomenal, but tasty nevertheless. The portions weren't very big, but I probably won't get this again because it's pretty cut and dry.   I'll probably swing by again and I'll try out the pancakes / french toast. Very accessible from ASU, and some nice places to venture around for a post-meal walk. Also, they have a digital payment system where you can pay via card when they bring you the check, which I thought was very cool.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Snooze Spuds Deluxe w poblano peppers and chicken sausage

1LThxph1o5CxBzOuHbEW7A.text: A gladdening proclamation for this Saturday morning: I am a fan of Snooze.   What has changed? Change comes only from within, so I've been told. Thus, I have implemented the following which have rendered Snooze more favorable in my sight.   (1) My last three visits have all been early-- 6:45 AM, 7:45 AM, and 8:30 AM respectively. In all cases, seating has been quick, service has been good, and food has been excellent.   Previously, I attempted to come for breakfast at 9:00 AM or later, and to me, that is just not worth it. The wait can reach an hour or longer, the service is inevitably slower, and the food -- again, by my observations -- does not compare to the early-morning harvest.   (2) I've changed up the orders! In my last three visits, I have ordered the sweet potato hash, Goldilocks' porridge, and, this morning, more sweet potato hash. These "Light as a Feather" dishes, though lower in calories, are certainly not lower in quality, flavor, or even presentation. They are creative, delicious meals that treat the appetite without a sliver of guilt or jab to the wallet.   Previously, my orders were sauce-heavy: oh Benny, how I wanted to like you. My girlfriend's order of the pot pie was gravy with a side of pot pie -- just didn't do it for us. Maybe these styles are appealing for others, but going forward, we'll stick to what we know.   ~  I am always pleased to have my mind changed, and I say that Snooze has captured my approval and gratitude. Look at their accolades; clearly they have been making the right moves. From myself and all in my company, we recommend Snooze highly, and as previously insisted -- just get there early.

-N-xiy40H7n9bYeFFENSoA.text: I love Snooze. They are really committed to sustainability and do a lot of little things like composting their food waste that add up.   I stopped in for a quick breakfast. Eating a full order of eggs Benedict makes me feel like a whale so I just got a half order of the smashed avocado Benny--they are really accommodating of special orders. I had a moment of hesitation when I was ordering--cheddar hollandaise did not sound good. Should have listened to my gut. It wasn't for me. But that's Snooze. They combine big flavors. Sometimes it works, sometimes it's a hard no. I'm kind of a traditionalist.    Everything else was great, as always. They change the menu four times a year--it just takes time to find new favorites.

HxdWTW1lu2si5iMZukTngA.text: Refreshing spot. Service was fast and super friendly. Menu items were awesome. Huge menu with so many options. Yummy pancakes galore! I can't wait to go back.  We tried this for breakfast after a college tour since it was right across the street and a student recommended it to us. We definitely were not disappointed!   Some standouts: -Ooo La La Frittata (egg whites with asparagus & mushroom salad & topped with arugula) -Sandwich I Am (pretzel roll with eggs and sausage) -Peanut Butter Cup Pancake (!!!) -Havana Daydreaming (pork belly, ham & Swiss on a ciabatta roll with Dijon & hollandaise) -Shrimp & Grits (with just the right amount of kick) -Hash browns were also tasty  I see that there are many Snooze restaurants across four states so we will definitely try another location and hope it is as good as this experience was for us.

The ambiance of the restaurant is sooo cute. The service is pretty good both from my last two visits.. I feel like all the food is hella good. I also love how it's superrrr close to campus, so I can always come here before class hehe.   I have yet to try their mimosas but shoot I hope their mimosas me hella drunk, Lol.

8oAl8kCiUg7uF-_5YiNygg.text: Please don't sleep on Snooze! I was in Phoenix for work and needed to find a great Bloody Mary! I found more than that at this gem located near the ASU campus. The interior is just the cutest! There is a bar as well as a high top table along the windows that are open seating. I opted for the patio considering it was such a great day!  My server was amazingly sweet and didn't judge me for ordering the Horse and Sidecar, Bloody Mary accompanied with a can of beer! I also ordered the shrimp and grits. It was good. I would've liked the grits to be a bit creamier. But the flavor of the sausage and shrimp made up for it. I can't wait to visit again and try a different menu item!

RmLnIacun1K-KatuGYF4-A.text: Visited here for brunch and wasn't disappointed.  Everything was very fresh and the menu was well thought out with a ton of amazing options.  Their eggs Benedict selection was my favorite part of the menu because you can tell a lot of thought went into the different flavor combination.  Also as you can see from my picture you can order a duo if you cant pick just 1, which is awesome.    The staff was also very attentative and friendly. ewC82LjqECxjorwtMkNM8g.text: I wish I lived in Phoenix so that I could eat at Snooze EVERY. SINGLE. WEEKEND.  We arrived with a group of 6 around 10 AM, which is ill-advised --- they don't take reservations, and by then, the wait was around an hour for a group of our size. I appreciate that they'll text you when your table is ready, so you're able to walk around while you wait. We picked up coffee at another local shop and wandered a bit until we received a text about 10-15 min earlier than we had been promised.   The atmosphere feels a bit 50's diner, and we were seated in an oversized booth. Our waitress was friendly and super helpful, and our food came out pretty quickly. We also enjoyed the background music choice, and I definitely may have exchanged some glances with waitstaff who were dancing to the same songs I was.  There were a variety of fresh, breakfast-y spins on classic cocktails. I enjoyed their mojito, which adds green tea to the mix. If I ever go back, I want to try their Bacon and Eggs cocktail with bacon-infused bourbon.  The food menu offers a wide variety of unique dishes, and we all struggled to decide what we wanted. I appreciated the many options to customize your dish --- you could choose two different Eggs Benedict options to mix and match or swap out your hashbrowns for a pancake of your choosing if you (like me) struggle to decide between sweet and savory brunch. I chose to get one Avocado and one Lox-and-Latke benedict (smoked salmon with a latke instead of an English muffin) and loved every bite. I did like the Avocado benny slightly better. Others at the table ordered the Breakfast Pot Pie, which was essentially eggs and breakfast sausage gravy over puff pastry and seemed to be enjoyed. We also tried the coco-nana pancakes (coconut, banana, chocolate, white choc chips) and the pineapple upside-down pancakes, which were phenomenal. I loved every bite of every dish.   I hope I have an excuse to venture back to Phoenix and eat here again.

oj_KNIbNb6Ve-Tl_tgilwQ.text: I've been visiting Snooze AM for awhile now and I'm ready to write a review. I will say this, sometimes I get a four star experience (food is good and service is helpful and prompt) while during other visits the experience is one star or less (food is good but service is horrible [non existent] and very slow).  When I visit during the week, the service is great. The servers are helpful and I always have water in my glass (a marker of good service). The food is also usually very prompt. During the weekends, the servers are friendly (when they are there) but they don't come back and sometimes mix up your order.  All in all, the food is always reliably good and often very rich. However, the service can be good or bad depending on the day of the week. I suggest going during the week when there are less people while during the weekend there are long waits and spotty service.  For lack of constituency of experience, I give two stars.  Things I've had: 3 Eggs Any Style (Made my order perfect) Breakfast Pot Pie (very very very rich, lots of cream) Snooze Breakfast Burrito (my favorite, large burrito and the flavor is very universally appealing) Green Eggs 'n Hamwich (Delicious) Sister Fig's French Toast (too sweet) Fall Greens (lovely light meal) House Coffee (not strong coffee) Choice Mimosa(for me YES!)

jrX4LvOlkBhb1fOydgolzA.text: Sorry Colorado- the best Snooze location is in Tempe!  I've been to four different locations, including Denver- and the Tempe location crushes all the rest. The building is just beautiful- a ton of thought and money went into making such a comfortable, bright, and airy restaurant. We all know mornings can be rough- so why not have breakfast at an amazing place?  Snooze Tempe is home to some of the best restaurants professionals I've ever encountered. In the last two visits- Flip & Starchild were amazing servers. Friendly and helpful- and just totally on point. Today I was having s friendly debate with my sister and her friend. They had never had the pineapple upside down pineapple pancake- so I was trying to tell them how epic it was. Starchild helped us settle this debate by bringing out a pineapple pancake which was just delicious.   In closing- this place is wonderful. There WILL be a line on the weekends. Just know that in advance. Craig breakfast spots don't have a line- do if you can't wait for amazing food and greet service- just hit up the nearest Denny's and let your taste buds become depressed. Otherwise check out Tempe Snooze and start your day out in the best possible way.

hNxwu9UF-3hXc-AkoufXWg.text: I'm not totally getting the hype here. However, it is tasty enough and worth a visit.   The food: Everyone in my party ordered different types of eggs Benedict. I think between the three of us we tried every single flavor. They were all delicious! The salmon one... was a little weird and I would not recommend it. I felt the menu was a little misleading in that the salmon wasn't pieces but more of a salmon patty.  The hashbrowns were extremely salty but I'll write more about that below.   The drinks: YUM (and affordable!). I ordered a straight up bloody mary with an added strip of bacon for an extra $1.25. I wouldn't recommend adding that extra slice of bacon but the drink was overall tasty.   The service: The service was what made me bump this review from 3 to 4 stars. We were told the wait would be 15 mins but we were seated in less than 5. Our server (I can't remember his name..) was attentive and friendly. My server even put all of my sauces on the side because I said I had a slight dairy allergy. I complained about my hashbrowns being salty and he promptly got me a new batch of them. Deeply appreciated and no hassle! He also offered us water since it was a hot AZ summer day. Overall, the best service I've had in a long time.  Stop by and try some of the dishes! But beware... there's not much here that's dairy-free. You might have to do some improvising.

ZdJW7rZcP_m1pdMevs0HlQ.text: I had been wanting to come here FOREVER but it is so hard to get in this place on a Saturday or Sunday morning! We finally had the perfect opportunity this past weekend as we were up early running errands around town.   Our first impressions:  Front hostess was super peppy and warm, not just to us, but to everyone..even as the line grew out the door. Her enthusiasm was contagious!   Casual and laid back retro atmosphere. The Tempe location draws a somewhat versatile crowd but it's truly the perfect spot for families and hung-over twenty-somethings alike.   Our server, Savannah, did a fantastic job. She noted that it was our first time, and treated us to a pineapple upside down pancake which literally left me speechless it tasted so good! I am definitely ordering pancakes next time!  My eggs and chicken sausage plate tasted great - I ordered more on the boring side unfortunately. Mimosa came out pretty quickly and was a solid size for the $6.  Overall, this is a no-brainer 5 star rating for amazing food and even amazing-er (yeah, I just made up a word) service!

_VNCLSBM7P_hFvYlWEYmMg.text: If I'm anything, I'm a breakfast enthusiast. Which is why I LOVE to find places like Snooze when I travel. Now let me tell you, deciding what to order at Snooze was probably the hardest decision I've made in 2016. But it was my first day in Arizona, so Juan's Breakfast Tacos it was. pIkd6FfcFeF8m0pFLTEznA.text: Feels like a ski lodge, they bump an interesting blend of electro/dance music like the lodges too. It makes sense since Snooze is a mostly Colorado based breakfast/brunch chain and the interior matches it's laid back attitude with simple orange decked decor.   Free coffee in the lobby is pretty good but the paid stuff is even better. I can't quite explain the coffee taste but it's a strong bold blend with a fruity and floral aftertaste.  The mocha is delicious! I sipped through it pretty fast but at least there's a lot of whipped cream to eat when your done.   Food-wise they do a great job as well with pretty huge portions. The spuds deluxe was a giant serving of potatoes with scallions and cheese. I chose the barbacoa and mushrooms which were great but wish the dish came with eggs instead of having to add them on for $2 extra dollars. The B.E.A.T. was a solid rendition of a BLT as well with egg and avocado ($1.75 extra) and a nice little cake of hash browns on the side.  Great addition to the neighborhood with Postino's and I look forward to eating here more. The price at both joints though will be limiting my trips sadly :'(  Drinks looked interesting, especially the Bloody Mary variations! Though I'm a little hesitant to get my drank on in the morning.

SMSmyK0U0iCGLKmmaUPo2w.text: The pancakes were terrible. They have a strange taste to them and the portion sizes are not very large. There are better breakfast places near by that are well worth your money. Go to them instead.

0X67ZHr7xHOE--CP_luGUA.text: I tried the Snooze location in Tempe and had an equally great experience. I've realized that you can't go wrong with any of their benedicts, and as per usual, the sweet potato pancakes were delicious.

zwDq1emu-7h4jGl2-gOjdQ.text: Awesome breakfast entrees! Completely satisfied! It was a 10-15 minute wait though on a busy Saturday morning..Gotta try if you're around the area.

0I_bDeuQKMRZfRVZ1SrZkA.text: Had a wonderful New Years brunch with JellyBean as my server. She was great and the reason why I will return! The rest of staff was also very friendly. Food selections normal for a breakfast place, but delicious.

INxPMFPJTWyEtYTTi0-_hA.text: Had brunch here yesterday with my girlfriend, in from out of town. Honestly chose this place because of their yelp reviews and happy I did.  Super great food, really good drinks! Sat at the bar and Starchild helped us! I recommend the Brewmossa and Eggs Benedict!

Bk9hPhU2zOVfdyvnJJL8jw.text: I am from NJ And this was amazing! Everything we got we loved :) recommended food: smashed avocado Benny, rancheros and OMG! French toast was to die for!!! Amazing environment as well, the waitress was really nice and accommodating to many needs. Definitely would come back next time I am in Phoenix!

tDQxMN9G5qhh7Qn9k5OgKQ.text: Best brunch in the Phoenix area! You'll have a wait on the weekends but it's totally worth every minute. My favorites are the Juan's Breakfast Tacos with a peanut butter cup pancake but really everything I've had here is amazing. And we saw Michael Phelps here one time!

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States

2hE32x3YfD0qJHqkVzwusQ.text: I'm not the biggest fan of breakfast food but oh man this place is amazing! Everything on their menu is great! I love that they have some delicious healthy options but honestly I can never go in without getting a pancake or two or three ;)  If you go on a weekend you can expect at least a 45 min wait but it's worth it! Service is always great!

mX8g5ydA9yHPdWM8sVpnCA.text: Food was consistently delicious. We ordered two pancake flights and two duo Benny's. These are awesome ways to go -- you get to try more than amazing dish.  It was a great place to bring my autistic daughter. She enjoyed the rhythmic reggae and nobody in the place gave a second thought to her stereotype. Once we were in the booth, which provides good lighting but lots of seclusion, she was very happy. Servers were great with her.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Benny Goodman

xFE2BDCjqH7faqTM0RWYCw.text: Went there last week for the first time And I have to admit the service was not as good as I expected. My girlfriend and I waited for almost 30 mins for our food to come out. When the food did actually come out, it was already cold so we asked for it to be heated up again. The food was decent, but the fact that we had to wait for another 15 mins longer to get a nice heated brunch was quite unreasonable. I'd probably go back one day to give it another try, but not any time soon.

RS8eQWkKT-m4btv0fSQ6BQ.text: By far my favorite spot for breakfast!! I had the Caprese Benedict which was amazingly delicious!  That plate had ripe heirloom tomatoes tossed with pesto, served over mozzarella. It also comes with 2 poached eggs (caged free eggs) with cream cheese hollandaise on top of crispy toast. I'll definitely come back again to try more items on the menu.

Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Caprese Benedict lower right

bs2tvaXQt-m_TCymXa2zSQ.text: I am sure the food is good had we got a chance to eat there. What was supposed to be a 20 minute wait turned into almost an hour. Had to leave to find abother place.

UjxdnZKoIt7LYyDHwdub6Q.text: Simply fantastic. Try the soyrizo omelet with mushrooms, avocado and cheddar. You won't be disappointed.

D3Q_aht21d04oGqI7ikNnQ.text: Absolutely my favorite place to get breakfast. The atmosphere is amazing and staff are so friendly and nice to talk to. All pancakes can be made gluten free, my favorite is blueberry streusel. I highly recommend this place!

h_UjoxN2fZldxYpkDLIYTw.text: Was visiting for the Tempe Half Ironman in October, 2017. We have Snooze in Colorado, so I knew what to expect. This location did not disappoint.   Since I was by myself, I had no problem getting a seat, but if you come with a family or a group, you may end up waiting.   This restaurant treats breakfast like a dinner; meaning, they turn it up a notch. The food is creative and of good quality. During my short stay, I came here twice so I could try different things on the menu, the menu is that compelling.   Given the areas, the prices were not unreasonable.

hED4LHm42aL7f8Tzl5TTLQ.text: The peanut butter pancake is hands down , one of the yummiest in the valley. One pancake is plenty yet some can argue differently. The wait time however is obnoxiously long but overall staff was great and nice patio seating for the winter months in AZ!

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Peanut butter pancake

KxPCSs010xrRPB35IgiGFA.text: So - love this place, but definitely go to the Gilbert location.  Waitress was too busy to refill any drinks or check on us.  Not because the restaurant was busy, she was "too busy."  Heard other tables complaining too.  Food was good, but not as good as the Gilbert location.  My son had the same meal - said it wasn't as good - but not bad.

mZSJgsRRX7zTDU12CRc5lQ.text: Stopped in for brunch today. Can't complain about the food. All our dishes were delicious! Service was deserving of a 2 star so the food really helped you on this review. I understand it's 102 outside and the outside tables probably aren't the ones you want to check up on. But geez. Drinks forgotten... Coffee forgotten... Get charged wrong on the bill then confronts me like I'm wrong but then offers to remove the whole charge?? I didn't want it removed I was fine paying what it said I would be charged on the menu. I didn't even have her waste her time rebilling me. We just left. Bloody Mary's were gross too. Casinos make a better Bloody Mary than this spot.

bjnZDtL_AEcouAyI3uEkOQ.text: Never a dull moment at SNOOZE!   It's definitely packed and has reason to be! You will wait a bit for a seat if you're not early on the weekends, but let me tell you, it is absolutely worth every second of the wait! Their pancakes are to die for, the eggs Benedict are amazing, and the breakfast booze is always appreciated! On a cool day, it is nice to enjoy your meal on the patio.   I recently had their "Breakfast Pot Pie" and it is so good! Of course I had my meal accompanied with a Bloody Mary.   Go go go! It's worth it!

daglDK_nnCanifq91hWbIw.text: Cool spot in downtown Tempe. The decor takes you back to more retro times.  Fav dish: chilaquiles benedict

-yNMHP6XCifQf-hWXFLRmA.text: The food was great but I ordered a breakfast burrito and it came with green chili, I asked for gravy instead and then when asked if I wanted to add a meat I chose steak. When the bill came they charged me an extra $3 for gravy, and an extra $10 for the steak... when I asked they took it down to $5 the "fancy meats" were a $3 add on but steak wasn't and option. If I would have known that steak and gravy would cost an extra $8 to a $9 burrito I wouldn't have gotten it. The service was okay but they should tell people how much the add on would be.

-FkD4FwHsFF9mW3iQEcn7A.text: My favorite breakfast spot! Substitutions encouraged meaning it's great for picky eaters and wonderful selections! The tacos and burrito are always a hit as well as the spuds deluxe. They always are offering free drinks and pancakes too! Overall a great experience

lLbZdebEAJT3F2X2EMMM-A.text: OMG... Fantastic breakfast and experience.  First time here and our server Vinny and Steven were AMAZING!  Recommendations were spot on and we ended up ordering some really amazing breakfast plates.    Although the breakfast pot pie and the breakfast burrito are their most popular, my favorite was the Juevos Ranceros with pulled pork on corn tortillas and the Traditional and Winter Harvest Eggs Benedict.     If you love pancakes then you have to try the upside down pineapple pancake.  It lives up to its name and taste like heaven!  You definitely have to try breakfast here at Snooze!

rgfzXM2hQ1rmsOCAXXEpLQ.text: This was my second time to Snooze and this time I remembered to snap a quick pic before devouring my amazing breakfast!   Snooze is a hot spot for breakfast and will get very crowded on the weekends especially since it is located on ASU campus. You will see your fair share of sorority girls and frat bros but don't let that deter you from enjoying the creative breakfast selections. I went for the vegetarian friendly Eggs Benedict and was very pleased. They serve their hash browns made into a small cone with good flavor but I do prefer mine slightly crispier. The eggs are cooked to perfection and are served on top of a wide range of fun selections. They also have some tasty sounding sandwiches and plates that I have yet to try.   The service is decent but you can tell they are trying to move you through as quickly as possible. They clear your table before you're really done eating and bring the check when you're only half way through your meal. This doesn't bother me too much since I'd rather not wait forever to get my check, but I don't like feeling rushed either. Despite the long waits and mediocre service Snooze is totally worth it because they are friendly and most important the food is fabulous!

Svacf-2SYimA0K0sodwn8w.text: It was pretty good but not great. The pot pie itself was good but it got kind of tiring to eat after a while. The hash was bland IMO but maybe I just have very salty taste buds.  I'm sure a lot of other items on the menu would have been good, but I just didn't get the best. They also have very interesting alcoholic drinks that I wanted to try, but didn't have a chance to.  Service was great. The employees there are very nice. It was a nice sunny day out so we sat outside with the umbrella. It felt so nice.   Overall I would recommend coming here, just ask the server for the recommended item :)

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Pot pie

6guQUI5D7wwGc9flLkRw8w.text: I almost don't want to write a good review because people in tempe haven't figured out how epically good snooze is yet. This is one of the best breakfast places you'll go to. Every single thing on the menu is out of this world, even the a la carte items. Try the hash browns but ask to add cheese...you're welcome! Plenty of seating, great coffee, lovely area...homer in every time.   PS if you have a hangover go here!

70jDHQKiH3qrqYmrb5PY8A.text: Service was good until it came time to close out, another server came by and made it seem like it was unreasonable to ask for my tab before paying, which really soured the experience. I get being busy before close but when 5 of you are clustered just chilling and talking while we wait on a check it's a problem. The host was really good, very engaging on our way to the table.

icNQrHc1YmN4iERgtBRKlw.text: It was 45 minute wait, which is expected Saturday at 11:00. We sat down ready to order, it took ten minutes to be greeted and drinks ordered, (they forgot about us). Ordered pancakes and eggs benny, a mimosa and bailey and coffee in one go. Drinks took at least ten minutes, but were great. Now we play the waiting game...45 minutes later we get some food. Which I might add was awesome.  As a restaurant worker, I understand you can't do anything about slow food or bartenders slowly making drinks. But the people next to us got a pancake while they were waiting, the entire table next to us got free shirts, and the other table got a free round of drinks. We got a long wait, good food, and server needing a tad more empathy.   We'll come back. Hopefully they'll get food and drinks times down. A bummer birthday breakfast for two.

T1i89SL1TGA32gOmBTBcZA.text: Absolutely delicious eggs Benedict's- I had the Chili Verde version. Lovely, lovely service. Very friendly and laid back but very efficient

PsGPu0Ecc3NrG8oQHqoADw.text: This is my favorite spot for Breakfast. Great service, delicious food, and yummy drinks. Highly recommend this location. I go here at least once a week.

-6naUxkJr7lXdMYchi5IwA.text: Been here a few times. It's definitely worth the wait... a little pricey but it's soooo worth it. Make sure you're not in a hurry because this place is usually packed. Especially on the weekends. Had one of my very first dates with my boyfriend of 2 years. It's a really great atmosphere. I need to try the Bloody Mary. The employees are always fantastic and great service. The pancakes are huge! They gave us a complimentary pancake once. I think it was Valentine's Day! It was really nice! That's why we keep coming back.

1zA1xExLsCYWXhg0XMShpg.text: It was absolutely amazing. I ordered the pancake of the day: chocolate chip pancake with vanilla bean sauce and was totally blown away. I will definitely visit here again during my stay here in Tempe. Thumbs up!

Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States

g9URKmsi7CwJEqTko7Uz0A.text: I love this place! The breakfast is always phenomenal when I come! I've had many meetings here and brought visiting friends and family here as well. Each time they never disappoint!  The only downfall to me is the parking. But much like the rest of DT Tempe, paid parking is the norm. At least they are conveniently located right next to a parking garage so you don't have to go too far!

w5rkxruLtiQDG-6pWYx-jg.text: Came here on a Sat morning after hiking A mountain. Got here about 8:30am and no wait and got seated immediately. We asked to be seated outside because the weather was gorgeous after it rained the day before.  My friend ordered the Breakfast Pot Pie which was a lot of food that filled up her plate. I ordered Juans Breakfast tacos which comes in a trio. It was a little on the lighter side but my friend and I shared plates. Highly recommend the Mmm  Mmm mimosas which has OJ and Pomegranate liqueur....So good and refreshing!

-YXRZWcwdVGWT1v-Fwt6vw.text: Eggs Benedict - salsa verde is untouchable.  Wow so freaking delicious.  I seriously day dream about this stuff.  I don't know how to explain it other then you won't be disappointed.  It has so much flavor and every bite will take you closer to heaven.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Do I really need to say anything about this?  Absolute heaven in the mouth!

5iKgEEsEHQirXd622iA1Fg.text: Go EARLY and avoid the wait to be seated. We sat at the bar to avoid waiting for a table. I had the pancake flight (one was the French toast) with a side of bacon. Everything was favorable down to the thick cut bacon. The Mister had egg white omelette with veggies, hash brown and toast. He enjoyed his food as well. The atmosphere is what you would expect in a college area...casual, hip and busy. Wasn't too thrilled with having to watch  the Nickelodeon channel at the bar while drinking our mimosas. Would have preferred sports highlights or national news.

td9Xbbswz6XpOfzlceBlBg.text: A new hidden treasure in Tempe. Just look at the menu, read it and when that question comes up "Could this really be as good as it sounds?" The answer is totally YES! So worth spending an hour to find a place around here worth going to for breakfast. Not an easy task I might add. Normally I don't mention anyone but the "bartender/waitress" that helped me was very knowledgable and as excited to tell me about their menu as I was to try it. It made my indecisive self make a clear choice based off of her recommendation which was honest and so correct!   Breakfast Tacos with Barbacoa. Not something I would normally order and something I have never had. So good!  Reasonably priced high quality food with competent and friendly staff. Not much else to ask for.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. I could not wait to take a bite.

_7hShUercbiFsJnHCJYzyw.text: My husband and I came down to Tempe for a weekend to have fun and meet up with his college roommate.  His roommate took us here (he always takes us the best places) when we said we wanted breakfast.  We had a nice walk from our hotel and only a short wait to get a table.  The place was hoppin'.  We ate on the patio, which was perfect as it was a beautiful day.  Our server was peppy and attentive.  They were doing a 50s beach/surfer theme, so staff was all dressed in character.    I ordered the Snooze breakfast burrito and a mimosa.  It was very flavorful and I liked that it was black beans instead of refried.  My husband got the corned beef hash breakfast and was equally impressed.  It was very hard to choose what I wanted to eat because there are so many options.  They have a breakfast pot pie that looks sinful.  There are all kinds of breakfast sammies and they have pancake platters if you want to try different flavors.  I would love to eat here again on our next Tempe trip.

O-lNT8qdj4dpKIwImi18Zg.text: Me and my husband went here for breakfast it was sooo good! He had the shrimp and grits and it was divine. The mimosa are soo good. We will definitely be back.

x9rOAz7QdoRyLoVuDxzsKw.text: If I can eat a cage free egg and gluten free pancakes and listen to Pink Floyd, this place is cool with me!

T29OyiJEaFhuodd2y8KCzg.text: Came here on a busy Monday morning. It was a holiday so we expected a long wait. Everyone was very friendly and good came out within a reasonable amount of time. The pancakes were amazing! They do get pretty busy, so expect a bit of a wait. The wait was well worth it! Will definitely be back.

wNngnRIWl9EJlJMkc9KI9g.text: Breakfast is one of my favorite meals (let's be honest, there isn't a meal I dislike...) and Snooze does it right! The atmosphere is fantastic and they have a lot of indoor and outdoor seating options. The menu is fairly extensive and I'm pretty sure that even a picky eater could find something they like.   One thing to be aware of is parking. There really isn't any close parking (limited street parking and there are nearby garages), but the food makes up for it.  I highly recommend this place and can't wait to go back!

ngHWAKXhTzRwkvzW-k5Kfw.text: Great service, pleasant inside and outside seating arrangements and comfortable relaxed atmosphere. The food was pretty good, although the eggs seemed to be quite small, so three egg breakfast is not at all intimidating. Overall I did not feel that we got  a good value for the price.  The two things that were very bad - coffee and a choice of music. Coffee was watery and disgusting. Neither cream nor sugar could rescue it. Terrible music of a style I'm unfamiliar with was blasting precluding is from talking in comfortable tones of voice and forcing waiters to squat next to tables.  Maybe the issue is that we came near closing time, will try to get there earlier next time - maybe it will be better.

Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. 3 egg breakfast with chorizo sausage

t43zTkWJlxMabs7D7eM6lA.text: My favorite place to have breakfast every time I'm in Tempe or Phoenix area. This place dishes out the classic breakfast dishes with their own twist!   My usuals - Breakfast Pot Pie/Bella Bella Benedict/ Corned Beef Hash/O.M.G. French toast and always a side of tender bacon!   Snooze also has great drink selections with a well crafted breakfast oriented cocktail menu.   Also their pancakes are great, get the pancake flight and try the hot cocoa pancakes!   Go early, as lines start to build on weekends.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. O.M.G. French Toast
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Breakfast pot pie with a side of tender bacon.

4ZHBEHzv-YEtScgvWjQNaw.text: Snooze is a great breakfast spot. They have something for everyone and their seasonal pancakes are always on point.  They also have some of the best breakfast drinks I've found. The mimosa is solid, they make a mean greyhound and the mayan mocha will really wake you up!  Be prepared to wait for seating - this place is BUSY (but worth it).

P-fcuFOIi-NmgjxpYonLZw.text: I think this a great place to grab breakfast with friends because there are a lot of different things to try on the menu. My first time here a couple years ago was a bad experience, but the couple times after since I've gone they've been really good.   At first I was going to get an egg dish and get a pancake on the side but the pancake was FOUR DOLLARS. FOUR DOLLARS FOR ONE PANCAKE. AND NOT EVEN A BIG PANCAKE, JUST A NORMAL SIZED PANCAKE. lol, ya'll are funny.  So instead, I got the pancake flight this time around and it was such a good decision. Three pancakes, three different flavors, so yum. I was only not feeling the pumpkin pancake, so I wish I would have gotten a different kind. BUT they had their pancake of the day which had chocolate and pomegranate and it was probably one of the best flavored pancakes I've ever eaten. I definitely suggest getting this flight if you can't choose from their selection.  The only problem I have is the portions are pretty small while the prices are fairly high. I was actually pretty hungry not too long after I ate.

OSoXBmX5RtwLQ1jBU2QlGQ.text: I've never had a breakfast here that wasn't on point. I don't mind waiting on busy weekend days, there are always a lot of people out socializing and even that can be fun. My only complaint is that The sweet potato pancakes and Hash are so good that I've never had a chance to try anything else!

6dnd87wPLRwwjvV2xBtwrg.text: I had the OMG French Toast and it was really good. The wait was about 30 minutes to get a table but I'm giving 3 stars because our food took a really really really long time. I kept thinking they were going to tell us that the meal was free, but they didn't.

o8anWYu8LVSb6I5JbsUBAw.text: Love this place. The food is great and they have a pet friendly patio. This is one of our favorite breakfasts place to bring the dog.  They have a great eclectic menu that has something dor everyone.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. This is the OMG french toast with a side of bacon. The front picture is the breakfast pot pie. So good.
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States

taY4l-FoU4y0rne1aINsNg.text: Delicious healthy breakfast brunch. I enjoyed the quinoa eggs hollandaise (sorry can't remember name). Super tasty and healthy. Only minor issue was the toasted grains were very hard, could break a tooth. Were they supposed to be crispy? BF had the pot pie egg dish and was excellent. There was a size-able crowd and we got seated impressively in 30. Great service and very friendly! Highly recommend.

u_3eCtEAe_5F5AX0VbZLwQ.text: A little late on my review but this place is great for breakfast/brunch. It does get very busy so expect a wait. I ended up coming about an hour before they close and was able to get a seat at the bar straight away.   The mimosas are totally worth it. I think they were about $6 but they are big and you can tell there is enough champagne in there.   Highly recommend the eggs Benedict. I had the dui of Bella Bella benny and ham benedict III. The Bella Bella was my favorite. Definitely get the hash browns extra crispy... tastes way better.   There is so much to choose from and everything that came out of the kitchen looked delicious.

Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Ham bendedict III and Bella Bella benny

Re1kd3QRRIUCKPd3ZpULQw.text: Was in town for the Innings Festival and wanted to find the perfect local joint for brunch before the bands hit the stage. This place was perfect! Friendly staff, awesome food, great vibe. Free mimosas and bloody Mary's while you wait. The breakfast burrito was a beast. Pineapple pancakes were delicious. It was so good we went two days in a row. Highly recommend if you're in the area!

osauFOySSdOVQAFIZ-E6Mg.text: Snooze is so amazing. From the moment you walk in the door you feel welcome, but that's not even the best part. The best part is the PANCAKE FLIGHT! I got to pick from a delicious assortment of pancakes (I went with pineapple upside down, sweet potato, and chocolate chip) and I was left in pure amazement. So good!!   They were also amazing with the little one in our party. I highly recommend this place.

8GuTpD-_sPVowqyHWyvxxQ.text: Love love love this place! I have never had a bad meal! The OMG French toast is the BEST! The Bloody Mary's with bacon are awesome!

wqYdZUQT7kGHGcCY8gpkxw.text: Excellent service, great food and prompt! Morgan was awesome, pleasant and accommodating. Next time I'm in Tempe, I'll be back.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States

EZ3cjH1PiN2k5T0cibmr5Q.text: Amazing! The pancake of the day was so good we ordered again before leaving. I was so impressed.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. The pancake of the day was white chocolate with a strawberry jam and almonds. They need it on their menu!!

bqeWrtUm5Fqn4gz9F-_y-Q.text: Cute restaurant with great service and a tasty menu. I had pancakes and hash browns and coffee - everything was amazing and the service was perfect. Well worth the trip!

pqgpen1DinUl1gVEjHBP_Q.text: Awesome food and our awesome server Riley was dope!!!! Coming back again!!! Make sure to try their coffee and their breakfast burrito. It'll make you full all day lol

zXteuvljZxItmzjRC492yg.text: I been here many times and always have an amazing experience,the food it's amazing my favorite is the pineapple pancakes all the employees are super friendly and attentive always happy to help the restaurant is always very clean and organized come here once a week!

ublEexqo_cUPd93pQmWcPQ.text: Stopped in Tempe while running some errands and decided we better get something to eat. Stopped into Snooze after seeing they had a flight of pancakes. The A/C was broken and it was 51 degrees inside, so we chose the patio, but can being cool in Arizona be a bad thing. We tried the pineapple upside down, pumpkin, and the pancake of the day, a lemon blueberry concoction which sounded like it had a lot going but it was by far the best of the three and the others weren't bad. Ordered a side of bacon and hash browns as well. Both delicious. The bacon was good hick cut and cooked perfectly for us and the hash browns had a slightly seasoned and onion taste. Again delicious!

rY8Wmwz4Klgqm7215wmcog.text: Best breakfast in Tempe! I have probably been here about 4 times since it opened and it's now my go to breakfast spot in Tempe.  The decor is so fresh and cute but also inviting. Every time I've been the servers are great and always able to give suggestions. I have had all of the eggs Benedict but my absolute favorite is the chiliquiles benedict! It's eggs benedict with salsa, barbacoa, and a stack of tortillas instead of an English muffin. Seriously delicious! If you can't decide which eggs Benedict you want you can do half and half.  Speaking of half and half, my boyfriend was deciding between 2 different french toasts and our server said he could do half of each. They seriously go above and beyond to make their customers happy and encourage customization.   Next time you need a breakfast close to ASU or you want to show off Tempe to out of towners, come here!

d5Pkpthk8ozzbmI0Avi2kw.text: This is a ASU favorite  I went for the first time while moving my daughter back to ASU.  Had the pineapple upside pancakes, and WOW what an explosion of flavor.  Its a must to return.  Try it you wont regret it

LksS_9PjpBw9QyE_bUnaUw.text: I'll start out by saying that the manager was very nice and comped our breakfast. The bad news is that we sent the toast back 3 times it was either warm bread or burnt. Eggs over medium were eggs over hard and bacon was cold and like jerky. This experience is unusual. Normally the food is very good. I'm hoping it's just a new cook or different process.

KMgIbx_075jiPPKpkeybzQ.text: Traveling through Tempe again and stopped here for breakfast once again. They always cook pouched eggs perfect, not to mention the sweet potato pancakes just melt in your mouth with flavor. My husband and I always share plates to taste different things. Service, also great. This ranks as one of my top favorite places for breakfast. The reason I didn't put a 5 was because they allow dogs and when they shake all their hair goes all over the place. Don't get me wrong, I love dogs, have 2 of my own.

kEIzAEJGi7wSdhdIfBhuRQ.text: Great place, great atmosphere, great food, and staff is friendly. If you feel like enjoying a good mimosa then head down to snooze.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Breakfast burrito

YKFBDkviS2e9MY52sQea-w.text: This place is soooo yummy! I have been here twice and have not been disappointed. You really can't get anything wrong on the menu. The drinks are delicious too. The service is great along with the atmosphere!

Hcm6qEKSqGN9Zlzlr2WlQQ.text: Don't snooze on Snooze. it is DELICIOUS! I get a half order of the OMG French toast and a half order of the breakfast tacos and by the end of it, my plates are bare. the sauce in the tacos is just magical. and the syrup mixed with the cream cheese or WHATEVER IT IS, that's on the French toast just melts me. I really enjoy snooze. (and the tacos are vegetarian. PLUS!)

tRlkk5OxY8izIUHsbLMhlA.text: First time trying Snooze. Had great expectations but unfortunately our duo Benny plate came without some of the necessary accompaniments, like hollandaise. However, our server Kate let the manager Adrienne know, and they handled it quickly and professionally. Hence the five stars. Kate's service was impeccable and Adrienne's to handle the situation with grace is why we are giving the five stars! And we are coming back to try another dish and give it another go! :)

EgzzdIkIyHz5jRgnIy9Ugg.text: Great food in a fun atmosphere!  Come prepared to wait.  Coffee was excellent!  Good tea selection.  We had the breakfast pot pie and pancake flight and both were very good!

hhpBAvvpQI_cvRpiOzQMsQ.text: Beautiful morning-open air Snooze. Love the staff and the vibe for Duck / Sparky matchup later!

-z05piOAvHdU3kzOhmI3ew.text: I wish you could give bonus stars for customer service! Myself and some gal pals from the office placed a to go order and when we got back to work realized we were missing one side taco. I called the manager who offered to drive over the item since our office isn't very far away. Very shortly afterwards he arrived with not one but 3 tacos and 2 different kinds of pancakes. I was blown away! First of all, the food is insanely delicious to begin with but what really caught my attention was how well the manager guaranteed that we'd be back by going above and beyond!

UsaFBzUcdQVTWbGCtH7y8g.text: Snooze is hit or miss. The tofu is terrible. I love that they have t but it's so undercooked even when I order it well done. Hashbrowns and pancakes are amazing. Mimosas are great. Great service this time.

dju-iITiP8D75dWhXkVcqw.text: Incredibly friendly staff; they all seem like they love working there & have a nice team-atmosphere. The wait can be a pain, but they offer a self-serve station with yummy free coffee which helps. Cute retro decor & decent food/selection. The portions are quite large & great for sharing.

OrGPNUAo1_Vd5qX5O3rpUw.text: Came here off of a recommendation with two of my friends and the wait wasn't terrible we sat down after a 10 min wait. I got the mmm mmm mimosa and that was amazing both of my friends got coffee one had ice coffee and the other had regular coffee and they both agreed that there coffee was good. Now when it came to the food I've had way better breakfast food the chocolate chip pancakes where just ok. My one friend had the breakfast pot pie she said she couldn't even justify now could it could've been because it was ice cold. My other friend had the Bella Bella Benny and the Benny good man and all she has to say was gross the hollandaise sauce had way to much mayonnaise in it and did nothing for it. The waitress was not that great ether it just really seemed like she didn't wanna be there maybe she was just having a bad day

L6hzev5CfGrTABl3SrDpbg.text: Pineapple upside down pancake was amazing!  The wait was a little long, but the food was so worth it!  Went there for a meet and greet between my boyfriend/mom.  We each had something different, but loved every bite!  My mom happened to mention how great the pancake would be, and the waitress brought us one on her!  Would recommend to anyone who enjoys good breakfast/brunch!

9I988eE2e6zVPZ-4btwUMg.text: We came for lunch, were seated and waited for 15 minutes with no drink orders nor any contact by the wait staff. We saw several standing around chatting with each other. We waived our arms and were ignored. We walked out.

P0ykKwOwu2wJhpI1RIUdyw.text: Generally I try to stick to local spots when I eat out, but snooze is a breakfast joint and I love breakfast. Anyway, my first time there the waitstaff was having a competition to see who could drink the most bloody Mary's on shift; my group found this hilarious and the feeling in the restaurant was fun and professional. The food was 4/5 stars, the service was great, the prices were kind of high, and I will definitely go back. Oh! Also, they allow pets on the patio which is great for my dog -- he loves it! There are better local spots, but you probably won't be too disappointed here either way.

hLJ7dc2sS-AH-RD-tUeg4A.text: Food is not bad (average breakfast food). Nice atmosphere and nice staff but way over priced. Especially for being on a college campus.

e0rZRRBAgvzQEiP4VUkp3w.text: There is no reason to go to snooze when ncounter is within walking distance. The quality isn't terrible, but the prices make it seem like snooze thinks they invented breakfast.   The hollandaise sauce was thick, almost the consistency of nacho cheese you'd left sitting for a bit too long, and lacked the familiar spice or lemon zing you'd expect.   Snooze: ham Benedict (English muffin, ham, egg, hollandaise, shredded hash brown) 10.50; $13 out the door   Ncounter: farmers market eggs Benedict (English muffin, ham, avocado, sauteed spinach, tomato, egg, hollandaise, country style hash browns) 7.50, side of fruit (pineapple, grapes, cantaloupe, honeydew, watermelon, oranges) 3. $13 out the door

PoqSJIMixqgaZkG8VG8sZg.text: Stopped by Snooze AM Tempe last weekend, second visit to the chain and the first at this location.  Atmosphere - Nice layout, we had a table inside but would look to sit outside as the weather changes. My only dislike was having the A/C vents pointed right at some tables which made it too cold when it kicked on.  Service - Great. The estimated wait time was exactly what they quoted. The waitress was great in her very positive demeanor and her speed. Food came out very quick which was a plus.  Food - Really good and creative menu. Breakfast Pot Pie - Tasty and the perfect size for my wife, the crust is very flakey and gravy is good. Snooze Spuds Deluxe - Good dish and if I were to re-order I'd make two changes to my order. First, don't order the chorizo, it tasted nothing like chorizo and I even asked the waitress if it wasn't the chicken sausage but she confirmed it was chorizo. Second, take their recommendation to put an egg or two on top, without them it is a little too dry. I'd like to them to put on a little more cheese on it.  Overall, a very good place and I'm going up to four stars based on the service.

zmgPhvldAUfztA7szN-25Q.text: This place has it all. Great atmosphere, food, & drinks. Service was good. We went on Valentine's Day & i loved that in the bathroom they had Valentine cards & treats just incase you forgot someone. Very excited for one going up in Gilbert. Love the Bloody Mary options. Had the Bangkok & it was spot on! Chilaquiles Benedict where amazing & I'll be honest I was very nervous about this choice. Everyone else enjoyed their meals & they were very accommodating for my friend who doesn't do dairy. Sweet potato pancakes were a pleasant surprise. Def worth the wait, especially since Postinos is next door for a Bellini while you wait.

GRPq9a6n7iQnupNcMeX83w.text: Visited Snooze on New Year's Day. Very busy with all the staff working hard. One staff member was missing though - the cleaning person. The floor had puddles of spilled drinks and who knows what else and the restroom was filthy. Lots of staff, but still one short. Gave it a 4 because the food was great.

p_yx5SpEwwWDVXUVhxaWuA.text: Food was really yummy!! The service was great also!! Definitely go back again! Hot Chocolate was delicious wish it was a little warmer.. And the OMG French Toast was divine!! It started to rain they put up umbrella's fast and the heaters were on because it was windy and cold!!

fNVTmy8KLUo3-fNVn8dcow.text: Hip hop music, slow rude inept staff from the bottom up, bland food.  Maybe Saturday at 9:15 is better spent elsewhere.

OjgMQy2AQHv2aeUOuLm4VQ.text: Cute cafe just off ASU campus. Great breakfast brunch selection.

lNH0lvyHTpHVLTBMPN_xAg.text: I love this place. A lot. The only negative thing I could say is it's hard to choose something off the menu because it all looks good.  There has been a wait every time I've been but never more than 30 min for 2 and they have a nice setup where you can sit and relax on the patio, play ping-pong, or play bags while you wait. The bar is also first come first serve if you happen to get lucky and spot someone leaving.  Starting with drinks, they have some really interesting sounding morning cocktails and fancy coffee drinks but so far I've just tried mimosas (grapefruit & orange) because they're fresh squeezed and you can't go wrong with a mimosa for brunch. They also have free coffee set up near the host stand to drink while you're waiting for a table.  The food is amazing. I've tried the Harvest Benedict. So good! I also got the Sandwich I Am with a pear pancake instead of the hashbrowns (you can sub for like $3 I think) and I would definitely recommend both of those as well.

Cdabq1xEu7UA2GjLWTtH8A.text: Stylish and eclectic atmosphere with really yummy breakfast food! Staff is nice and attentive, very good place for breakfast or brunch. This particular location can get kind of crowded and difficult to get to though because the college is so close. Also, you have to pay for parking and may have a walk a distance. However, it's close to a parking garage (still have to pay and walk, but it's covered!). Recommended for a brunch once in a while!

MVmtKHVR9_IXFz5n93w8Qw.text: The b.e.l.t. Is amazing! I added avocado and it was to die for! The Dijon mustard aioli made the sandwich. $5 for beer pitchers and wine by the glass, an awesome deal. Definitely recommend for brunch

Qaw1Adp-vENiqjHYv_B9GQ.text: Snooze has the most creative pancakes I've ever tasted/ heard of! I tried the pineapple pancakes, literally little pineapple bits in the pancake with brown sugar on top. Soooo good. I also had the pecan pancakes. They are very large pancakes and can share with 3-4 people. Iced chai tea is really tasty. I ordered the "sandwich I am" on the menu because it sounded delicious with bacon, a fried egg, and hollindase sauce on a pretzel bun.. But somehow she put in a different breakfast sandwich instead. I ended up with the BEAT sandwich.. Served on cibatta bread with bacon, tomato, an egg, and aioli sauce. It was alright but I would preferred the one I ordered. Has browns are very crispy on the top and soft in the middle. They are generous with their sides of fruit. Friendly staff with dog-friendly patio seating.

aOT87HV69gYBLz6-xRiULQ.text: The service is awesome, Caitlin was the best! The corned beef was the best I have had anywhere in the USA! Add to that the great bloody Mary's!

qMLT1fbP1Eiwtkl9YIVtWw.text: We usually always eat breakfast at I hop or first watch, but you get tired of the same locations and want to try new breakfast spots so we tried snooze for the high ratings. We went to Snooze on a busy Sunday morning, with a long waiting time, but overall the service was really great. The quinoa bowl and eggs Benedict were really good. The regular snooze coffee was good too. I had ordered the macchiato previously but wasn't a big fan and the server was kind enough to ask if I had liked it or wanted a regular instead. The server went above and beyond not rushing us and making suggestions she also was trying to put more umbrella on the patio outside for us and other customers. Even with how busy it was they still gave us great service!

tAbl4Jpdch0N89KFPTF_Ag.text: Over all this place was pretty good. The wait sucked but food made up for it. I had the chilaquiles it had lots of flavor. It was a little pricey for the portions you get. I am not sure if I would ever come back here again though.

YJxOVWhQAv958mRAGZrITw.text: Best pancake I've ever had in my life. Every time I go I get the pancake of the day cause I know it won't disappoint! If you are looking for a good breakfast place in Tempe I highly encourage you to look no further. Snooze is everything!!

uSESGUHvJHF-WNNprHQ63Q.text: Had breakfast with a group of friends today, and what a treat. Our servers, Jesse & Carleen were super attentive, cannot beat the customer service we received.  Travis greeted us and checked in several times to make sure all was good. The place was packed, but we  never felt rushed to order or eat. We must have timed it right, because there were no lines, but it did get completely filled.  The food was delicious, and definitely worth going back again. So many choices, and we did get to sample the pineapple pancakes, sweet potato pancake, and OMG French Toast. Will definitely go back and recommend to my friends.

ieVtt5_WYNPb0gu01yydsw.text: Have been here a few times, as usual the place was busy, which is a good sign in my books. The food is and was excellent, had a three egg omelette with beef, spinach and mushrooms, sourdough toast with blackberry jam and a hash brown. I tried one of their coffee cocktails, the dirty drunken chai. All fantastic. The only issue with the place was the service, poor would be an upgrade on what we got.

8_VZww8F8wN0RKPg-tfIEA.text: The meatless eggs Benedict (Late Harvest Benny) is very disappointing and was probably the worst "veggie" eggs Benedict I've ever had. The pancake flight (pick three different pancake flavors) was pretty good, nothing amazing though. Don't know if I'll be back.

5Wk1Y9e_vXZEkJd9TeQhYw.text: Had the best experience this morning at snooze. Our server Liz was incredible. She really made the whole experience that much better, not to mention the food is incredible. Thanks Liz!

RgZ7AAtii_8-Nc-tJpDLhQ.text: 5 stars on the food and only one star for the service.  After our food was delivered it was impossible to get attention for coffee refills or items wanted (tabasco).  The decor is five stars.  It is a 1950's throw back ambiance. There is nothing to buffer the sound so 'ya gotta speak loudly to be heard.  There is good offering on the menu.  The omelet with 3 items was great.  One person in our group got the hash (yuck) but he was an aficionado & loved it.  All of our entrees were great.  We arrived at 8:30 on a Saturday morning and there was no wait.  However, when we left 1.5 hours later there was a huge waiting line. (They open @ 6:30 am.)  Tip: If you have more than four in your party you might go elsewhere.    Tip for the management: If you have more attentive servers you'll speed along the dining and cut down the waiting time for other patrons.  Also, the manager should float around asking if everything is ok.  Or, at least have the servers check with the customer a couple of minutes after serving to see if all is ok.

8z2il24gSkQOvb-BVZ9d-A.text: Great service and even better environment! I had the burrito and wasn't super crazy about it. However, that could just be personal preference. Everything else was phenomenal!! Can't wait to go back!

4Wfp_WRUx4GBvCOVasP8MQ.text: Fabulous brunch place!! I love the sweet stuff on the menu. The specialty pancakes are amazing!  There is parking available in the asu Fulton garage if you can't find a meter.

KPBQdJufhORtZTJM_iRTsA.text: This place has the worst fucking service times of any breakfast restaurant I have ever seen. So fucking pathetic that I left a $0 tip for the lazy fucking waiter there. You guys suck at serving customers.

mY4mIwE9ZwxajVmpa-TnVA.text: Snooze is always consistent with their food and service. We came here before heading to the airport to leave AZ. We had snooze in Pheonix the day before and really enjoyed our experience there. We had to wait 45 mins for a table at this one. Something I like about Snooze is that their timelines are accurate for a wait. They also text you when your table is about to be ready. This location of this one is pretty small and it's right on campus. We made the mistake of saying first available and it was a hot day. They strategized well with with umbrellas and each table was under an umbrella. The still air didn't help the situation though and we were pretty hot while we ate. It really just took from our experience a bit since the food and service were still great. I had the lower east sider (I'm not sure if it's lower or upper) and it was great. My husband had the build your own omelette which he really enjoyed (again). We both shared the cinnamon roll pancake which is thee best pancake ever! It melts in your mouth and has some sort of warm frosting filling. Oh man, it's divine.  So yeah good food, service, ambiance and I recommend sitting inside!

r_RU3__IKb8Akq2FhIYj_Q.text: Melt in your mouth deliciousness!! Had the chilaquiles bene amazing and Mamosa everything fantastic

xFatW375mcLAfAaHMDlDmw.text: Expect to wait awhile if you're coming during the school year during the weekend brunch rush. This is easily one of the better breakfast places in Tempe. When I come here with a friend we like to split the gluten free pancake flight and regular 2 egg breakfast. My friend has celiac disease and they are very accommodating. The gluten free pancakes are just as good as the regular ones, super fluffy and sweet. Make sure to ask about some of the flavors that aren't listed on the menu, the cinnamon roll and sweet potato are my personal favorites. The hashbrowns and eggs are also spot on.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Post Race Mimosas
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Pancake Flight

vysjOYqOBlFCX7pj_y1gew.text: I dont usually go out to breakfast that much, however that has changed ever since my first visit to snooze. Farm fresh, inviting staff, unique pancakes, ping ping, delicious cappuccino, vegetarian choices. ...........i could go on forever. .........good music. .........LOVE this place.  All locations!

y2Jsat4ELR0znbzzJCG17A.text: Tried to visit but too much construction on college avenue - had to go all around from north only to discover parking must be paid at the building in the back about a football field away! Worst location for a restaurant - should be commercial or education based locale.

WxQe1Hy4IAle_NRdc4rDuw.text: I'm originally from Colorado so I was so excited to see that they opened a snooze down in the valley! The pancakes...Amazing! The breakfast tacos are probably my favorite though. My girl friend and I went in to get some breakfast and couldn't have been more impressed with the service and the food. I'm 99% sure the girl that served us was named Parker and she did such a great job at making us feel welcome and she put a smile on both of our faces! I have worked in the food industry for most of my working career and its very hard to find good service. Not with Parker! I will definitely be coming back and very soon!! And if its possible I'm asking for the same server! :)  (I really hope I got the girls name right...?)

8X-Ge0-Rbcreujk9bmK5tg.text: Went here for the first time and the food was very good to excellent, although sadly I have to knock off a couple of stars due to some poor customer service which I'll get to in a bit.   First the good, I had the corned beef hash which was very tasty and so much better then the standard hash you get from most breakfast places. At the table we also had eggs benedict which were great, and the french toast was some of the best I've ever had. The coffee was above average for a breakfast place, and the prices overall were reasonable. The juices tasted freshly squeezed the overall quality of the food was great.  Apparently there is often an hour wait when ASU is in session, but with school out the wait was only 10 minutes or so.  Now to the aforementioned downside. My partner ordered some chorizo along with his breakfast. When we got the bill he was charged double the amount listed on the menu. When he brought it up to the waitress she got the manager who pointed out a section on the back part of the menu where the same item was shown with the increased price, then attempted to explain why sometimes it costs more and sometimes it cost less. When he pointed out there was nothing on the menu to indicate one vs the other we got a big eye-roll, shrug and the manager left without another word. It was only a difference of a couple dollars on a 60 dollar tab and an easy fix for the manager but the blow off left us annoyed and unlikely to come back, despite the quality of the food.

RyV55Gg91Lm38yl79ORacA.text: On campus in Tempe, went on a Saturday morning so the wait was long as expected but once we were sat we had a great waiter and delicious food. One of my favorites now! I tried the Snooze Simple dish with 3 eggs, choice of meat, hash browns, and toast! It was a perfect amount of food for the price and it was delicious! Can't wait to come back!

Evn4SuswhKMobA0z13UPjQ.text: Food here is absolutely phenomenonal.  There is a nice outdoor seating area with a great view. AND be sure to try one of there mimosa.

GcF2Y8aG9b4R3Nc5i701Dw.text: Food is usually fantastic. Today was not quite up to par. Server was a bit preoccupied. We ordered strawberries on the pancakes ask specifically for fresh not soaked in sugar. We didn't want them if soaked. Typically have always come fresh but last week they weren't so we asked. They came soaked in sugar again:( also two of us ordered hash browns flat and crispy only one of us got then that way:( server was refilling waters one in my part covered his glass and said none for me thanks. She the preceded to refill his glass. We will still come back but hope for different server.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. View from our table

CyW5d3Sje82UgktYLIdM0w.text: They told us 60 minute wait.  When I checked 30 minutes into the wait they told me "You are 30 minutes into your 85 minute wait".  They said the same to another party behind us.  We left for Harlows

Bj-6caZwDPc60vJ8XxOU3Q.text: Wow! All I can really say is wow! Incredible food! Honestly the best breakfast I have had in the whole state of Arizona! That is how impressed we are! Best Bloody Mary's in the state as well! Incredible impressive! We recommend to everyone!!

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Nothing but deliciousness!!!

UqsgOBUganjis3FBsM02Pg.text: This place was spectacular. The atmosphere, the service, and the food were all excellent. My first visit was yesterday, and I am already planning my next trip over there (I live in SE Gilbert).   I had coffee and the Green Eggs and Hamwich with a side of hash browns. My son had scrambled eggs, sausage links, and a chocolate chip pancake. Everything was delicious. I will definitely be back.

MpJ9ub3GeoMqW6vJFa5qJg.text: We went around 9am on a Saturday morning and had a minimal wait. Great outdoor seating area, with ping pong and cornhole games. Brunch was awesome! They have several great eggs Benedict options, and you can mix and match two together. I had one with smoked salmon and another roasted vegetables on top of griddled roasted pepper grit cakes (Late Harvest Benny). We tried several mimosa variations, all good. Service was spot on - very attentive and never rushed us out of the table, even as the place got busy (and it gets BUSY). Will definitely be back.

V6-nPuDlzt0b-ES9pJPD5A.text: First time at Snooze.  Everyone complains about the wait but we were seated right away.  The omg French toast is amazing and the pomegranate marg was tasty! I would recommend and I will be back!
