G3ZJuGk-xlKx9ZLfydrXRg.text: Waited happily for about an hour for a table with friends who could not say enough wonderful things about Snooze. We were seated outside at a beautiful table, and as we walked to the table we were assured that although the there was no umbrella over the table currently, they would be moving one to alleviate the Phoenix sun.   After our waitress took our drink order, we were basically told we were moving inside due to not being able to move an umbrella. SHANNON was very rude in her delivery of the news and never apologized or recognized the error in their lack of hospitality. The new waitress more than made up for the rudeness of SHANNON and our meal was delicious. However, the incident in moving our party of 5 hung over our meal.   Another authoritative member of the staff did bring a complimentary plate of pancakes that we were not terribly interested in having since 4 out of 5 of our party had already ordered pancakes. Again, still without apology.   Restaurants are not solely about food, but experience. SHANNON could use some training in her understanding of a full dining experience.

GJilUKzMW7u9ZO3MFpVP5g.text: Just got done eating at Snooze. Nick greeted us at the door about as friendly as a host could be. Cisco, our waiter was absolutely the best. Friendly and prompt service. I had the delicious breakfast tacos and a chocolate pancake that was to die for. Definitely one of my new favorites.

8Nkkq_w7hv7YeIyULtFKUA.text: Today was my first Snooze experience and I cannot wait to go back! I want to try everything on the menu! Perfect portion sizes and appropriate pricing. The caramel apple mimosa is delicious! Definitely a new favorite. Love the trendy, upbeat atmosphere as well as great service. Would recommend to everyone!

en5LWXCkmpk8DaAt4deMXA.text: They only offer two types of beer which is disappointing if you don't like breakfast type alcoholic beverages. I had French Toast Neat, which was disappointing, with a side of two scrambled eggs, which seemed like one in serving size, and it was all very overpriced. I won't be coming back. Perhaps I will try Postino next door for brunch next time.

QnMZ0cpzNPeokP0YtJXp1A.text: Great food and service. Hard to get over all the hipsters though. It's like Seattle but with sun and no rain in that place...

tm7OlIAm5mp7bqf4qbm7aA.text: Amazing food and good service. We had the Chili Verde eggs Benedict And the sinful pancake. They where both FANTASTIC!

OObTvu9xcY71wktV0tdWWQ.text: Alright I'll admit it, I'm no morning person. Sleeping in till 12pm is a breeze for me. And waking up before then is considered early for me. But no way will I snooze through the morning anymore after eating at this amazing restaurant!  After visiting Snooze for the first time in Phoenix and experienced the most amazing brunch ever, I just had to take my mom. We visited this location on a gloomy Sunday. It was raining earier but when we arrived the rain had stopped and the sun peaked through the clouds. The host took my name and number and told us the wait was about 45 minutes. We walked on over to the art festival Mill was holding untill I received a text that our table was ready.  After 45 minutes we were seated outside, which we didn't mind at all. I ordered a cappuccino with almond milk and my mom had a cup of coffee to start with. The cappuccino wasn't bad but wasn't amazing either. I actually really liked my mom's coffee more. After our drinks I ordered the Breakfast Pot Pie with the OMG! French Toast on the side. Mom got the Winter Harvest Bene with a side order of the Pineapple Upside down Pancakes.  By the time our server came out with our food the rain had started to pour. I was excited to dig it but the wind was super intense and started to damper the mood. I ask the waitress if we could sit inside as soon as there was a table available. She was very understanding and said yes of course. Less then 5 minutes later a outdoor umbrella comes crashing down towards our table. I let out a scream and held up my hand to keep it from falling on my face. A handful of servers witness this including our's. She quickly grabbed our plates and told us we're moving inside ASAP. We were seated promptly indoors and I was given ice and offered pain medicine for my hand. I'm thinking through all of this "Man, when will I be able to dig into my French toast???? *cries*".  Finally after getting situated we were able to fully enjoy our food. The puff pastry on my plate was amazingly pooffy and the sunny side up egg was on point. The gravy wasn't bad but I felt like it could use an extra something to make it special. The hash browns had the perfect crispy to soft texture ratio too. But honestly none of that really mattered after biting into the French toast. The warm mascarpone sandwiched between the perfectly toasted bread was outstanding. The caramel sauce on top was by far my favorite thing out of everything. You don't need syrup for this masterpiece of a dish! My mom loved her Bene  although wished the eggs were a bit more runny. I tried her pancakes and again you don't need syrup for them either. They were light and almost melted in your mouth. Probably the best pancakes I've ever had, yum!   My overall experience here wasn't so great because of the rain. But the manager and our server handled it well. The manager covered our check and followed up the next day to make sure I was okay. The food though, was totally on point for me! I for sure will be back, just not on a rainy day, haha ^^;;

LmiU4sblh1BK0hr4gWOAXw.text: Wether its the snooze in San Diego or Phoenix the food is consistently good with great service.   Eggs Benedict done numerous ways and you can mix and match.   They have good hashes and great sweet things too.

I ordered half of the Benny Goodman and half of the Winter Benny, both were amazing. Adrienne told me about their pancake of the day (which was Samoa) I didn't think I could eat all of that food, so I didn't order one. She was so sweet and sent out a small one to try on the house! awb8bn409yxDwUzo_nOcCQ.text: Awesome staff, amazing food. We need one in Tucson!! I've never waited so long or been so happy I did. Of course it was Mother's Day so waiting was absolutely expected! Not typically a "sweet breakfast" kind of person but their blueberry danish pancake was just the right amount of sweet and something I would absolutely go back for. However, the real surprise was the breakfast pot pie. Incredible. I thought no way would this be good but I tried it and I will never be the same.

n_5Mz1BVGA0RmMBSW0v9Ww.text: Came here and had breakfast on a turnaround trip with my sister and it was by far one of the best places I've ever had breakfast. They give you free coffee while you wait and waiters circle around while you wait for your table asking you if you need anything from the bar. Five stars all the way

8VacmOZCkk48hh3dUqImdw.text: Went here recently for the first time and I. Will. Be. Back! Loved my waitress and the positive, energetic vibes! The food was FANTASTIC! Portion sizes made me forget about portion control, haha!  The drinks are awesome and well thought out as well... I never thought to have tequila with breakfast until i came here and it was worth it!  My group had a blast and loved the service and food! 10/10 would recommend. It's worth the wait on a busy day!

1tpzBOyLSjQ_gmRA0qF9vQ.text: I've eaten here a number of times since it opened and found the service to be great and the belly bacon always delicious. The one thing that always bugged me though is I've always hated the hash browns molded into a tour. Well today, while doing breakfast with some friends, the waiter let us know we could get the hash browns mashed down and fried crispy. i didn't get any but some of my friends did and they are everything a breakfast hash brown should be, flattened out and crispy all over. I asked if this was a new thing and the wait person told me no, it was always available and not listed so you have to ask for it.  Well Snooze, knowing that I can get my hash browns the way I want them kicks you up a star. In addition, it was my first time eating at the outside tables and wow, it was so nice outside, what a great way to start the day.

RN6DETZeXPS5eBhokEM2SQ.text: Went to snooze for the second time Friday (first at this location). I was told our wait would be 20-25 minutes, but only took 15. The staff were friendly and attentive, and my meal was perfect.

xr8EPfbhGPpg80j56ChMoA.text: The food is good. The service however is slow and some of the waiters are rude. Also, if you're allergic to bees, don't come. There's bees crawling and flying around everywhere. I brought this up to the manager Miriam and she made up for it all; she deserves a raise.

d03Cthn_UF5TNOF0aJU-GA.text: Snooze is really great! I'm traveling for work and I was looking for a good breakfast place and this was closest to my hotel. My server was awesome and food came out FAST! And it was hot! I ordered what my server suggested and I was not let down!

uX3U-i2tvWGasHhrMxKalw.text: Loved the decor, music, and food! The service was great. My family and I just flew in from a red eye... We were starving! So luckily they popped up on yelp for an early morning breakfast. I had the sweet potato pancake, which was perfect. It was too sweet.

1sDD8DD3UpNayXMN9hv4yQ.text: I get the same thing every time pineapple upside down pancakes! Pancakes are a good size so unless you want a side you won't need one to be full. I've had bites of other items on the menu and everything is pretty good. Hash browns are very oniony just a heads up. I prefer the Gilbert location as it is less busy. Also they do not take reservations regardless of the situation. I wanted to have my birthday brunch here but they wouldn't allow me to reserve seating for 9 people as they said their seating is "first come first served".

uoR4_0p0B6olOUaHEvxXiA.text: Fantastic service and Amazing food. Order the spring frittata if you get a chance, you wont be dissapointed.

JFoSf5fLg2P8nQEzXadprg.text: The spicy bloody Marys are highly recommended. We were a group of 10 and even though we came on a crowded Saturday afternoon the crew was able to host us in 15 mins.    The food was great. Lot of veggie options ( if you can eat eggs). The drinks were well mixed. We had to wait a little for our food, but the staff was very friendly. Considering we were 10 people the wait time was warranted.   Highly recommend the place. Especially for groups.

jrkGsFqmIS-XlFyBNRRe-Q.text: Reilly, our server was super fun and awesome to our table

oNBGIoE7sLntO8nMHZFEvA.text: Same great food as their other location.  Wasn't happy that there was no wait however it was a Friday with ASU on summer break.  I would imagine I wont be going back to this location when school is in seesion.  Also parking is more difficult here. The location at the Town and Country has plenty of free parking.

jSF-oLhueFjwZBf7lNhXDQ.text: Fun retro decor. All of the pancakes are great. The pineapple pancakes are especially superb. Friendly staff. Excellent service. Will return whenever we are in Tempe.

J0E8tMcocDbSpZzrGNPndA.text: One of my favorite new brunch spots! Unfortunately, it's always packed (both this location and the one in Gilbert), but that's a good thing :) Amazing food, amazing mimosas! The people at both locations are awesome, too. If you get there early, you'll be in and out. But pretty much anytime after 8am, expect a long (but well worth it) wait.

Aom5ZR-J-rW01xbIOOflrw.text: I went in with my girlfriend earlier this week at 7am. They open at 6:30am. There were at least 10 servers on the clock and maybe 3 tables other than us. The service was pretty bad. We got sat in the area where the bartender served us. Not sure why but no big deal. We quickly ordered because I had to get to the airport. The staff was very busy rolling silverware, eating their own breakfasts, hanging out by the coffee station talking about their last nights experiences, laughing, having a great time. We however waited a very long time for our food. I asked the manager if he could check on it because it was taking so long, he went in the back and the food came right out... hmm. He did not come back over and ask if everything was ok or apologize. Actually no-one said anything about it. Our server was not at all attentive once we got our food and didn't thank us when she brought the check. No one said a word to us when we were leaving. The food was good but we definitely did not feel welcome and if you have anywhere to be don't go early during the week. They are more concerned about customers coming in later and chatting about their personal lives.

MW1KmQhQStjKgkwmfnmgxQ.text: This place rescued what was a horrible father's day and turned it into a awesome day.  The Eggs Benedict was awesome, the bloody mary was delicious (extra spicy).  The kids loved their dishes and my wife finally settled on the strawberry pancakes, which she loved.  We will definitely be back for more.

yIV137RI5lA2sA0JRY1nbg.text: Ok, this place STARTS off with FREE coffee while you wait for your table!  Once we sat down, the staff was great!!  The menu has more than enough interesting options!  (not just the usual stuff).  I had the  French Toast and my girl friends had the Breakfast pot pie.  Both were delicious!  The music was great! Our waitress was Julia, I believe, she was wonderful but if you needed something, like ICE, the others jumped right in.  I say ICE because, while it was pretty sitting outside, even under an umbrella, it was HOT!  It's AZ in June, needed ice to cool off our skin...OUT DOOR MISTERS, FANS WOULD REALLY HELP!!  Postinos next door has them. They make a BIG difference in enjoying your meal.  Corp. in Colorado says its not policy or necessary.  IT'S AZ ! BETW MAY - SEPT. , ITS NECESSARY!!  Let Corp. know that it makes a big difference!  I will definitely go back, I'm hoping I don't have to wait until Oct to do so. Renee McCray,  Gilbert, AZ

yplqdlXAPlFMEPq62Rk4Sg.text: Amazing breakfast. Had the green chili Benny and the pancake flight. Pineapple upside down pancakes are unreal. Beau is an amazing server and this is a fantastic location. 5 stars.

8wgh7LPifQCmeAV4Ceb0Og.text: Decor: A  Food:C+ Service: B+   I had been hearing positive things about Snooze for a while, so I thought it was time to give the place a try. My friend and I arrived there at 1:30ish on a Sunday afternoon, about an hour before closing so we were sat immediately. Service was prompt and friendly, no complaints there. I immediately noticed the fun decor they used for the inside, I really enjoyed the retro/60s vibe they had going on. They had a fairly wide selection on their menu, which I appreciated, there were vegan/ gluten free option.s The food came out at an average speed, I got the corned beef hash, my friend had pancakes of sorts. I was fairly unimpressed by the corned beef hash, it was fairly unoriginal. The beef was masked by the potatoes, and the portion was super small. My friend raved about her pancakes though, so they were able to make up for it there. I would return, but I definitely wouldn't order the hash again.

5RfV1MLs94V8p0eJ7yQmcQ.text: My boss took me here for lunch.  The service was fast and friendly.  The food was awesome.  The hash browns freaked me out a bit when they came molded in a little dome shape.  Overall the food was good.  It was really filling.  Unfortunately not enough for leftovers.  Another one of those places I wish was open all day.

qgYAipDu0HZHBxfJaDzGlw.text: The food at this place is really good.  However, the service is horrible.  I was so excited to eat here with my girls, and was pretty disappointed.  We waited about 15 minutes to put in our drink order, and then didn't get our drinks for over 30 minutes.  We asked the waiter if we could order our food (after about 20 minutes) and he said the bar was backed up (even though a table that sat after us already had theirs).  My friend who was pregnant and about to eat her arm ordered orange juice and when the waiter brought our mimosas, I told him she didn't get her juice and he acted annoyed with me.  I get that everyone has a bad day, but he never apologized for our wait (our food took a while too).  I have told this story to a few other people and they said that's the restaurants MO.  They are known for bad service?  I am usually not one to write bad reviews, but I thought the owners might want to know.   **Side-note: if you order the breakfast burrito, do not order the green sauce unless you like super spicy food!  Might put an asterisk next to this item for spicy.  Just my two cents.

NXdP-niq8gfbv6JkktWvtw.text: Food is really delicious, but be prepared to wait, especially on the weekends. My husband and I biked by one day and decided to get brunch. Coffee was great and they have lots of fun breakfast drinks. It took a while for food to come, but it was worth it. We had a great time sitting outside drinking coffee and watching people go by. Have been back several times since then.

2pcKdn7rBfcRDy13PijLyg.text: I don't even like pancakes. The only time I ever have them is if people say, "you have to try these". The best pancakes I have ever had is Boots and Kimos in hawaii. These pineapple pancakes are ridiculously good. I think we have a tie. The place is clean and swanky. No doubt, this place is a keeper.

h4lTPUkdA3CMjEH2_s2aRQ.text: ONCE WAS ENOUGH.....My wife and I had been here once, the service was slow and it took 25min. for our food to get to the table. The food was good , and the place was packed. on our second visit there may have been 20 customers in the place and just as many staff. The girl who seated us threw 2 menus on the table and walked off. 16 min. later nobody had taken our drink orders or said a word to us. The server was playing with a customers dog. we left and will never return. Hipsters may love this joint and the trendy setting , Snooze and Hipsters have one thing in common ALL SHOW AND NO GO.

W_Ivg1qjcO31pnbXv9NGow.text: Just ok. So loud inside, we couldn't even hear the host. We sat outside, which was wonderful. Waitstaff Stacy was terrific. Gourmet prices but food was not. I ordered huevos rancheros (suppose to come w/3 eggs but only 1 was served). Egg was runny (I asked for medium). Each fresh vegetable that you ask for is an additional 75 cents for a serving that is about a tablespoon. Beans tasted like taco bell's. Manager deducted $3 for the missing eggs but bill was still $30 for 2 of us. Perhaps I am too picky, but I was not impressed. I will not return.

9Sl11pmjc6fcFJ1l11fSsg.text: So happy that snooze has opened up within walking distance! I love this place... Sometimes the wait can be a little bit long but they have coffee for you to sip while you wait so I don't mind :) service has always been great and I haven't tried anything on the menu that I don't like yet.

ECNwYpL3DDxHxS5KhuwIQA.text: Delicious. I'm a lover of breakfast and they do it right. Good portion size, great variety, vegan/vegetarian options and they always ask if I was the rest of my coffee to go as I'm signing my check! Just love the idea of that.

_aQ9_M-vMPnN5KX4Ub9kXQ.text: The atmosphere was great and our server was awesome, but the wait was long and the food was really only decent.  I was expecting higher quality and more flavor.  I ordered the corn beef hash with poached eggs.  The hash came out blackened and bland.  The poached eggs were hard cooked rather than runny - the server brought me the correctly cooked eggs very quickly - props to her!  Like Jensen M who wrote a review on the same day, our wait was really long, not just the wait to be seated, but the wait for our food.  We waited more than 45 minutes just for the food.  The manager stopped by to thank us for being patient.  He said he had been keeping an eye on us.  That was cool. I could tell he had been "keeping an eye" on most of the tables in the restaurant as we all were waiting a really long time for our food.  I have worked in a restaurant and understand that some days are difficult, especially during the first month of being open.  I would try the place again.  I definitely would come back for the chai!

hKrdnppU7XFY5zpdYHApbA.text: Snooze is good. It's in a really hip area just east of downtown Tempe across from ASU that is almost like a small "Mill Avenue".  The restaurant (and the one right next door) are in  a converted original ASU building so there is cool architecture with lots of exposed brick. It's literally right behind Mona Aquatic Center (think ASU swim meets) and occasionally you'll see high divers practicing right behind the building.   Eat there on a morning when it's good to eat outside. That's the best experience. Nice waiters and well informed. Food is good and not just traditional bacon and eggs. Very attractive crowd at breakfast though you may find a long wait during really popular times on a Saturday or Sunday morning..

EQQe7E6eVn4Sz_gyHDRRFQ.text: It was really good except the strawberries that came with my Omg! Frenchtoast tasted like meat was on them (probably cut with the same knife they use for meat). Other than that it was good service and my friend was completely satisfied with his pear pancakes we both couldn't finish and came in starving.

odpkdSeNHAl1qjSM5E1lBQ.text: This place is so cute. The food was unique and exciting and the atmosphere is even better. Spencer took care of us and she was amazing! She was very attentive and made sure we got all of our orders just the way we wanted them. She even sent over a gluten free pineapple pancake for me on the house! This was totally unexpected because I didn't mention my allergy but she  noticed I specified corn tortillas instead of flour. The pancake was divine and I was so appreciative of her doing that. After dining at many other breakfast locations in the Phoenix area, Snooze is by far the most exceptional in accommodating their guests and I will definitely be back soon!

qJ2Eq-KEkuOI5agjZVninQ.text: This place is awesome!!! The details in the decor are bright and energizing (perfect for morning time) and the food is awesome!! Our server Andrea was super sweet and even gave us a complimentary appetizer since it was our first time here! I'd definitely come back if I lived out here!!!

UtYp6Pa8DrEuam16J2-DXQ.text: Coffee. Donut. Pancakes. Together in one marvelous dish. Breakfast is my favorite meal, so I have high standards, and this place met every one of them. Not only is it located in a trendy area near ASU, but the whole place is well-branded with their logo on everything. They had coffee available while you wait for a table. At 10AM on a Saturday, we only had to wait 15 minutes for a table for 3. The coffee and donut pancakes were amazing -- made with Granny Smith apples and served with a coffee cream to be used like syrup. My sister got a breakfast sandwich on a pretzel bun, which was unique and good. Their hash brown were also really good. Very friendly service! Highly recommended.

nLKO_I2tiNMy-xCUk6hq_g.text: Amazing food, hands-down.  Service...amazing!  Atmosphere.....if you have piercings, tattoos, unshaved arm pits (Girls), the latest Hemp clothing fashion....you will love to eat or work here.

-cps9RXwqo4RrEP4MJhnjA.text: Snooze is a decent place to go for brunch if you don't mind splurging around $30 - $40 for two people. This is one of those restaurants I'll go to if I have the extra cash for a every-few-months treat. They have a laid back, somewhat retro atmosphere. Waits are never too long.   Their pancakes are fluffy with a variety of new, interesting flavors to choose from. I tried the Blueberry Danish  and a couple of others, although the Blueberry Danish sticks out in my mind the most. Sweet blueberries and tart lemon actually compliment each other very nicely.   I'm also not a fan of overly-dressed up hash browns (Snooze's include onions and spices which can be somewhat overwhelming, if I remember correctly. Honestly, it could have just been the day we went.). That's not to say that their hash browns are bad (they definitely aren't!), I'm just more of a purist when it comes to my potatoes. Give me salt and pepper.   I'd say give Snooze a visit at least once to try their unique menu and come to your own conclusion.

jabGgq9c2Wy4yaKlsYi9JA.text: The food was really yummy and the restaurant was really cute. However the bacon had a odd taste which was a little disappointing.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. We had a 3 eggs and side of bacon and bela-bela... The bacon wasn&#39;t good! I give it 2 out of 10! Everything else was yummy!!

wv_cVTJltX61-Rne0vAgvw.text: Breakfast was delicious I will return in a heartbeat  I dined in twice the whole weekend.

Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States

bLLxPs8xAVDudJ3Xb_-_jw.text: Avoid the long lines everybody is talking about and go on a weekday.  Even on a weekday (Thur @ 9AM) to be exact, inside was already full but outside was empty - so no wait at all, and with the nice warm Tempe winter weather, I was perfectly happy to be outside with my sunglasses and a heat lamp on.   Others in my party ordered americanos or other fancy coffee from the barrista (which I am normally all about) but I just got their house coffee, which was great. But I am partial to just getting drip coffee when I do brunch.  I got their breakfast tacos (highly recommend) + bacon on top.  Others in my party got the corned beef hash, one of the benedicts with salmon, and the 3-egg farm style plate, everybody was happy with their meal.

xsXH4__x9yLb3MALsWOQMw.text: The food here is always awesome but my review is regarding the service that was provided. We came on a Sunday morning so of course, it was busy. The hostess told me it would be about 20-25 minutes but we only waited for 5 mintues which was a great. When we sat down, our awesome waitress, Kylie, took our order. Kylie was nothing short of a great person in general but also the best waitress we've ever had. She was ontop of everything and had a great personality. My family and i agreed that we will now always request her as our waitress! So to the manager of Snooze, you should definitely offer a life time supply of pinnaple pancakes and a beer on the house for Kylie for her exceptional service!

G4f2P4AK6hA2GU0nhOTICA.text: Funny, I've gone to the place next door all the time, avoiding the crowd and wait. Now I understand why snooze is always busy. I ordered the bene duo (Verde and bella); so good. I'm a bene connoisseur and I absolutely loved the southwestern take, so the Verde was my fave. Everything was tasty and flavorful. Hubby got the spuds deluxe. We both cleaned our plates. The only negative I have is that the music was a little too loud, as it often is at these modern hipster joints. I like being able to have a conversation with my meal companions and I kept having to ask the hubby to repeat himself. Still I enjoyed the food, the service was excellent and it was a pleasant overall experience. Already planning to invite friends here for brunch... Soon.

dUdMx6bSHrtm4UpuBJWLqw.text: Great breakfast menu, awesome location. Ordered  3 egg omelet with three fillings. Their cop of coffee is like a small vase, you probably won't ask for a refill.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Fall greens.. Delicious

UHfY4QeBUSYG3cY3KDf8OQ.text: I get that every restaurant needs a re-vamp and I'm usually all for it. But this visit to Snooze involved our food taking over a half an hour to be ready, a cricket falling from the ceiling narrowly missing my mimosa, our food being cold, and finding out that they changed the Bloody Mary mix for the gazpacho Bloody Mary, which we came for today specifically for my boyfriend's birthday (which the bartender failed to acknowledge when checking our IDs). The bartenders/food Runner's are sweet as always. This is just not what Snooze used to be and I'm pretty disappointed that we chose to come here today for a birthday celebration. It may be a while, if ever, that we return.

GHX8DcP823uWHAgz19e63w.text: Found a hair in my omelette so they brought me a new one. Found another hair and they didn't even acknowledge it, they said it was a fuzz. The person I was with found a hair in his orange juice. Definitely will not come again.

IxgKWFZE0WhKj4mHUc74Rg.text: Visited on a Sunday morning and (as expected) was very busy. Since our wait was long the restaurant gave us some delicious spicy chai teas on the house! The Snooze Breakfast Burrito was more than enough food - with a green chile sauce that had spectacular flavor. Great atmosphere for a breakfast/brunch in Tempe!

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Spicy chai tea
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Snooze Breakfast Burrito

Kyng-sqwpb7Gs2v0oHN-oA.text: My favorite breakfast place in AZ! Phenomenal service, everyone is happy to be there, delicious food, seriously there are no better pancakes in the world, I'm convinced!   Make sure to ask what the pancake of the day is! Oh and sinful pancake (not on the menu) is my absolute fav. It's like a cinnamon roll pancake with bacon bits on top. Yum, so good! Oh and so many mimosa options. If you like to brunch so hard, you will find no better place. :)

SObGTUGxYAQu4QQEo3HpSA.text: Excellent service and food! Awesome atmosphere. Great for gluten dietary restrictions and very knowledgeable about cross-contamination. My Celiac daughter had the gluten free kids' French toast and loved it. They also have her a GF chocolate chip pancake to sample. Excellent find!

K9XtNQGVG4dNFJX0I_9lcQ.text: We have eaten here twice now and been blown away each time. The Benedict dishes are outstanding, and I like the way you can try two as a meal. You can do a variety-of-an-item-option for the pancakes as well... and it's a good thing with choices like Sweet Potato, Blueberry Danish and Peach Pie Pancakes (say that 5 times fast!) This past visit, we had the Pineapple Upside Down Pancake, and oh. my. god. The coffee is high quality... and I'm a bit of a coffee snob. We enjoyed reading the story about it on the nifty tri-fold drink menu gracing each table, though I was so involved with that ridiculous pancake, I've forgotten where they buy it from. Great stuff all around.

IOaZMISI6o0KlSqAtxNiXA.text: Super busy, full of kids, loud music, the servers did not fill up my coffee or water... I also paid EIGHT, yes eight, dollars for a bowl of quinoa and oatmeal. I expected a large bowl and honestly it was the equivalent of one of those oatmeal packets.  I have actually been to other Snooze locations, this fell to the bottom of that list pretty quickly.

hPM7_mqoPNBDR270UcfOaA.text: Delicious! We shared a blueberry pancake prior to getting two eggs benedict (option to have two different types). We were able to try 4/6 different eggs benedicts and they were all amazing. We will definitely be visiting this place again. Staff were friendly. Only downside is the wait but it was worth it!

S1qrF8ij3186i8l4MlrGuQ.text: Very good service, great food, the coffee was a little too light. The wait was way too long.

46iJ2ybq6EghCdpx3YlRMg.text: Well, I'm sick. Walked out of the restaurant 10 minutes ago after eating maybe one eighth of my "Ham Benedict III" and I am physically sick. And that's literally not even the only bad part of the experience that I am taking a break from puking right now to write about. I want to make clear that the coffee is decent though, I love a good iced mocha from here, and the barista is doing a good job in the midst of a landfill.  So the waiter literally walked up to us and just stood there and smiled until one of us at the table said, "Hey how is it going?". One of the creepiest waiters ever, and then he said, "Do you want to hear about our pancake?", we replied with, "Sure" and then the guy did not even know what was in the pancake.  Food comes out and nothing better happens. My plate literally smelled like body odor, I don't know if it's just the hollandaise or what, but it was repulsive. Then we don't see the guy forever and then when he comes back and no one has eaten anything but some hash browns, he says, "Do you guys need a box?". Our cards are already out and on the table, come on dude no we want to get out of here before we actually puke on the floor.  I have had bad experiences here before with under cooked eggs and just weird guy servers who sit down next to you to take your order but it's just so close to home and school that I keep finding myself going there out of convenience but never again, not after being sick for food that is not even appetizing.  Bottom line is, the food is not good, the service is trash, there is almost always a ridiculous wait which still perplexes me, I would not recommend this place to any one, and honestly, if you don't offer Frank's Red Hot as one of your hot sauces you are already a garbage establishment.  Snooze, when you read this, please leave this location so something better can come in and use the spot. Thanks for nothing.

wVEW1lyS_Snm3WVKgYlvVQ.text: Unique menu items.  Fun decor with good service.  We really enjoyed this restaurant.  Loved the potatoes, the pancakes and the omelette.  Good juice and coffee.  Everything was very fresh, and you could really tell.  We will return, although not with the kids, they can go to Denny's!

HlrTZ2RdaTxnG9LcqYbnQA.text: Great service! AMAZING pancakes! Whenever I revisit Phoenix, I'll have to come back and grab a bite here. There was quite a wait, but the dining experience made the wait worth it. Definitely recommend!

oQaQbF_CqsvOH-0KaOnp3g.text: Love the atmosphere of Snooze, the great attitude of the hospitality staff, the food and music. I will come here as often as I get back into town.

0zbrvoMup54wcGMjvbhLiQ.text: Great find - cool spot by ASU (though the area was crawling with hipsters and basics - one dude in particular was trying waaaaayyyy too hard).  Anyway, cool retro-atomic interior (including coat/hat racks) - love it.  On to what's important.  Coffee - blah blah single source blah backpacking blah south america whatever - good coffee in a big mug with prompt refills - that's all that matters!   We got a pretty good cross section of the breakfast menu among our party - a flight of pancakes (one blueberry, one sweet potato and one OMG French Toast - all very good, but the OMG French Toast was the winner), a Chilaquiles Benedict, another spicy Benedict, a combo of Sweet Potato pancake and OMG French Toast, a

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Chilaquiles Benedict
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Flight of Pancakes with blueberry, OMG French Toast and Sweet Potato (all done gluten free)
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Corned beef hash

UPD5xC7g4L651jg57IgsKQ.text: Best breakfast in the entire 50 states. If I see there is a Snooze near, that is the breakfast for me. Coffee, selection, and pancakes cannot be beat. You will never be disappointed with Snooze.

2GKJvPidZYaVFdcJUIPJAg.text: Great breakfast spot, reasonable prices and very good food. Really big portions, so choose carefully

tXRWwh03Djcxhe_SCag2jQ.text: Excellent chow, friendly/efficient service, bright and airy setting make for a worthy breakfast experience.  Place was busy on a Friday at 830: 10 minute wait on a table.  We opted for the counter, where the service was attentive, even though our server Tori was filling drink orders non-stop. She made sure we got everything we needed, and she topped it off w/ some tasty beverages, my BMary included.  I had scrambled eggs, hash browns and sausage pattie. Menu says 3 eggs, though the serving looked more like 2. Hash browns were tasty, but not as crispy as iike them, and the sausage was alright.  I added pico de gallo to my plate, and it balanced the flavors for me instantly. The rest of the family enjoyed their breakfasts, the pancakes and bfast tacos very well received, and we all left satisfied. I'll return!  Cheers! RS

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Triumvirate against the hangover

dVz-SU6bsFMNfoqdn_d7bw.text: Our company headquarters in Tempe so I'm here often for work. This is always my "go to" place to grab breakfast and do some work before heading into the office. I assume everything on their menu is fantastic but I never get anything but the Benedict's at Snooze...they're fantastic. The only thing I have them do different than normal is spread out the hashbrowns so they cook more thoroughly instead of the puck they normally come out in. Great spot here...you won't go wrong.

NHMS74Lc5t2AbsxyIa8L4A.text: Other than the fact that I feel like every time I'm there I am battling a fly or a bee while I'm trying to eat, it is so yummy! The wait is a bit long for my taste and some of the staff act like they are doing you a favor by allowing us to wait. Good thing it's so delicious lol

pBVNziGVAR31Y0NIOJT5uw.text: Holy deliciousness. I came here for the breakfast pot pie, and was sold on the pancakes and cocktails. Let me back up... the breakfast pot pie was good, but I wouldn't say it was 'great'. There was nothing wrong with it, it just had a few spices that don't match my tastes. Loved that it was in a puff pastry though, and that you get to choose the type of egg you want on top! Also, major bonus points at Snooze for being able to swap out different sides to customize your dish without it impacting the price- probably the best part about Snooze as a whole. I really wanted corned beef hash (which was A-MAZING) so I subbed out the regular hash browns for that instead.  Anyways, THE PANCAKES. I got a single blueberry danish pancake as a side to my pot pie, and oh my gosh I wish I had gotten a full stack. Normally, when you get sweetly flavored pancakes, they are super, supppppper sweet - you can hardly taste the pancake underneath. This was not the case at all at Snooze. This was the fluffiest, tastiest buttermilk pancake with a delicious light and sweet lemon cream cheese filling. The streusel, sweet cream, and blueberry topping are lightly drizzled over the top. No overkill at all - the perfect light enhancement to the delicious buttermilk of the pancake.  For beverage, if you don't get the mountain mule, you are severely missing out. This might have been the best breakfast cocktail I've ever had in my life, and I'm a big fan of brunch, so thats saying A LOT.  I will DEFINITELY be making Snooze a regular in my brunch rotation... I may even go back next weekend.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Breakfast pot pie, sub corned beef hash for regular hash.
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Blueberry Danish Pancake - O.M.G

P0BHQs6tGxd0fNd-w5_8KA.text: Outstanding coffee. Delicious food. Extremely good service. Busy Friday morning but server made time to recommend her favorites and refill our table's iced tea and coffee. Halfway through a delicious breakfast of lox, goat cheese and cress, a server brought over a pancake. On the house. Pineapple Upside Downcake. Readers, this was properly amazing. Not too sweet, but the right combo of rich and fruity. Seriously, possibly the best pancake we've ever had (and not made, either).

CIPMpJCJaV562H4G8tUXnw.text: The food is SO good. This is honestly the best breakfast place I've ever been to. It can be a bit of a wait if you go at certain times, but it's totally worth it. Also, the portions are very big, I always take some food home with me. Even if you're extremely hungry coming in, you'll always leave satisfied because they give you a lot of food and it's all very filling. I love the spicy chai tea, the pancakes (the sweet potato and the sweet cannoli ones are especially good), and the eggs Benedict and hash browns are also fantastic. You really can't go wrong here.

P_6I8IYsNzby7v73I-nJUQ.text: We were sat quickly, but told there would be a wait. Hostess was fantastic and friendly. Food was great. Fast service. Great place for breakfast. Trendy but not too expensive. I can see why this would be popular with local collage students.

zZaIk_L3MWDfL4xZanhuGA.text: I didn't use any salt, pepper or hot sauce on anything, it was all that delicious. With their intriguing and diverse menu, not to mention the paradoxical vintage yet modern ambiance, I'll be eating at Snooze a lot more often.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Side of Soyrizo. Yummy!!
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Reuben. Aaaamaaaazing!!!

fe6iURLxm36WAhJ8ehBveQ.text: Our server was awesome. Blonde really chill relaxed guy. But honestly y'all need to bring back the salmon Benedict or I'll never get over it. That is the only reason for four stars. Otherwise this place is the greatest brunch place of all time. You can't have a bad meal here. Please do the public a service and give us back the salmon Benny!

BH0EdamAwU32b-XW6Q2vEw.text: Amazing food and drinks! Causal atmosphere from the people to the food. The Tempe location is more laid back and attentive service over the Scottsdsle location.

Kht7Hs6QuaCxaXDa70C8Dw.text: The food is delicious, very unique and very rich ingredients that create a great combination. The staff is ok. The biggest complaint is the wait is so long and the food is a little pricey.

0Wt0fpf6fqXrZmDcFdGKMg.text: Great spiked apple cider. I was trying to decide what drink I wanted but wasn't really sold talking to the waitress, but I'm glad I decided to get it. I also got the Bravocado and it was good. I'd get it again although I wasn't that keen on the tomato stuff. Their berries were also really sweet

X9y49Flux6iY6QxUv1ImSA.text: What a great place! The food was amazing but the service lacked a bit.  The portions were just the right size and you could taste the flavor in every single bite. The patio was pretty full but it was a nice day. Overall, very satisfied and we will be back

DQ_TVS493YpRSJQj6Tq62Q.text: My boyfriend and I ate breakfast here this morning and would 10/10 recommend to this place to anyone. With breakfast being my favorite meal, I can be a tough critic, but this place had not only great food, but great service as well. Our waitress was extremely polite and attentive and constantly checked in to make sure we were being taken care of. For my beverage I got a Bloody Mary and boy was it good! For breakfast I got the Bravacado Toast which was tasty, but it had a little too much on it for my liking (I should have read the menu better). My boyfriend had The Classic and he actually isn't a huge fan of eggs, but he said it was really good! Overall, if you're looking for an awesome breakfast place check out Snooze.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States

kchVb_-17_rPQJdl0IOAlQ.text: Wow! Phenomenal. Fantastic. All of those amazing words can't begin to describe this place. When I read my friend Andrew's review of this place and in his words, "every town has a "best brunch spot" and this may very well be Phoenix(area)'s", I was super excited to find out that this place was within walking distance from my hotel, Tempe Mission Palms.   When we walked in, we immediately felt old. Everyone inside was like 25 or younger. Oh well, I didn't feel out of place. The hostess and the waitress were super nice. Our waitress even brought us out a "gift", a pineapple upside down pancake. Thank you, Abbie. Now our trip complete. My friend doesn't usually eat breakfast, but she talked out this meal for hours.   They have several morning drinks available, including three versions of bloody marys. I played it safe and stuck with the basic one which was $.75 less anyways. For my meal, I ordered the Snooze breakfast burrito and requested the sauce and pico on the side. It was stuffed with scrambled eggs, hash browns, and black beans and was excellent. I'd say it was the best breakfast burrito I've ever had. I was hesitant in ordering it because of the potatoes, but they weren't greasy at all. My friend ordered The Snooze Classic which included farm fresh cage-free eggs cooked any style and a choice of ham, bacon, sausage, chorizo, pulled pork, chicken sausage or soyrizo, hash browns, choice of toast. She said that her entire experience was life-changing.   I agree this is "the" breakfast spot in the Phoenix area.

Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Bloody Mary

1rhzRdtaPBJdVaVQocd68w.text: This place is unbelievable. Whether you are a local or a tourist you'll enjoy your meal at Snooze. Our hotel concierge recommended "anything on the menu" and we were not disappointed. I started with the Bangkok Bloody Mary which I have to say is one of the best, most flavorful and interesting cocktails I've ever had. The Bangkok was served with some sort of yumminess (better than salt) sprinkled on the rim and pickled veggies on top. Of course I had a hard time ordering food because ever looked so amazing! I chose the pick any two of the eggs benedict and chose chili verde and steak and eggs. They were both very tasty and even better with the local hot sauce. I preferred the chili verde. The restaurant alone is a reason to come back to AZ. Outstanding food, location, and service. Indoor and outdoor dining options.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Eggs Benedict (Chili Verde &amp; Steak)
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Eggs Benedict detail
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Bangkok Bloody Mary

HmEYDoWI5Rmnovsh8qx3vg.text: This place is everything. Hard to pick what to eat. Ended up splitting a pancake flight and the chili verde eggs benny. Breakfast cocktails are a must.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Am Manhattan, Spicy Bloody, Dirty Drunken Chai

lSLf9gciguIS1rAiPhHI_A.text: Be prepared for a wait! But it's worth it and there is plenty of room to wait comfortably and the bathrooms are centrally located for easy access which was nice. The location is great and the ambiance and decor was great. Our server was noticeably overwhelmed and our service time was a bit long but we were visiting with friends so we're not rushing, don't come here in a hurry. The food was really good, and fresh tasting. There was a good variety. The pancakes were delicious, rich, but delicious. Definitely a place to try!

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States

gHdgJmc9ZbX268Ug0BWLEQ.text: It's really good in Ahwatukee or Old Town Scottsdale. In Tempe they burn my stuffed French toast every time and the employees spend way too much time huddled up chatting together than anything. Back when I used to serve we couldn't get away with that, there's always something that can be done besides congregating and making customers feel like a burden.

YicppIKxLBtZeCJ3M6SAvA.text: Great service, usually good food. If most of your menu is breakfast, then your hash browns should still be good at noon. They are what I recommended to my guests! Ours were uncooked and cold. Tables near us weren't eating theirs either.

m0k3mykBVRC29AOC-0XvAg.text: Hash browns are the best: super crispy top and bottom with soft shredded potatoes on the inside. Their Eggs Benedict menu is huge!! Get the Benny Duo and you get to pick two kinds. Amazing Bloody Mary menu as well. You can't go wrong with anything on the menu!

i50ZTPAHPwAuBErqu4VH7w.text: We came here for brunch on Saturday around 9. I would say the earlier you get here, the better . This place filled up quickly, but everyone seems as though they got sat pretty quickly  I started off with a cocktail of grapefruit juice, sparkling wine, and tequila. I can't remember the name of this drink, but it was pretty tasty and not super sweet. I then decided to get the Snooze Spuds Deluxe because it seemed to have everything else I wanted squeezed into one dish (potatoes, cheese, eggs, veggies, and meat). I added spinach, bacon, ham, and jack cheese to mine with over easy eggs. A few people ordered pancakes, so I got to try some of theirs.   My Spuds were delicious. They were very flavorful and filling. It was basically a mix of a hash, omelette, and over easy eggs. A perfect combination in my opinion. I also got to try the french toast (good, but not a fan of coconut) and the cinnamon bun pancake. Oh my god....that cinnamon bun pancake was so amazing. I only needed 1 pancake.   You're near the campus, so I'm guessing a lot of people working there were students, but they all were great and handled our large party very well. I will come back .

Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. French Toast
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Cinnamon roll pancake

0e05IxWw6-2DXLUJxcampw.text: Love this place.  My go to for breakfast with the wife.  Many tasty Benny's but I can never make it past their corn beef hash with poached eggs.  Hash is fresh and eggs always poached perfect.

MltzYVlIv8TD9tUB93bhGg.text: This place is popping for sure! Very modern vibe, great food and awesome staff. For sure recommend checking this place out. And oh yeah, try their Ham Benedict, so freaking goood!!!!

zc6eU2U25qpSwRGYJa_6rA.text: My wife and I ate here on the suggestion of another person. Definitely worth it, I had the shrimp and grits and the wife got the burrito for breakfast. More food than we could eat, burrito was huge. Everything tasted just right. Waiter was a bit creepy though, he wouldn't even look at the other person, just stared at one person each time he came over.

dcaqfP-8bT8AdNSY_tFTGw.text: Great food and a whole bunch of variety of options. This place never disappoints. Always expect wait time but it's well worth the wait!

cpz1JILfU0mWAG2_EGkfMA.text: Just had a mimosa with friends today but have eaten here in the past as well. The place is really nice and modern. This location is just off ASU campus as well as nearby to Mill Avenue; so there is plenty to see/do before or after grabbing a bite to eat (or a mimosa!)   The mimosa was pretty good. Standard I'd say and it came in a flute glass. The price, I thought, was a bit expensive but hey - I bought it anyway I guess.   All the food has been good here. My personal recommendation is the cinnamon roll pancakes!

iXMFXsKdnPVPKNsMCQrTuA.text: This was our first stop upon landing in Phoenix. We were tired and hungry and just desperate for a place to sit and eat. Usually, settling with the first place you find on Yelp out of desparation isn't too good an idea, but I am so glad we ended up here. It's in a prime location on the ASU strip and the restaurant atmosphere was a cute retro. The corned beef has was so delicious and filling, but the star of the show was the french toast. ORDER THE FRENCH TOAST!!! The only downside to this place is that now no other french toast will be good enough.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Corned Beef Hash and French Toast
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Mocha

MQEOyZIjIuMZffNUZ9pARg.text: I loved having breakfast here today. Everything tasted so fresh and had amazing flavor. I couldn't decide on what eggs Benedict I wanted so I ended up doing the duo. I can't remember the name. Total yelper faux pas I know. One was like the traditional eggs Benedict and the other had the cream cheese hollandaise with arugula and balsamic. I'm still drooling thinking about. While I was sitting there I started chatting with an employee about what pancake someone was eating nearby and he was so thoughtful he brought me one on the house. I haven't had customer service like that in a long time. It was the blueberry danish. I would definitely recommend that pancake that was fluffy and full of flavor. Thank you for a wonderful delicious way to start my day. I'll pay it forward somehow other than the large tip I left behind.

1UCuqwWE8vO0bQglI3xxtA.text: Breakfast burrito and classic breakfast. A lot of flavor packed into it. This place is right next to the college campus so it is a young and hip place. Packed on a Thursday morning. Their mimosa were different from your typical mimosa.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States

IiaUDJOtK4wXr6JIiTkJ8g.text: I love the Snooze AM on Camelback.  But this one ...   I ordered the Green Tom Bloody (Bloody Mary).  They use really cheap Vodka for this drink, which costs $8.75, and it gave me a splitting headache for hours until I took some detoxing agents.  Do not get this.  On top of it, the tomato juice used taste gross like it's been on the shelf for years.  The veggies they place on top of the drink don't taste fresh at all.  Ruined my Friday morning happy mood. 1-star.  I ordered the pancake flight which was pretty good.  4-stars.  The ambiance here is nice on a Friday morning and the temperatures have dropped so that it is nice outside.  Service seemed slow.  15 minutes to get my bloody mary drink.  25 minutes to get the pancakes.  10 minute wait on Friday morning at 10:30 AM.  Nice thing about this place is that they text you when your table is ready.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. pancake flight.  blackberry, pineapple, and blueberry pancakes.

v1BRmW-rPOCLr9cppEc6gQ.text: Such a cute diner! Right by ASU it can get pretty busy, but they try their best to squeeze you in within a decent amount of time. Really yummy eggs Benedict!

nXzXac-Ilw4D7wAz3yUR3A.text: A very delicious breakfast restaurant on Mill! The place is very vibrant and the service is fantastic. Everyone seems to be in a chipper, hearty mood which makes for a comfortable, enjoyable atmosphere to enjoy their great food! This is one of those places where you can order anything off the menu and be satisfied! However, my only complaint is the wait. We waited 50 minutes for a table. The food is good but not THAT good. However, I would return!

hKPKrnsCorjmBIPb-dsYrQ.text: Good food but the wait on Saturday at 09:30 was an hour. Totally annoying server: she had to be asked to refill a coffee, she acknowledges, walks away and returns empty handed. Worse, she sits down at the table with friends, scrolling thru photos on the friends phone.   Yeah, it's not worth the wait.

UYUZJZ1YRq0Yf0ZFya8iZA.text: Nom nom nom. We loved this place! Great food, so many options & great service. We ate here twice on our short trip to the area. The place was totally packed on Sunday, which makes sense. They got our number so they could text us when our table was ready, so we were able to walk around while we waited. When we were seated, I ordered the Spuds Deluxe with avocado and Soyrizo, which was awesome. I love that they offer vegetarian options! My mom ordered the classic breakfast and said it was great, especially the jam that comes with the toast. On visit number two, she went for the pancake flight (delicious) and I got the Straight Up French Toast. I loved the fresh berries and real maple syrup! We'll definitely be back!

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Spuds deluxe with avocado and Soyrizo
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Straight up Bloody Mary
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Straight up French toast and a side of hash browns

4SYqy5DFMjSBQXcjf33oqg.text: Mimosas are amazing but the lack of vegan options is very disappointing. Would definitely come more often if there were options for me to eat. But for now I'll just enjoy my mimosas.

iMiQobnCMYTPmueN_hPH-w.text: Amazing customer service! They have made every single time I've ate here memorable. Plus the food is to DIE FOR! (and I'm not even a breakfast person... but I'm always down to eat at Snooze)

d1oO42nMJ5YIV9Tfrvmb5Q.text: Oh my! Here visiting and so glad I ate here! Woohoo best breakfast hands down. I had the lox Benedict, I can't remember the name. Amazing. Must eat here.

9BWErYvVOK90EsH5XkusHg.text: Great breakfast/brunch spot! Nice location and seating options, and the staff here are super friendly and accommodating. Awesome choices for drinks, include a great little lineup of bloody Mary's. Absolutely one of my favorite places to enjoy a morning meal.

DQ7wTnQluxhlUGhvO62C0A.text: Love this place, when the wait is not too long but that tells you a bit about how good they is!!  I think it's one of the best Reuben sandwiches I have ever had so delicious!!! Also the pancakes and French toast is yummy, this breakfast place is amazing!!!!

1xG1fp2jwKMWS4V1Dvxnow.text: Everything in this place is good.  Pancakes are light and fluffy with a hint of authentic recipe added in the mix.

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Bar menu
Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Bar

lGbL8dS9TGZUgF39kYKB1Q.text: I always take pictures of my food but at snooze I straight up didn't have time the first time because it was so freaking delicious. I have since been at least a few times and have some more to say   I haven't seen anyone talking about their shrimp and grits but it's really good! Perfectly spicy. I'm saying that as someone from NOLA!   The hot chocolate is also delicious! Strong recommend!   The sweet potato pancake is a must! We have ordered it a la carte and it was worth the almost $5. I couldn't have 3 myself just because I can't handle that must sticky, thick sweet. The pancake itself has the perfect amount of sweet though. Sometimes we get it in the flight if we are really feeling ambitious. It goes well with the pineapple upside down!    I will say their hash browns really aren't something to call home about. It's the only part of the meal I felt we could've done without.   Service was good, prompt, kind. Seated outside which can sometimes be hazardous (they have bee problems like everywhere else in Tempe). It's a good place to take someone to Brunch if you want to seem hip.

c_7z1w0vAZU4h__n-FmR-g.text: This place is amazing because of the wait staff,  food, and atmosphere. It has a lively vibe and seems to be always filled with happy customers. I ordered the Shrimp and Grits dish which was more than I was expecting. Furthermore, while sitting outside we didn't have to wait long for our server to check on us.

38wCOL5K4J9E6e27ba-Auw.text: I've been to the other one in Gilbert, but this one is quite a different feel. I think it might habe to do with the location being on ASU's campus, so it's a bit "collegey". The decor is cute and classy but it definitely caters more to a college scene.  My friend at for breakfast at 8am and it was about 80% occupied for the indoor seating. No one was out on the patio seating area as yet because it was a tad too chilly still. By the time we left though, the line was out the door onto the sidewalk at almost 10am.  I ordered the Benny duo (one of each type of eggs benedict) with the Bella! Bella! Benny and the Chili Verde Benedict with pulled pork. So the chili sauced tortilla that they had as the "bread" for the Chili Verde Benedict was very different, but I wasn't too sold on it. It might be the texture or the corn tortilla flavor overpowering the rest of the benedict... it wasn't a hit for me. The hollandaise, egg and pulled pork though were pretty good. For the Bella! Bella! Benny, the slice of ciabata bread it came on was so thin and just underwhelming. The prosciutto, egg and hollandaise sauce again were spot on. But with how salty prosciutto is, I felt like there should be a more hearty piece/type of bread to balance out that natural saltiness of the prosciutto.   The meal came with hash browns which to me was the only perfect (for me) item on my plate. The outside brown and crisp on the outside, moist and cooked just right on the inside. My other complaint is that they neither have blue cheese dressing nor ranch dressing/dipping sauce, and those are my sauces of choice for potatoes (I don'tlike ketchup).  Another thing is Snooze changes their menu, but it always has a lot of similarities to the one before. It's like they remix items that are on the menu. They have a lot of great ideas and sometimes they're great (like their fall menu was) and sometimes they fall short - like the current menu.

QxnwvkNEx9LxLeRVsTXIeg.text: Snooze is a hipster breakfast spot located right by ASU. We visited on a Saturday and waited an hour to be seated. It's worth the wait.   The table ordered the deluxe Benedicts half steak and eggs and the other ham. The steak Benedict's is a must try. The meat was extremely tender and flavorful it was served with harsh browns and veggies. It's also topped with holiday sauce and green toppings that tasted like pesto. I wish I ordered just the steak. Instead of bread it's served with something else that's amazing. The ham Benedict was good too.  We also tried three pancakes the pineapple upside down, blueberries, and another one that tasted like amazing dessert. There small but man it's a great portion. Their version of small is the size of my hand.   Overall great breakfast spot but get ready for a wait.

bx2BQAGVqMRmMk8joltGOA.text: This place is absolutely fantastic. Came on a recommendation from a friend and I'm probably not going to add anything many other reviews on here have said. 5VXrxxzycjewZ3UCt3MTEg.text: Pretty nice place, well seasoned hash browns, but overall average food. English muffin tasted odd. Straws available upon request. It's cute they're trying to help save our home planet. I would return, but not hugely impressed.

Xb5GL6fMFo_miBcRIdyLag.text: After having been to Snooze AM in Tempe twice, my verdict is that it leaves much to be desired.  The first experience I had was absolutely horrible. We waited for about half an hour and were seated on the patio. Although the weather was okay, it got hot really quick since there was absolutely no shade. There were dogs on the patio which is fine, but what did not sit well with me was that the waiters were picking them up and then delivering food to tables. The dog that was at the table right next to ours was small & not trained as he kept peeing on the ground. Like I said, one of the waitresses kept picking him up & playing with him while serving tables. Complete turnoff!  On top of that, the food we got wasn't impressive. My date got the breakfast burrito & I got the omelette with spinach, mushrooms, & cheese. I ordered white bread and not once, but twice, our waitress brought me sourdough! We aren't pleased with any of it.  The second time I went, it was with a large group & we opted to get a table inside. The wait time was horribly long but we knew that would most likely be the case. The service was spot on. Our waitress was great in getting us everything we needed, kept our cups refilled, etc. The food was much better. I got the Benny Duo with the Bella! Bella! Benny and the Benny Goodman which came with hash browns. The Benny's were just okay - the Bella was better than the other one, but the prosciutto has a weird taste as did the salmon lox. Keep in mine their hash browns aren't of the crispy variety.  I will have to give it up for the pancakes that we received to share! The Pineapple Upside Down Pancake was one of the best things I did ever have! There were chunks of pineapple cooked inside the pancake which was topped with a vanilla sauce & cinnamon butter. I would highly recommend this!!! If you're a fan of peanut butter, try the peanut butter cup pancake! The flight is really sweet so if you're looking for something a little bit less sweet, try the French toast!  I think I'll be returning to Snooze for the pancakes and perhaps the French toast .. But probably not this location.

wyd2RFF49F6wJA17z7M0iQ.text: Been here twice so far with my boyfriend. Whenever we have time to get breakfast we always end up wanting to go here. It was super busy and the experience wasn't as great as I had that next Tuesday. I think it was just because it was so crowded. The great thing about this place is that they text you the link of their app. The app shows up exactly how many "parties" are ahead of you and what the estimated time of wait is. It's amazing! I wish more restaurants did this. Anyway, the second visit I got the Benny's. THEY LET YOU COMBINE BENNYS ON ONE PLATE! genius. I got the Bella Bella Benny and Benny goodman. The BENNYS also come with hash browns (you can ask them to make them crispy!!) Yum!! The coffee is also surprisingly light and amazing. I liked the regular coffee better than a mocha latte, which is saying something. I'll keep coming back but preferably during the week. Service is also EXCEPTIONAL. They are attentive and customer oriented. On the patio, they made sure the sun wasn't in my eyes. If you're also not satisfied with the food, they'll go above and beyond to make sure you had a positive experience.

g2IUy2_arfzKkaTevoeF9w.text: My heart was broken. Still bleeding, I found myself on a seven day sojourn in Denver. Looking to get lost for a while. Looking for a tourniquet. It was that trip, and the encouragement of a dear friend that opened my eyes to the beautifully unexpected marvel that is SNOOZE. I didn't know then that that experience would change my life, but what I did know was that the OMG French Toast, friendly faces, prompt service, and gallon of coffee were exactly what I needed after a loooong night trying to un-torture my past. I wandered aimlessly through the great city the next 6 days. I was a sponge. The gentle hum, the drugs, the fairer sex, the wind, steel butting against rock, all of it. Soaked it all in. They say the sponge has no nervous, digestive, or circulatory systems. I could relate that week. However, in a seven day stretch of desolate whimsy with no clear direction, I found one constant. SNOOZE. Sweet, savory, and made with pride. A game changer in the world of breakfast.     I returned home to Chicago. The scar was slow to heal, but my life would go on. Good days, bad days, days so uninspiring you can't even classify them, whatever. A rut was developing. I needed something new.     I settled in Scottsdale, AZ. I have no idea why, but here I was and I  found some fast friends. After what can only be described as one of the more epic nights in recorded drunken history a friend suggested we work off our hangovers at Snooze.     Wait....  What?  There's a Snooze here?  Are you fu**ing with me?   She was not. Once Google confirmed her story to be True, I ran out of the house as if it was on fire. I drove down to Tempe. Alone. I wanted this experience for myself. The whole 15 minute trip I fantasized about breakfast burritos, Bennys, pancakes, Micheladas, EVERYTHING! The car was floating. I was floating. I was about to be reunited with an old friend I thought I would only ever see in the city of Denver. I didn't want to pinch myself for fear of waking up.     I walked in. It was different. Not in a bad way. Just different. More open, airy, better lighting, a lot of Dr. Dog on the stereo. The smells were the same. The smiles were bigger. I liked it immediately. I sat down at the bar. Continuing to look around and soak it all in. I was a sponge again and all of the emotions of my lost week in Denver flooded back into my brain. There was pain, but there was more excitement. I was ready. I knew what I wanted.    This is when my life changed. Forever.   I haven't been to all of the Snooze's in the country, but I don't have to visit them all to tell you that Snooze Tempe has something the rest of them don't. Her name is Parker. The wild card. She's an X-factor the other locations could only dream of having. Shortly after sitting down she was right in front of me. I ordered coffee, and then it goes blank. I was lost. More like trapped. Trapped in the beautiful abyss of her eyes. I bet a thousand men have been told what the pancake of the day is, yet never truly heard the words coming out of her mouth. I gathered myself and continued to look around. Soaking everything in. I was studying the food of everyone around me, watching the staff interact, listening to the stories being told of last night. I never wanted it to end. It was pure magic, and in the center of it all was Parker and her smile that could make the world stop. I ate, we laughed, the music played, and eventually like all things do, it ended. I may never see Parker again, or eat the delicious tacos or pancakes at Snooze, but the beauty and warmth felt that morning changed me. Reinvigorated me. A meal at Snooze is not just a meal. It's an experience. I now realize that's what dragged me back there every morning in Denver, and will most likely make me return to SNOOZE TEMPE a lot more in the future.   Thank you Parker, and thank you Snooze. You woke something inside of me, and for that I'm eternally grateful.

J2TJXTnYoPYqjMvknbqKrg.text: We went 2 days in a row the first day we went in the afternoon, I got loaded hash browns with green chile sauce (medium spice level) and sausage, he got a duo of eggs benedict one benny goodman and one ham benedict III no complaints and since it was so late we had our run of the place. I had corned beef hash without the egg and I think it needed something in place of the egg it just didn't feel complete, I opted to switch my toast for a blueberry danish pancake if I had any complaints it would be that there was to little of the lemon cream cheese.  He had another benedict duo this time he had the Bella! Bella! Benny and the caprese benny the hash was cooked to a golden perfection and both of us cleaned our plates. Chilaquiles Benny  The only down side for me was that I ordered my eggs over medium and they were brought to me over easy.

Mz63lrtdhG4gtf6k0-iroQ.text: Oh my GOSH!!!! DELICIOUS!!! Everything was perfect!!! The atmosphere was amazing and the staff were super friendly! The mocha was perfect, just the right amount of sweet with the most amazing coffee I have ever tasted! The mmmm mmmm mosa was sooo good! I have found my breakfast spot! I might even make this like a tradition! I will go broke and get fat eating here and I am not ashamed!   So the last time we had really bad service. It's been a few since I've been back. Seriously, if you want waited on like royalty, ask for Jason. He definitely works the weekends, I think he said Tuesday was his day off? Anyways! Jason's MY MAN NOW! Hahahaha

Tqa5i31_i4-ck68ycRdZXg.text: The atmosphere is super awesome! and the menu looked unique and intresting . Although when we ordered we were not impressed with our food. I got the chili verde Benedict and my friend spud plate . Mine came with literally two little strands of pork and hers was just a pile Of potatoes with an egg on it. I thought this place would be so much more impressive food wise . Not impressed

9OAhKnePGuwGqdsNs4EjCA.text: Have been to snooze two times and each visit has not been far from impressive.  I have been a server for nine years so I try to be very understanding of the potential for things to go wrong within the restaurant, but a good attentive server whom is apologetic when things do go wrong can save a bad visit.  Each time I have been to snooze the servers are far from accommodating and unfriendly.  Today my friend and I came into eat and the visit started as an average experience.  We ordered quickly and the bartender was prompt.  Our food however took along time to come out, about 25-30 minutes and when it arrived both plates of good were very cold.  It took us about five minutes to track down a different employee to send it back. While we waited for our plates to be remade we were not offered refills on empty drinks or offered another bar drink. The plates than took another 20 minutes to be remade.  I was appreciative that the manager came and apologized and offered to take care of our entrees.  When one of the bartenders came and dropped the tab she said well as the meals were taken care of so hope that made you happy.  It was a very snide and rude remark and first of all we didn't want the meal comped.  We wanted hot food and in a timely fashion. Needless to say after her comment I will no longer return to snooze. I can make a better, more pleasant breakfast at home and I would rather give my business to a more pleasant and deserving staff.

2Ka9tImhLrmKgYho97lBvw.text: yes! this place is incredible! great prices, excellent food and awesome service! can't say enough good things about snooze! bear down!

cFB5_PqyaHF07_Y7xvdDEA.text: I have mixed feelings about snooze. The first time I went there was a 45 minute wait, but hey it was a busy Saturday morning and I was okay with that and the food was good and I overall had a good experience, the food was tasty, however then I went today (2/16/15) and it was a 15 minute wait, and then when I went in the hostess at the front said her partner would be back to seat us in a moment. After she said that, a new party came in and then the lady who came to seat us despite being told there are two parties only took the group that came in after us. When she returned another group had come in and the lady began prepping for that party to be seated (again ignoring us) and when the other person in my party asked about that she said in a snippy, rude tone "yes, i just sent you a text!" (she hadn't, we'd been waiting after having received the message that our table was ready for about 5-10 minutes) and then seated the second party to arrive after us. Then a different person took us to our table, finally. Ultimately, that woman (working at 10:30, who was seating people) was incredibly rude, and the experience was awful and we ended up leaving because that one person gave me such a horrible time. I truly hope this was an isolated experience and that she will learn some people skills. It's really sad because I had such a good experience the first time. We left and went to ncounter and enjoyed the rest of our day.

JSUVDiX7bxj6qyWAuhIGbg.text: BEST breakfast place ever, I will spend my last dollars on their Bella! Bella! Benny! any day. Everything is so flavorful and the staff is always so nice and in a good mood, absolutely love this place.

x7HKekJHiNaVtU901mzajw.text: First time experience, came in with a group of friends that have been in plenty of times and recommended it over a bunch of other breakfast places. They close at 2:30 and we arrived right around 12:30 on a week day, dining room was less than half occupied and the patio was maybe at 60% occupancy. We could see plenty of management just sitting around at tables not doing much other than talking with each other. Our food took about 35 mins to come out, okay but all of our egg and potato dishes came out ice cold. It was clear our plates had been sitting in the expo window for plenty of time. Come on management you're supposed to be leading a team, go and help your servers run some food. Big shoutout to our server though Toast Malone, really nice guy and could see our frustration, my 2 stars are for him, otherwise it would be a one. Thanks Snooze for a good first experience, please take note to there name, you definitely wanna sleep on this place.

lOFx8qFVdw5X7yThSVvmMw.text: Always love coming here! I'm not a big sweets person (especially for breakfast) but OH MY their pineapple upside down pancake is ahhmazing. I definitely recommend checking this place out if you haven't yet. Just be cautious that there's usually a wait (and for good reason).

IC4f7s1PnkChCwEVx1Zzrw.text: Love love love! Every time I go it is always great and the staff is awesome! The breakfast cocktails are delish! Amazing food, amazing atmosphere.

mA06v2XDLFqmIe9DVOPSvQ.text: Has great breakfast options but I'm not sure I would wait in line for a long time to receive this service.  Honestly, I go sometimes because I know Michael Phelps eats here A TON!

wCx0gdYJWfleVYPkFo9jqw.text: Today my boyfriend and I split the corned beef hash and a pancake flight. Hash was delicious, just a little greasy and I wish there were more hash browns in the mix. Pancake flight was fun, and there are so many unique flavors! We got the peanut butter cup, bourbon pumpkin, and sweet potato. Sweet potato was to die for, light and moist with just a hint of sweetness - perfect. Pumpkin was also great with a tasty glaze. The chocolate pb one was just too sweet for me; delicious but I am just not a big fan of super sweet breakfasts. All around tasty breakfast with reasonable prices and unique menu items.

0WZKhiphP63qlZ_Qu2jU1Q.text: Such a great place to have breakfast. I had the Benny duo 2 choices - the ham Benny and chililetos (beef) Benny. OMG both excellent but my fav was the beef one w pico de gillo and crispy hash. Hubby had the pancake flight with peanut butter, the house special berry and peach cobbler pancakes. The peach cobbler one was my fav too.   Staff is friendly and helpful if you don't know what you want. Outdoor seating is available too. Very retro decor.  Plus coffee is the best! Nice and strong.

NMQP6Grmsd7G5gBTKL0EBg.text: Very impressed. There's absolutely nothing that we didn't enjoy. Service. Food. Price. Can't complain at all.
