MgSA55h3MLvuFFIDetr4bw.text: This place is overrated, not really worth the hype. The pancakes are decent. The portions are small. The jam is flavorless. The eggs Benedict is meh. In the time it takes to wait for a table and get your food one can go to the grocery store and make this themselves. I'd rather go to IHOP or Denny's. I recommend First Watch if you're into a nice brunch!

uCf1uSrSPkX5nejW2WyvLA.text: Best brunch in Phoenix? Possibly.   This place is incredible. Went here this morning with a friend after we randomly saw it online and decided to give it a shot.   First of all, the decor is really cute and trendy. For lack of a better way to phrase it, it feels very college. Not surprising since it's located so close to ASU. We immediately loved the feel of the place. The menu has sooooo many good things on it so it was a struggle to decide what to order. Both of us ended up ordering the Spuds Deluxe. I got mine with bacon, ham, and red peppers. It was so delicious! The hash browns were fantastic and the meat was all well cooked but not overdone. I'd come here again in a heartbeat and I can't wait to do so so I can try more items on the menu. The pancakes and French toast sound extremely tasty!

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Spuds deluxe with bacon, ham, and red peppers!

cR7KOV6scy5qr7RDzwrYkw.text: This has become my top breakfast go to, usually to recoup from a night of drinking too much. Not only do the have a wide range of mimosas to cure the hangover, but all of the eggs Benny's and their wide variety of flavors has always left me satisfied. I honestly haven't been able to try anything else on the menu because being able to get an eggs benny duo is the only thing I have ever dreamed of.

aOuDkra4dfqSjfF7IW6fcQ.text: Service is great and the food is good but lacks a bit of flavour. If you're up for the typical American breakfast with an updated twist, this is the place to come. The atmosphere is upbeat and everyone looks like they've just come off the set of Portlandia. If you like oddly shaped hash browns and quirky ketchup come by and know it'll be a bit pricy.

CCPli-vcQLxfz3Cmq7Wqtg.text: Good food great vibes and alcohol in breakfast what else you need. Really amazing cocktails and they have a ping pong table too.

Tz_gF14LeI2vmfNhx5nUCw.text: Excellent place to go for breakfast. While visiting from New York we had the opportunity to dine at this place and the food and service was great. They use all local farm ingredients which enhances the flavors in your mouth. I would definitely recommend this establishment also because of the atmosphere as well.

M4FDkCmsG7s7nvhwGzF_Bw.text: I love this eatery! It has a fantastic vibe!!! The food is fabulous!!! The staff is fantastic!!! My only complaint is the occasional wait, but they are pretty good about turning over tables quickly, and you can always get Bartop service. Try the bacon Bloody Mary you won't regret it!!!

dvrXvCVSb3TB7itpKiLTqw.text: Fabulous little breakfast joint! Great vibe and very friendly staff.  We ordered the breakfast burrito, and after a night of boozing, it was like heaven wrapped inside a tortilla.    The only downfall was our food took a bit long to come out but given the amount of people that were there, it was understandable.  Great find on Yelp!  You won't be disappointed!

photos.caption: Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Amazing breakfast burrito!

YuY8AbIJD7fae5xtHsva7g.text: Service is very good but the wait time was a lot. However, they had ping pong table so it wasn't very boring to wait. Food is good but the portions are very small.

p_DTFsDJIZOeEhv4Eq9oJw.text: So delicious! I always go to a Snooze when there is one in the row I'm staying at. Loved the pancake flight!

sn4PY0VDlg6b0zqBD1cewQ.text: My wife and I visited Tempe for my nephew's graduation and were looking for a great breakfast to set the tone for the weekend. We weren't disappointed. There was a 25 minute wait as expected so we decided to sit at the bar and start the morning off with a Mimosa. First incredible surprise with a sparking champagne and orange juice. We talked to our barstool neighbor who happened to be an employee. I thought if he comes into work for breakfast this is going to be really good. At his suggestion my wife had an egg white omelette with spinach, mushrooms, and chicken sausage. It was a Home rum. I went with the breakfast burrito with sausage and topped with green chili. It was a spectacular. The restaurant is next door to ASU so it was full of college students which created a really great vibe with graduation season in full effect. Oh yeah we had a blueberry pancake with a cream cheese center that was sinful. This place is awesome.

M4Ob3ydczcDV19RKTXAUVA.text: The food was tasty and big portions...a real value for the money. The staff was friendly and attentive.

RDKmsxZZczP4EiTCB9AYOw.text: We sat outside on a perfect morning in Tempe.   Our server was Gloria and she could not have been nicer or more efficient.  If i was the restaurant owner, i would be blessed to have someone like her working for me!     I had the corned beef hash and my wife and daughter had the breakfast tacos.  Both were awesome. ..

6JgcNLYZq5I9w2fPjSQymw.text: Absolutely, loved my experience. The food was great! Are server "Rainbow" kill it, she gave us a delicous pancake to try on her. All the servers were so nice and came up to us and talked to us. By far some of the best service I have seen. They didn't even know it was my birthday, and they treated me like it was. Thank you! I will be back. Definitely recommend this place!

bhe0PAxxFbq8M0axzieN-g.text: Definitely a hot spot for breakfast or brunch.  This place has a very urban/contemporary fits in with the college crowd feel.    As soon as you walk in, everything is vibrant from the decor to the friendly staff.  Everyone was exceptional from a service stand point.   They have so many speciality cocktails and while I didn't get to try one this time around they are definitely in my radar for next time.  That's right....there will most certainly be a next time!!!!   I ordered the "OMG French Toast" and they did pack quite the flavor punch.   They come with mascarpone butter and a Carmel syrup glaze tops with fresh strawberries and coconut shavings.  While the serving wasn't large it was just right since towards the end of the meal it was getting almost too sweet too sugary.  So be warned of your not big into sweet stuff.      Prices are a tad on the higher side, but nothing that was a deal breaker. You can at least tell that the increase in cost goes to fresh ingredients and excellent attention to detail in the little things.    I hear they might be opening one in downtown Gilbert and can't wait as that's a little closer for me, but either way I will be coming back to taste other delightful items on the menu and throwback some cocktails!!! SUNDAY FUNDAY DONE RIGHT!!!!

J7IgmpJ9dYRHkdBOS9286Q.text: I've only been to Snooze early on weekdays as to avoid crowds so I can't complain about wait times and spotty service. I've had both the corned beef hash and Chile Verde eggs Benedict. Both were delicious. I tend to choose savory options, but will have to try their pancakes a French toast in the future.

Lgj-lEsWF5eddTZoNMt2mA.text: I absolutely love Snooze, but I had to deduct one star for this location because they completely messed up my order.  I ordered the pancake flight and my food came out significantly after the rest of my party and only 1 of the 3 pancakes were what I ordered.    Otherwise, I love this location - convenient to light rail and a great patio.  The pancake flight is amazing and the peanut butter cup is my absolute favorite...I crave these pancakes every once in a while, so can't wait to visit again and hope the service is better next time.

s4xEOday3LkNsfEQjEds9g.text: Slow service, small portion, coffee unfilled. Average food.  Could not get an English muffin right. Uncooked, then burnt. Server was kind of clueless.   To charge high price they need to deliver a good experience. Failed to do so.

bNuI-0_Ak4wVWiDFqQcUMg.text: Food was good. Mascarpone is amazing on blueberry muffins, pricey for smaller portion of quality foods. The server actually gave us a complimentary pancake being first-timers as we were.   Atmosphere was great. I like the decor--a bit retro but a la mode as well. Out door seating area is handsome and the red brick ties it all together. I love the decor of the place.   One complaint is that their orange juice tasted odd. I don't know if it was just the cup, but definitely not ordering that again.

Photo of Snooze, An A.M. Eatery - Tempe, AZ, United States. Late-harvest Benny with corned beef hash.

MN-250Ms0FYjRHTRSJkBbg.text: Came for brunch and was not disappointed.   I ordered the Chilaquiles Benedict with a spicy Bloody Mary.   The Chilaquiles were served as two croquet type servings, two tortillas with the toppings piled high on top. The helping of Barbacoa was fairly generous and really tender. The egg was done perfectly and the fresh chopped tomato salsa was really fresh. They aren't spicy but some Jalapeno Tobasco helped with that. I felt the portion was just right but if you're really hungry make sure you get hash browns on the side to fill up.   The Bloody Mary was OK. The mix they use is somewhat thick and spicy wasn't really that spicy. They also use a lot of pepper which I'm not personally a big fan of.   My wife got the Pot Pie which she devoured. The crust was soft and flaky and the gravy had great consistency as well. She had a mimosa with cranberry and lemonade and absolutely loved it.   We will definitely be back!

2--01TH8iAwhOmmg0P84hA.text: Great breakfast options just ridiculously long wait to get seated. But what can you say. When it's good, the people will follow. Love the pancake flight and their Benedict's options are very tasty.

cfmrQv24pgW2oiyfuu0V8Q.text: You just can't go wrong with Snooze! I've tried their restaurants in San Diego (Hillcrest and Del Mar) as well as Phoenix (Tempe). Damn good food and great staff. Highly recommend!

DntoN2Mt_-hyCLAtiIRk6Q.text: I make sure to visit Snooze when I'm in Tempe.  Always great service and food.  Love having a lot of gluten free options.  Everyone in our party shared pancakes and everyone agreed they were hands down the best pancakes ever.  Grilled cheese and tomato soup was another favorite. Cannot wait to visit again soon.

ZxzDI4ETeGKMrgrkiJBUkQ.text: YOU MUST GO! Diverse menu, amazing coffee and wonderful portion sizes.  My friend and I ordered the Breakfast tacos and the French toast and split them. Both were great. Also, sit on the patio if you can.  The weather + the view of the campus and its surroundings are wonderful.

oGPP1DeWRf2Ug0Tta30xiA.text: Came down to AZ for some baseball spring training. We stayed in Mesa and relied on yelp to help us find good places to eat. We found snooze a.m and it was delicious. The staff are great and friendly. The food was suburb. I got the breakfast tacos ( added bacon and jalapenos for the extra taste). The portions are good. If you are in the area, definitely stop by.

2CaBpeANiCm_54qvbM-0Xw.text: Random Yelp pick while on the road... Did not disappoint! Latte was average but food and service were amazing!

wRcz6_zVaU05FsCBEFKRGg.text: First time here a couple weekends ago, but the dish I got (shrimp & grits) was soooo good. Also tried a blueberry pancake, which was very delicious. There were too many other tempting menu choices to not return...

OC3YpYB9v0Hkm5xaHvSlbw.text: My boyfriend and I randomly decided to enjoy breakfast here this morning and we are considering moving to Phoenix because it was so amazing!!!! Not only was the food and drink incredible, but Kate provided us with the best service I've had in a very long time. Being someone who manages luxury hotels for a living, I know what good service looks like, and she blew us out of the water. We are sad to have to leave the restaurant to return back to our normal lives because she made our morning brighter! Thank you for the great service and amazing experience!!!

RoXopCf3924dIWbw9kSUGQ.text: Love snooze. I'd eat here every morning if I could. They take great care of their guest, I've even gotten a few pancakes on the house. I come into snooze a lot and I'd like to shoutout the server Steven as I've had him a lot over the last few months and he rocks. Also had a guy who went by merman this morning and he was super cool and attentive as well!! But overall never had a bad experience!!

aLn08NErYHd5RF8oU8Y5JQ.text: Cool spot. Great place to meet up with friends for something quick and unique dishes.  Came here on a whim for breakfast and was impressed. If you like eggs benedict order the Benny Duo because you get to choose two different styles, Perfect for someone who can't decide which ones to pick.

z5pWU9fM-Nkvt9JYeoxo0Q.text: We have been trying to come, being ASU territory it tends to be busy. Decided to come early, well worth it. The sandwich I am is mouth watering good, soft pretzel bun was perfect. My partner got the eggs Benedict, beyond pleased. Will be returning for another adventure in good eating.

qgLi38d-7rteN_yalt3NmA.text: Tasty little spot, good for mimosa brunch.  If you're a fan of gourmet pancake combos, they have a lovely selection.  Chicken sausage, while sustainably and locally sourced (most of their ingredients are) did not quite hit the spot.  The menu needs pork sausage biscuits and gravy.  Their Benedict's were killer.
